                    { 17161, "", "5 min", null, 1, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/anime/2/45821.jpg", 12671, "G - All Ages", 5.23m, null, 1, new DateTime(2010, 4, 15, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 1, "Special included in the Peeping Life: The Perfect Emotion's DVD release.", "Peeping Life: The Perfect Emotion Special", null, "Peeping Life（ピーピング・ライフ）-The Perfect Emotion-", null, 4, "https://myanimelist.net/anime/17161/Peeping_Life__The_Perfect_Emotion_Special" },
                    { 17163, "", "3 min per ep", null, 3, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/anime/9/45823.jpg", 12178, "G - All Ages", 5.42m, null, 1, new DateTime(2011, 1, 26, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 1, "3 bonus episodes centering around TV Asahi's female announcers.", "Peeping Life: The Perfect Evolution Specials", null, "Peeping Life（ピーピング・ライフ） -The Perfect Evolution-", null, 4, "https://myanimelist.net/anime/17163/Peeping_Life__The_Perfect_Evolution_Specials" },
                    { 17187, "", "58 min", null, 1, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/anime/8/46673.jpg", 2218, "R - 17+ (violence & profanity)", 7.42m, null, 2, new DateTime(2013, 6, 21, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 1, "The anime's story is set in 2027, one year after the end of the fourth non-nuclear war. New Port City is still reeling from the war's aftermath when it suffers a bombing caused by a self-propelled mine. Then, a military member implicated in arms-dealing bribes is gunned down.\n\nDuring the investigation, Public Security Section's Daisuke Aramaki encounters Motoko Kusanagi, the cyborg wizard-level hacker assigned to the military's 501st Secret Unit. Batou, a man with the \"eye that does not sleep,\" suspects that Kusanagi is the one behind the bombing. The Niihama Prefectural Police detective Togusa is pursuing his own dual cases of the shooting death and a prostitute's murder. Motoko herself is being watched by the 501st Secret Unit's head Kurutsu and cyborg agents.\n\n(Source: ANN)", "Koukaku Kidoutai Arise: Ghost in the Shell - Border:1 Ghost Pain", "Ghost in the Shell: Arise - Border 1: Ghost Pain", "攻殻機動隊ARISE -GHOST IN THE SHELL- border:1 Ghost Pain", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EAIJMcjprdE", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/anime/17187/Koukaku_Kidoutai_Arise__Ghost_in_the_Shell_-_Border_1_Ghost_Pain" },
                    { 17205, "The Cowboy Bebop series has been released in a Blu-ray format four times throughout the 21st century, with the fourth and most recent release being distributed by Bandai Visual in Japan beginning on December 21, 2012. The limited edition Blu-ray disc box set comes with a variety of paraphernalia, like production materials, audio commentaries, bonus footage, postcards, as well as Cowboy Bebop: Ein no Natsuyasumi—the latter of which would have been the first franchise-related animation in over a decade had it not been a series of still images. Alternatively titled \"Ein’s Summer Vacation,\" the special is paired with the song \"Doggy Dog,\" as performed in English by Seatbelts, responsible for much of the musical score that appears throughout the main anime series. The same track can be found on their album Cowboy Bebop Vitaminless. In 2013, distributor Anime Limited acquired a home video license for the United Kingdom; Part 1 of the Blu-ray collection was released on July 29, 2013. Appearing on the Part 1 disc, this would be the first time Western audiences could obtain a copy of the bonus short for themselves.", "1 min", null, 1, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/anime/1565/127387.jpg", 7930, "G - All Ages", 6.34m, null, 1, new DateTime(2012, 12, 20, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 1, "A Corgi can certainly dream! Taking a break from the frequent antics his colleagues get him into, Bebop crewmate Ein envisions himself sipping a tropical beverage on the beachside and scuba diving with Edward amid a barrier reef. \n\nIn this \"picture drama,\" Ein fantasizes about his ideal summer vacation.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Cowboy Bebop: Ein no Natsuyasumi", "Cowboy Bebop: Ein's Summer Vacation", "アインのなつやすみ", null, 4, "https://myanimelist.net/anime/17205/Cowboy_Bebop__Ein_no_Natsuyasumi" },
