                    { 13927, "", 31, new DateTime(2008, 9, 30, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/43451.jpg", 21866, null, new DateTime(2008, 4, 30, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Meat, trainer to the great Choujin superhero Kinnikuman.He thought his job was done helping his greatest subject become a master Choujin and king of his homeworld. But...what if upon waiting for his next subject,the little trainer was sent to another world...\n\nwhere Kinnikuman has yet to become a great hero yet... and is...female!? Welcome to the world of Kinnikuman Lady!\n\n(Source: MU)", "Kinnikuman Lady", null, "キン肉マンレディー", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/13927/Kinnikuman_Lady", 3 },
                    { 14022, "", null, new DateTime(2009, 3, 31, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/278793.jpg", 2741, 7.53m, new DateTime(2006, 2, 2, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Light novel spin-off mainly about school life played by the main series characters. The storyline revolves around class 3-Z's students and their wacky homeroom teacher Ginpachi-sensei.", "Gintama: 3-nen Z-gumi Ginpachi-sensei", null, "銀魂 3年Z組銀八先生", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/14022/Gintama__3-nen_Z-gumi_Ginpachi-sensei", 4 },
                    { 14124, "", 17, new DateTime(1994, 1, 30, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/20140.jpg", 21894, null, new DateTime(1989, 2, 5, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "This manga is deemed to be one of the works that initiated the \"irrational\" or \"unreasonable\" gag comic genre where the reason of its funniness cannot be explained by logic and traditional sense of humor, which made this title very popular among teens and early twenties at that time. One of the most popular characters that appeared in Uturun desu. was \"the otter,\" Kawauso-kun.\n\n(Source: Wikipedia)", "Utsurun desu.", null, "伝染るんです。", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/14124/Utsurun_desu", 5 },
                    { 14155, "", 1, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/270791.jpg", 15457, 6.55m, new DateTime(2003, 7, 20, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "About a boy of thirteen years who always tries to be a hero and for various reasons are involved with monsters, ending in his death, but it revived with the help a little thing (one might say that is the predecessor of innocence) and now must fight the Count ancient.\n\n(Source: MU)", "Continue", null, "コンティニュー", 3, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/14155/Continue", null },
                    { 14230, "", 42, new DateTime(1983, 11, 7, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/198355.jpg", 13541, 6.69m, new DateTime(1981, 12, 21, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Hakuo Gakuin has hired the Fuuma ninja clan to protect them from rival school Seishikan, who has been injuring all students who refuse to transfer. This is just the start of the Fuuma's adventure as they fight one last battle against their rival clan the Yasha, become involved in a war based around the 10 Sacred Swords, and fight against a rebellion within their own clan.\n\n(Source: ANN)", "Fuuma no Kojirou", null, "風魔の小次郎", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/14230/Fuuma_no_Kojirou", 10 },
                    { 14231, "", 122, new DateTime(1981, 9, 28, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/187140.jpg", 11437, 6.83m, new DateTime(1976, 12, 27, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Takane Kiku and Takane Ryuji are the children of a legendary world contender boxer. Kiku, the daughter seems to have inherited her father's boxing sense and tries to teach Ryuji to become a world contender. However, Ryuji hates boxing and gets picked on. After Kiku and Ryuji leave their hometown for Tokyo, Ryuji eventually learns to discover a passion for boxing after an encounter with a boxing prodigy, Kenzaki Jun. This will eventually lead him to learn crazy moves and out of the world opponents to become one of Japan's top junior boxers.\n\n(Source: ANN)", "Ring ni Kakero", null, "リングにかけろ", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/14231/Ring_ni_Kakero", 25 },
                    { 14232, "", 206, new DateTime(2009, 2, 3, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/20286.jpg", 21910, null, new DateTime(2000, 2, 8, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "At the end of Ring ni Kakero 1, Ryuuji Takane went up against Superstar Jun Kenzaki for the World Title. Now, 17 years later, Rindo Kenzaki, the son Jun Kenzaki and nephew of Ryuuji Takane, lives with Ishimatsu Katori, the \"Kenka Champion\" from Ryuuji and Jun's time. Rindo will meet up with a new generation of boxers to create a new Golden Japan Jr. to take on the world.\n\nSource: ANN", "Ring ni Kakero 2", "Put it all in the Ring 2", "リングにかけろ2", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/14232/Ring_ni_Kakero_2", 26 },
                    { 14368, "", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/22065.jpg", 2473, 7.57m, new DateTime(2006, 4, 25, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "Horitsuba Private Academy. Early Childhood division, Elementary school Division, Junior high school division, High school division, University, Graduate School. On an enormous campus, these individuals make up a huge, complete city built entirely on private property. Dormitories, Laboratories, movie theaters, hospitals, banks and so on; every possible institution is available in this campus-city, running in perfect order. Over 10,000 people attend school and live here, including, students, staff members, authorized persons, other family members, and the like. Exactly. since Horitsuba Academy is somewhat well-known all over, there are also lots of exchange students from foreign countries...", "Shiritsu Horitsuba Gakuen", null, "私立堀鐔学園", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/14368/Shiritsu_Horitsuba_Gakuen", null },
                    { 14377, "", 43, new DateTime(2012, 10, 18, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/152912.jpg", 2311, 7.59m, new DateTime(2009, 4, 17, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A retelling of Mazinger Z separate from the original series, as well the recent anime remake.", "Shin Mazinger Zero", null, "真マジンガーZERO", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/14377/Shin_Mazinger_Zero", 9 },
                    { 14414, "", 13, new DateTime(2012, 12, 13, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/273090.jpg", 5001, 7.28m, new DateTime(2005, 11, 29, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A series of 3-page long One Piece omake manga strips drawn by Eiichiro Oda. Their stories tend to parody other genres such as science fiction or fairy tales. Most of them were initially published as bonus content in One Piece Complete Collection between the 2nd Log (2005) and the 20th Log (2012). The anime adapted the five initial chapters in the recap episodes 279–283.\n\nThe Straw Hat Theater concept was created when Oda was given three blank sheets of paper by his editor and told to draw anything.\n\n(Source: One Piece Wiki)", "One Piece: Mugiwara Daigekijou", null, "ONE PIECE 麦わら大劇場", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/14414/One_Piece__Mugiwara_Daigekijou", 1 },
                    { 14674, "", 6, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/4/164810.jpg", 7620, 7.08m, new DateTime(1996, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "In this one shot volume Kazuhiro Fujita describes us the past of some characters of his masterpiece Ushio and Tora. In particular he describes the past of Tora, the tiger-monster that follows Ushio.", "Ushio to Tora Gaiden", null, "うしおととら外伝", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/14674/Ushio_to_Tora_Gaiden", 1 },
                    { 14841, "Durarara!! was published in English by Yen Press from January 24, 2012, to October 30, 2012. The series has also been released in Chinese by Kadokawa Taiwan Corporation from April 22, 2011, to November 9, 2011; in German by Egmont Manga from October 5, 2017, to April 4, 2018; in Italian by Edizioni Star Comics from January 14, 2012, to July 14, 2012; and in Polish by Waneko from February 6, 2015, to August 6, 2015.", 22, new DateTime(2011, 4, 17, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/202669.jpg", 1207, 7.83m, new DateTime(2009, 6, 17, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "In the flashy and restless streets of Tokyo's downtown Ikebukuro district, 15-year-old student Mikado Ryuugamine arrives wide-eyed and ready to inhale the exciting breath of city life. Up until now, his only insight into urban affairs was through an anonymous online group chat, where he found out about Ikebukuro's renowned legend. It says that a headless biker known only as the \"Black Rider\" roams Ikebukuro, executing its own justice against criminals.\n\nBut the district's quirks do not end there; Ikebukuro is swarming with so-called color gangs and their ceaseless conflicts. Among them, a colorless gang known as the Dollars is most noteworthy, as its founder, members, and numbers are all unknown. With odd cliques at every turn and uncanny tales coming to life, humans seem to mix with the supernatural, and Mikado soon dives into the deep sea of Ikebukuro's myths, deceits, and carefully planned out crises—a dangerous world, but possibly one where he belongs.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Durarara!!", "Durarara!!", "デュラララ!!", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/14841/Durarara", 4 },
                    { 14893, "Monogatari Series: First Season was published in English by Vertical Inc: first with Kizumonogatari as Kizumonogatari: Wound Tale on December 15, 2015; Bakemonogatari as Bakemonogatari: Monster Tale in three volumes from December 20, 2016, to April 25, 2017; Nisemonogatari as Nisemonogatari: Fake Tale in two volumes from June 27, 2017, to August 29, 2017; and Nekomonogatari: Kuro as Nekomonogatari (Black): Cat Tale on November 28, 2017. Vertical also released the series in a box set.", 107, new DateTime(2010, 7, 27, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/279887.jpg", 19, 8.91m, new DateTime(2006, 10, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "This is a story, a \"ghostory\" of sorts, about scars that bond, monsters that haunt, and fakes that deceive.\n\nThe story of Koyomi Araragi begins through a fateful encounter with the all-powerful, blonde-haired, \"hot-blooded, iron-blooded, and cold-blooded\" vampire, later introduced as Shinobu Oshino. Their tragic rendezvous results in the end of Araragi's life as a human and his subsequent rebirth as a vampire—a monster. However, this encounter is only the start of his meddlings with the supernatural. Koyomi's noble personality ultimately sees him getting further involved in the lives of others with supernatural afflictions. This is his desperate attempt at returning to a normal human life, in a paranormal world filled with nothing but tragedy, suffering, and inhumanity.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]\n\nThis entry includes the first season of the Monogatari Series.", "Monogatari Series: First Season", null, "〈物語〉シリーズ ファーストシーズン", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/14893/Monogatari_Series__First_Season", 6 },
                    { 14956, "", 100, new DateTime(1987, 7, 21, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/21633.jpg", 6159, 7.19m, new DateTime(1985, 8, 6, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Harukaze High School's photography club is anything but normal. All the oddballs in the school seem to join. And the craziest one has just arrived...an android built to take over the world! Though he'd rather just have a bowl of rice.\n\n(Source: Batoto)", "Kyuukyoku Choujin R", null, "究極超人あ～る", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/14956/Kyuukyoku_Choujin_R", 9 },
                    { 15018, "", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/40572.jpg", 2290, 7.6m, new DateTime(2005, 7, 31, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "The manga is a parody of the original Mobile Suit Gundam and features most of its characters in 4-koma strips. In addition, there are several \"sub-stories\" featured, including Captain Zaku-san, which features anthropomorphic versions of the mobile suits from Mobile Suit Gundam, and Gundam Sousei, which dramatizes the story of the creation of the Gundam franchise and features Yoshiyuki Tomino as well as other staff and cast members.\n\n(Source: Wikipedia)", "Kidou Senshi Gundam-san", null, "機動戦士ガンダムさん", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/15018/Kidou_Senshi_Gundam-san", null },
                    { 15035, "", 66, new DateTime(2017, 4, 3, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/158619.jpg", 13049, 6.72m, new DateTime(2009, 7, 3, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Shinichirou decides to look for a job in order to pay his rent, and his teacher suggests that he work for someone at their house, doing housekeeping. However, the person who hired him was Sakuya, a girl who is the 37th head of the Shimazu family, and her job is to exorcise and eliminate unwanted creatures. Shinichirou accidentally releases one of the creatures that Sakuya captures and they cooperate to catch it.\n\n(Source: MU)", "Isuca", null, "ISUCA", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/15035/Isuca", 9 },
                    { 15106, "", 1, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/21992.jpg", 13644, 6.68m, null, 2, "An bonus chapter included with the final volume of Getter Robo Āḥ. Dr. Hell discovers a biomechanical lifeform known as \"Kedora\" in the depths of Bardos Island, and realises that he can use it to fight Mazinger Z. \n\nThe story of this chapter was loosely adapted into the sixteenth episode of Shin Mazinger Shougeki! Z-Hen.", "Mazinger Z : Relic of Terror", null, null, 3, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/15106/Mazinger_Z___Relic_of_Terror", null },
                    { 15148, "", 14, new DateTime(2010, 8, 31, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/282847.jpg", 9906, 6.93m, new DateTime(2009, 7, 31, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A Gundam 00 side story. Planned to replace 00F in Gundam Ace. The story focuses on Innovades and Innovators.", "Kidou Senshi Gundam 00I", null, "機動戦士ガンダム00I", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/15148/Kidou_Senshi_Gundam_00I", 3 },
                    { 15200, "", 13, new DateTime(2020, 8, 6, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/22081.jpg", 22112, null, new DateTime(2003, 10, 14, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Nagasaki prefecture, in Japan, is a magical kingdom. While the wizards that live there are unable to cross the ocean, and are trapped in Kyuushu, they still pose enough of a threat that Americans dropped the bomb on them during WWII. The residents are worried that this will happen again, especially if the regular humans decide magicians are a threat.\n\nDaughter of the most powerful wizard alive, Mizukura Risuka is ten years old, and living outside Nagasaki, searching for her father and killing evil wizards. Her blood contains spells that control time, and allow her to fast-forward her own life. Her ultimate technique kicks in only when she dies bloodily—her blood will reform into herself at 27, at the height of her powers, for one minute.\n\nHer guide through the world of normal humans is Kugi Kizutaka, also aged ten. Kizutaka is a genius, and a sociopath. He believes the only way for people to be happy is to be ruled by him and views everyone he meets as a potential pawn, or slave. Including Risuka.\n\n(Source: easternstandard.pbworks.com)", "Shin Honkaku Mahou Shoujo Risuka", null, "新本格魔法少女りすか", 5, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/15200/Shin_Honkaku_Mahou_Shoujo_Risuka", 4 },
                    { 15305, "", null, new DateTime(1970, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/203669.jpg", 22138, null, new DateTime(1965, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The story is about Hyuma Hoshi, a promising young baseball pitcher who dreams of becoming a top star like his father Ittetsu Hoshi in the professional Japanese league. His father was once a 3rd baseman until he was injured in World War II and was forced to retire. The boy would join the ever popular Giants team, and soon he realized the difficulty of managing the high expectations. From the grueling training to battling the rival Mitsuru Hanagata on the Hanshin Tigers, he would have to take out his best pitching magic to step up to the challenge.\n\n(Source: Wikipedia)", "Kyojin no Hoshi", null, "巨人の星", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/15305/Kyojin_no_Hoshi", 19 },
                    { 15315, "", null, new DateTime(1978, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/203670.jpg", 22139, null, new DateTime(1975, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Hyuuma Hoshi is now adult and recovered from his injury.\nHe wants to prove he still the best pitcher.", "Shin Kyojin no Hoshi", null, "新巨人の星", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/15315/Shin_Kyojin_no_Hoshi", 11 },
                    { 15359, "", 14, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/22320.jpg", 3151, 7.47m, new DateTime(2001, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Getter Robo Āḥ is the fifth Getter Robo series chronologically.\n\nTaking place several years after Getter Robo Go, Earth is now a post-apocalyptic world. Hayato, now an aging scientist, has completed Professor Saotome's masterpiece, Getter Robo Āḥ. Piloting it are Ryoma's son Takuma, the human-dinosaur Kamui and the younger brother of Tayel, Baku. Alongside the reformed Dinosaur Empire, they fight the insectoid Andromeda Flow Country attacking from across time and space.", "Getter Robo Āḥ", "Getter Robo Āḥ", "ゲッターロボ アーク", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/15359/Getter_Robo_Āḥ", 3 },
                    { 15530, "", 120, new DateTime(2009, 3, 31, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/264674.jpg", 2527, 7.56m, new DateTime(1986, 7, 31, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The first story under the title \"Chibi Maruko-chan\" was published in the August 1986 edition of the shoujo manga magazine Ribon. Other semi-autobiographical stories by the author had appeared in Ribon and Ribon Original in 1984 and 1985, and were included in the first \"Chibi Maruko-chan\" tankōbon in 1987. The author first began writing and submitting strips in her final year of senior high school, although Shueisha (the publisher of Ribon and Ribon Original) did not decide to run them until over a year later. The author's intent was to write \"essays in manga form.\" Many stories are inspired by incidents from the author's own life, and some characters are based on her family and friends. The nostalgic, honest and thoughtful tone of the strip led to its becoming popular among a wider audience.\n\n(Source: Wikipedia)", "Chibi Maruko-chan", null, "ちびまる子ちゃん", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/15530/Chibi_Maruko-chan", 15 },
                    { 15691, "", 8, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/54433.jpg", 15886, 6.51m, new DateTime(2008, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Two manga artists are trying their best to have their work accepted by someone who appears to be their superior. However their latest work has been denied and their superior requests that they should write a manga about a drama where a man protects the peace of the world. The two get together and begin to write a manga about a boy who promises a girl protection!\n\n(Source: Mamo)", "20 Seiki Shounen: Ujiko Ujio Sakuhinshuu", null, "20世紀少年の脇役 ウジコウジオ作品集", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/15691/20_Seiki_Shounen__Ujiko_Ujio_Sakuhinshuu", 1 },
                    { 15918, "", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/23215.jpg", 14051, 6.65m, new DateTime(2001, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Different tales and adventures of the well-known Plue from Hiro Mashima's works.", "Rave: Plue no Inu Nikki", null, "RAVE プルの犬日記", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/15918/Rave__Plue_no_Inu_Nikki", 3 },
                    { 15921, "Mashima-en was published in English as Hiro Mashima's Playground by Kodansha USA as a 2-in-1 omnibus volume on October 30, 2018. It was also released in Brazilian Portuguese by Editora JBC from September 2012 to October 2012.", 8, new DateTime(2003, 10, 28, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/56849.jpg", 11586, 6.82m, new DateTime(1998, 7, 31, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A collection of one-shots by Hiro Mashima.", "Mashima-en", "Hiro Mashima's Playground", "ましまえん", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/15921/Mashima-en", 2 },
                    { 16010, "", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/30641.jpg", 11214, 6.84m, new DateTime(2002, 12, 27, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "K' (K-Dash) is a four volume doujinshi compilation released by Kodansha containing oneshots by a number of different authors and artists.\n\nThe first two issues contained short stories by published mangaka such as CLAMP and Ikumi Mia (amongst others).\nThe first issue was released in December 2002 at Comiket 63, while the second was released in March 2003 to commemorate the opening of the K-Square store.\n\nThese two issues contained short comedic stories from CLAMP; Tokyo Tower Kankeisha Kakui (characters from Chobits, Rayearth and Cardcaptor Sakura running into each other in the Tokyo Tower) and Murikuri Holic (Watanuki and Yuuko working at the K-Square store while characters from Murikuri look on)\n\nThe third and fourth issues consisted primarily of work from doujinshi artists. \n\nSynopsis: Ephidel/MAL", "K-Dash", "K-Dash", "K'", 6, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/16010/K-Dash", 4 },
                    { 16038, "Toriyama Akira ○-saku Gekijou was published in English as Akira Toriyama's Manga Theater by VIZ Media under the Shounen Jump imprint as a 3-in-1 omnibus volume on December 7, 2021.", 38, new DateTime(1994, 9, 30, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/5/252072.jpg", 9678, 6.94m, new DateTime(1977, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "3-volume compilation containing many of Toriyama's one-shots.", "Toriyama Akira ○-saku Gekijou", "Akira Toriyama's Manga Theater", "鳥山明○作劇場", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/16038/Toriyama_Akira_○-saku_Gekijou", 3 },
                    { 16088, "", 6, new DateTime(2007, 3, 25, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/36021.jpg", 22304, null, new DateTime(2006, 11, 24, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "In C.E. 73, tensions between Naturals and Coordinators continue to persist, eventually leading to another war between the Earth Alliance and PLANT. Sven Cal Bayan is a Natural pilot of the elite EA squad, the Phantom Pain, and carries out his squad's various anti-Coordinator missions without fail. Selene McGriff is a Coordinator researcher at the neutral Deep Space Survey and Development Organization (DSSD) and a developer of the GSX-401FW Stargazer space exploration mobile suit. Though their backgrounds are completely different, the expanding war will nevertheless force their paths to collide.\n\nIn the manga, the previously uncertain fate of Selene and Sven is revealed.\n\n(Source: ANN)", "Kidou Senshi Gundam SEED C.E.73 Stargazer", null, "機動戦士ガンダムSEED C.E.73 STARGAZER", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/16088/Kidou_Senshi_Gundam_SEED_CE73_Stargazer", 1 },
                    { 16110, "", null, new DateTime(2009, 4, 20, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/178356.jpg", 11141, 6.85m, new DateTime(2009, 3, 20, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Two strange aliens are terrorizing the home planet of Tarble, Vegeta's younger brother, they have followed him to earth. Read as Goku and his friends try to defeat these aliens at the request of Tarble.", "Dragon Ball: Ossu! Kaettekita Son Gokuu to Nakama-tachi!!", null, "DRAGONBALL オッス!帰ってきた孫悟空と仲間たち!", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/16110/Dragon_Ball__Ossu_Kaettekita_Son_Gokuu_to_Nakama-tachi", 2 },
                    { 16168, "", 12, new DateTime(1986, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/72047.jpg", 22325, null, new DateTime(1986, 1, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "As the continuation of Zeta Gundam, this series once again follows the story of the Anti Earth Union Group (AEUG) battleship Argama after Zeta's final episode. To fight off the Axis Zeon, now called the Neo Zeon, Captain Bright Noa recruits a group of teenage junk collectors led by the loudmouthed but powerful Newtype Judau Ashta to pilot the Argama's mobile suits. Now sporting a line up of the behemoth MSZ-010 Double Zeta Gundam and the returning MSZ-006 Zeta Gundam, RX-178 Gundam Mk-II and Gundam-like MSN-00100 Hyaku Shiki, the group is nicknamed the Gundam Team. As such, this became the first of a number of Gundam series where a team of Gundam mobile suits fight alongside each other regularly. The climax takes place at Side 3 in the Battle of Axis.\n\n(Source: Gundam Wikia)", "Kidou Senshi Gundam ZZ", null, "機動戦士ガンダムZZ", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/16168/Kidou_Senshi_Gundam_ZZ", 3 },
                    { 16456, "", 10, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/74077.jpg", 22373, null, new DateTime(1990, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The story of Gundam F91 revolves around teenage space colonist Seabook Arno, his girlfriend Cecily Fairchild, and the efforts of the Crossbone Vanguard militia, led by Cecily's grandfather Meitzer Ronah, to establish an aristocracy known as \"Cosmo Babylonia\". In keeping with Gundam tradition, the civilian Seabook is forced by circumstance to pilot the F91 Gundam, coincidentally designed in part by his estranged mother, Dr. Monica Arno.\n\n(Source: Gundam Wikia)", "Kidou Senshi Gundam F91", null, "機動戦士ガンダム F91", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/16456/Kidou_Senshi_Gundam_F91", 1 },
