                    { 23718, "Sword Art Online: Aincrad was published in English by Yen Press in a 2-in-1 omnibus on March 25, 2014.", 12, new DateTime(2012, 4, 9, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/77727.jpg", 11550, 6.82m, new DateTime(2010, 8, 9, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "In the year 2022, gamers rejoice as Sword Art Online—a VRMMORPG (Virtual Reality Massively Multiplayer Online Role Playing Game) like no other—opens its virtual doors, allowing players to take full advantage of the ultimate in gaming technology: NerveGear, a system that allows users to completely immerse themselves in the game world by manipulating their brain waves to create a wholly realistic gaming experience. But when the game goes live, the elation of the players quickly turns to horror as they discover that, for all its amazing features, SAO is missing one of the most basic functions of any MMORPG—a log-out button. Now trapped in the virtual world of Aincrad, their bodies held captive by NerveGear in the real world, users are issued a chilling ultimatum: conquer all one hundred floors of Aincrad to regain your freedom. But in the warped world of SAO, \"game over\" means certain death-both virtual and real...\n\n(Source: Yen Press)", "Sword Art Online: Aincrad", "Sword Art Online: Aincrad", "ソードアート・オンライン アインクラッド", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/23718/Sword_Art_Online__Aincrad", 2 },
                    { 23751, "Monogatari Series: Second Season was published in English by Vertical Inc. with Nekomonogatari: Shiro as Nekomonogatari (White): Cat Tale on February 27, 2018; Kabukimonogatari as Kabukimonogatari: Dandy Tale on May 17, 2018; Hanamonogatari as Hanamonogatari: Flower Tale on June 20, 2018; Otorimonogari as Otorimonogatari: Decoy Tale on August 28, 2018; Onimonogatari as Onimonogatari: Demon Tale on October 30, 2018; and Koimonogatari as Koimonogatari: Love Tale on January 29, 2019.", 199, new DateTime(2011, 12, 19, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/181553.jpg", 22, 8.9m, new DateTime(2010, 10, 26, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "This is a story. A story about choices and consequences, confessions resulting in love and rejection, and decisions leading to sacrifice and tragedy.\n\nKoyomi Araragi's decision to save a blonde vampire and meddle with the supernatural resulted in his death as a human and rebirth as a monster. But this was only one of the countless tragedies and choices that Koyomi would be faced with, and he is confronted with the fact that his seemingly unshakeable and hard-earned relationships do not last. As strange oddities continue to manifest in the world around him, he is faced with impossible choices—to sever his ties with those he loves, or eternally remain a part of the world of monsters and apparitions and watch the world crumble as a result. To accept or reject a confession, and sacrifice his all for the sake of others. However, both of these paths could lead to tragedy and farewells.\n\nThis is a story. A story about Koyomi Araragi coming to realize the consequences of his choices.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]\n\nThis entry includes the second season of the Monogatari Series.", "Monogatari Series: Second Season", null, "〈物語〉シリーズ セカンドシーズン", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/23751/Monogatari_Series__Second_Season", 6 },
                    { 23869, "", 5, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/282712.jpg", 48560, null, new DateTime(1989, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "December, Universal Century 0079. Zeon intelligence has identified a prototype Federation Gundam under development in a Federation base in the Arctic. Elite Zeon MS commandos are dispatched to destroy the prototype, but before they can accomplish their mission the Gundam is launched into space. When the Gundam turns up in a Federation R&amp;D base inside the neutral space colony Side 6, the Principality launches a covert operation to destroy the Gundam. The raid fails and Zeon will launch a nuclear strike against the colony unless the last remaining commando can eliminate the Gundam.\n\n(source: Wikipedia)", "Kidou Senshi Gundam 0080: Pocket no Naka no Sensou", null, "機動戦士ガンダム0080 ポケットの中の戦争", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/23869/Kidou_Senshi_Gundam_0080__Pocket_no_Naka_no_Sensou", 1 },
                    { 23942, null, 156, new DateTime(2015, 12, 24, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/38690.jpg", 952, 7.91m, new DateTime(2007, 7, 31, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, null, "Kimi ni Todoke", null, "君に届け", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/23942/Kimi_ni_Todoke", 16 },
                    { 24033, null, null, new DateTime(1987, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/159720.jpg", 13044, 6.72m, new DateTime(1961, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, null, "Osomatsu-kun", null, "おそ松くん", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/24033/Osomatsu-kun", 34 },
                    { 24294, "Ao Haru Ride was published in English by VIZ Media under the Shojo Beat imprint from October 2, 2018, to October 6, 2020. It was also published in French as Blue Spring Ride by Kana from July 5, 2013, to July 1, 2016; in German by Tokyopop from September 17, 2015, to December 17, 2015; in Polish as Ścieżki Młodości: Ao Haru Ride by Waneko from February 20, 2014, to February 20, 2016; in Spanish by Editorial Ivrea as Aoha Ride from February 2015 to February 2016; in Turkey as Gençlik Yolculuğu by Gerekli Şeyler; and in Brazilian Portuguese by Panini Comics from March 2015 to March 2017. The series was adapted into a Japanese live-action film that was released on December 13, 2014.", 53, new DateTime(2015, 2, 12, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/256907.jpg", 547, 8.12m, new DateTime(2011, 1, 12, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "While most girls desire popularity among boys, Futaba Yoshioka wants the exact opposite. After attracting many admirers back in middle school which resulted in her being shunned by her female classmates, she decided that high school will be her chance to revamp her image. Therefore, she starts acting unfeminine and indifferent to boys, allowing her to make some \"friends\" along the way. \n\nLittle does Futaba know, her life will take another drastic turn when her first love, Kou Mabuchi, returns after his sudden disappearance years ago in middle school. Despite his extended absence, the fond memories they shared together still linger in her mind, and she wishes to return to those days. But she realizes that the sweet, gentle boy of the past has completely vanished, and in his place stands someone cold and pessimistic. While he admits that her feelings for him back then were mutual, he warns that they can never go back to the past, as everything, including him, has changed. \n\nAo Haru Ride follows Futaba as she searches for true love and friendship, all while trying her best to stay true to herself. \n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Ao Haru Ride", "Ao Haru Ride", "アオハライド AO―HARU―RIDE", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/24294/Ao_Haru_Ride", 13 },
                    { 24295, "Mahou Shoujo Kazumi★Magica: The Innocent Malice was published in English as Puella Magi Kazumi Magica: The Innocent Malice by Yen Press from June 25, 2013, to May 27, 2014. It was also released in Brazilian Portuguese as Puella Magi Kazumi Magica: Malicia Inocente by NewPOP Editora from July 2015 to December 2016.", 23, new DateTime(2012, 11, 23, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/5/41783.jpg", 7686, 7.07m, new DateTime(2011, 1, 23, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A girl named Kazumi wakes up to find that she has been kidnapped and stripped of her memories. She is rescued by two girls claiming to be her best friends, Umika Misaki and Kaoru Maki, who take her back to where they live. While getting settled into this unfamiliar place, Kazumi is attacked by a witch and suddenly transforms into a magical girl!\n \nAfter discovering her powers, her two roommates reveal to Kazumi that they are magical girls as well, the three of them belonging to a group called the Pleiades Saints whose goal is to fight witches. As Kazumi's \"new\" life begins, things start to get even stranger when bizarre events start to take place around the city.\n\nMahou Shoujo Kazumi★Magica: The Innocent Malice explores Kazumi's readjustment to a world she has forgotten and the realization that her true enemies are a lot closer to her than she thinks...\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Mahou Shoujo Kazumi★Magica: The Innocent Malice", "Puella Magi Kazumi★Magica: The Innocent Malice", "魔法少女かずみ★マギカ〜The innocent malice〜", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/24295/Mahou_Shoujo_Kazumi★Magica__The_Innocent_Malice", 5 },
                    { 24312, "", 5, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/39215.jpg", 48685, null, new DateTime(1996, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The third installment of the Lupin III manga series.", "Lupin III S", null, "ルパン三世S", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/24312/Lupin_III_S", 1 },
                    { 24456, "Mahou Shoujo Oriko★Magica was published in English as Puella Magi Oriko Magica by Yen Press from July 23, 2013, to October 29, 2013, and later as an omnibus volume. It was also released in Brazilian Portuguese by NewPOP Editora from June 2014 to September 2014.", 7, new DateTime(2011, 6, 12, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/99257.jpg", 13855, 6.67m, new DateTime(2011, 5, 11, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Yuma Chitose is a young and carefree child, until her parents are abruptly killed by a witch right before her eyes. Left distraught and traumatized at the scene, she is shielded from the same fatal fate by a magical girl named Kyouko Sakura. Having always felt weak, Yuma believes that becoming a magical girl is the only way for her to become stronger. But Kyouko dismisses the daunting idea, encouraging the young girl to live a normal life.\n\nYuma's curiosity, however, only flourishes when Kyuubey appears before her and tells her that Oriko Mikuni thinks she would make a good magical girl. But who is Oriko? And why has she taken an interest in Yuma? Meanwhile, magical girls are being targeted and killed. Rumor has it that the one hunting them is not a witch, but another magical girl.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Mahou Shoujo Oriko★Magica", "Puella Magi Oriko★Magica", "魔法少女おりこ★マギカ", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/24456/Mahou_Shoujo_Oriko★Magica", 2 },
                    { 24457, "Mahou Shoujo Madoka★Magica was published in English as Puella Magi Madoka★Magica by Yen Press from May 29, 2012, to December 11, 2012. The series was also released as a 3-in-1 omnibus on August 18, 2020. It was published in Brazilian Portuguese by NewPOP Editora.", 12, new DateTime(2011, 5, 29, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/260243.jpg", 633, 8.07m, new DateTime(2011, 2, 11, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Fourteen-year-old Madoka Kaname has a surreal dream about a strange creature and a girl in trouble. The next morning, a mysterious girl named Homura Akemi transfers into Madoka's class; to her surprise, Homura appears to be the exact same girl that she saw in her dream.\n\nLater that day, Madoka hears a plea for help in her head. It turns out that the cries belong to an injured Kyuubey, the cat-like creature who was also in her dream. But she finds Homura at Kyuubey's location, who warns Madoka to get away from the small entity. Making the connection that her new classmate attacked the helpless creature, Madoka takes Kyuubey and runs away with the help of best friend Sayaka Miki.\n\nAfter their escape, Kyuubey offers the girls an enticing opportunity: become a magical girl in exchange for having any wish granted. However, not everything is as it seems, as the weight of their wishes may be a lot heavier than they might have expected.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Mahou Shoujo Madoka★Magica", "Puella Magi Madoka★Magica", "魔法少女まどか★マギカ", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/24457/Mahou_Shoujo_Madoka★Magica", 3 },
                    { 24499, "", 5, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/275369.jpg", 1843, 7.68m, new DateTime(2010, 10, 27, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Five short stories, one for each of the Bakemonogatari girls which appeared in the complete guidebook.\n\nHitagi Buffet\nMayoi Room\nSuruga Court\nNadeko Pool\nTsubasa Song", "Bakemonogatari Short Stories", null, "化物語アニメコンプリートガイドブック", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/24499/Bakemonogatari_Short_Stories", null },
                    { 24548, "", 4, new DateTime(2011, 1, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/282846.jpg", 48727, null, new DateTime(2010, 8, 31, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Mobile Suit Gundam 00I 2314 occurs within the timeline of Mobile Suit Gundam 00 The Movie: A wakening of the Trailblazer. \nThe manga features the revived Celestial Being shadow group known as Fereshte, and their encounters with the ELS.\n\n(Source: Gundam Wikia).", "Kidou Senshi Gundam 00I 2314", null, "機動戦士ガンダム00I 2314", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/24548/Kidou_Senshi_Gundam_00I_2314", 1 },
                    { 24561, "Kamisama no Iutoori was published in Italian by Edizioni Star Comics from November 15, 2014, to March 14, 2015. The series was adapted into a Japanese live-action film that premiered on November 15, 2014.", 21, new DateTime(2012, 10, 8, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/309107.jpg", 4097, 7.36m, new DateTime(2011, 2, 8, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Shun Takahata finds his daily life boring and uneventful—that is, until his teacher's head explodes. Out of the remains of the corpse comes forth a Daruma doll, marking the beginning of a sadistic game. All who move when the Daruma is looking will be killed, and the winner is the one to push the button on the Daruma's back.\n\nShun manages to remain calm through the slaughter of his classmates and becomes the sole victor in his class. But upon the game's completion, he finds that he is still locked inside the school and is forced to play through another hellish event. Who exactly is concocting these mysterious games, and is there any end in sight? Shun gives his all to find other survivors and work together to survive the Daruma's murderous tests.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Kamisama no Iutoori", "As the Gods Will", "神さまの言うとおり", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/24561/Kamisama_no_Iutoori", 5 },
                    { 24679, "Shin Kidou Senki Gundam W: Endless Waltz - Haisha-tachi no Eikou was published in English as Mobile Suit Gundam Wing: Glory of the Losers by Vertical Inc. from July 18, 2017 to November 5, 2019.", 85, new DateTime(2017, 11, 24, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/148227.jpg", 3763, 7.4m, new DateTime(2010, 9, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Centuries in the future, in the year After Colony 195, Earth is surrounded by orbiting space colonies. The colonists are cruelly oppressed by the Earth Alliance, which uses huge humanoid fighting machines called \"mobile suits\" to control the populace. Behind this tyranny is the secret society called \"Oz,\" which has infiltrated the Alliance military and steered it towards its repressive course.\n\nNow, the space colonies are ready to strike back. Five young pilots, equipped with advanced mobile suits called \"Gundams,\" are sent to Earth to wage guerilla war against Oz and its Alliance puppets. The war to decide humanity's destiny begins...\n\n(Source: MU)", "Shin Kidou Senki Gundam Wing: Endless Waltz - Haisha-tachi no Eikou", "Mobile Suit Gundam Wing: Glory of the Losers", "新機動戦記ガンダムW ENDLESS WALTZ 敗者たちの栄光", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/24679/Shin_Kidou_Senki_Gundam_Wing__Endless_Waltz_-_Haisha-tachi_no_Eikou", 14 },
                    { 24812, "", 4, new DateTime(2010, 12, 25, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/282854.jpg", 48759, null, new DateTime(2010, 9, 25, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The manga adaption of the Gundam 00 movie.", "Kidou Senshi Gundam 00: A Wakening of the Trailblazer", null, "機動戦士ガンダム00　―A wakening of the Trailblazer―", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/24812/Kidou_Senshi_Gundam_00__A_Wakening_of_the_Trailblazer", 1 },
                    { 24822, "Trinity Seven: 7-nin no Mashotsukai has been published in English as Trinity Seven: The Seven Magicians by Yen Press since May 19, 2015; in Italian by Panini Comics under the Planet Manga imprint since January 25, 2014; and will be published in Spanish by Ivrea España beginning January 2016.", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/63963.jpg", 2056, 7.64m, new DateTime(2010, 12, 8, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "Arata Kasuga is living an ordinary life with his cousin, Hijiri, when a mysterious happening called a \"Breakdown Phenomenon\" makes her vanish before his very eyes. Determined to eradicate the Breakdown Phenomenon and get Hijiri back, Arata enrolls at Royal Biblia Academy. It's a tough road ahead, but nothing's impossible when you've got seven beautiful girls--each a master of her own magical art—by your side! The romantic comedy and sometimes-serious wizard school story begins!\n\n(Source: Yen Press)", "Trinity Seven: 7-nin no Mashotsukai", "Trinity Seven: The Seven Magicians", "トリニティセブン 7人の魔書使い", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/24822/Trinity_Seven__7-nin_no_Mashotsukai", null },
                    { 24881, "", 78, new DateTime(2023, 11, 10, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/5/252110.jpg", 48761, null, new DateTime(1984, 7, 9, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Jingi Kikukawa is a guy who during his 13 years of life was never defeated by anyone, a year ago he was transferred to the school of Touun, each school is protected by a leader of warriors provided art lovers quarrels, after an appointment with Yasuoka (Tooun leader), Jingi is victorious, made him become the new leader of the school, however, will soon meet his nemesis, Sho Takeshima, head of a gang that controls the western Japan, who will teach a good lesson in the fight.", "Otokozaka", null, "男坂", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/24881/Otokozaka", 11 },
                    { 24901, "", null, new DateTime(2011, 2, 22, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/167394.jpg", 7033, 7.12m, new DateTime(2010, 2, 23, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A series of side stories of Durarara!! bundled with the first press release of all 13 DVD volumes of 1st season of anime.", "Durarara!! Minna wa Nakayoshi", null, "デュラララ!! みんなはなかよし", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/24901/Durarara_Minna_wa_Nakayoshi", 13 },
                    { 25096, "In 2012, Gin no Saji won the Grand Prize at the 5th Manga Taisho Award and the 58th Shogakukan Manga Award in the shounen manga category. Gin no Saji won the first Japan Food Culture Contents Award in 2013 and was nominated for the 19th annual Tezuka Osamu Cultural Prize in 2015. The series was published in English as Silver Spoon by Yen Press from February 27, 2018 to September 22, 2020. It has also been published in English by Shogakukan Asia since December 5, 2014 and in Polish by Waneko since December 2013.", 131, new DateTime(2019, 11, 26, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/231500.jpg", 271, 8.33m, new DateTime(2011, 4, 5, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Yuugo Hachiken has spent every waking moment of his life studying in order to achieve the highest grades in school. Finally cracking under the pressure of his parents' expectations for success, Yuugo decides to leave his city life and enroll in the rural Ooezo Agricultural High School. However, he has absolutely no experience with farming!\n\nAttempting to utilize the skills he has built through studying, Yuugo begins to pursue the true meaning of having a dream and perhaps discover his own along the way. But life is not as simple as it seems to be, and Yuugo must learn that hardship may appear when you least expect it.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Gin no Saji", "Silver Spoon", "銀の匙 Silver Spoon", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/25096/Gin_no_Saji", 15 },
                    { 25146, "", 1, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/40484.jpg", 11944, 6.8m, new DateTime(2011, 4, 3, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "One Piece x Toriko crossover chapter.", "Jisshoku! Akuma no Mi!!", null, "実食! 悪魔の実!!", 3, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/25146/Jisshoku_Akuma_no_Mi", null },
                    { 25409, "High School DxD has been published in English by Yen Press under the Yen On imprint since October 20, 2020.", 240, new DateTime(2018, 3, 19, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/203327.jpg", 460, 8.17m, new DateTime(2008, 9, 19, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Perverted youth Issei Hyoudou's dreams seem to come true when the beautiful Yuuma Amano asks him out on a date. But when she reveals her identity as a fallen angel and tries to kill Issei, his death seems imminent—until an upperclassman named Rias Gremory rescues him. When he wakes up again, she reveals herself to be a devil. In order to save Issei, she reincarnated him as one of her kind, making him her new servant.\n\nThis turn of events thrusts Issei into the world of the supernatural. As he is introduced to the various devils in the Occult Research Club at his high school, he must learn to adapt to this new world filled with devils and fallen angels. Setting his sights on becoming powerful, he must decide what is truly important to him as he comes to realize that the life of a devil is not an easy one.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "High School DxD", "High School DxD", "ハイスクールD×D", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/25409/High_School_DxD", 25 },
                    { 25515, "JoJo no Kimyou na Bouken Part 8: JoJolion won the Grand Prize in the manga category at the 17th Japan Media Arts Festival in 2013.", 110, new DateTime(2021, 8, 18, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/179885.jpg", 174, 8.47m, new DateTime(2011, 5, 18, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "In 2011, childhood friends Yasuho Hirose and Joushuu Higashikata discover a naked man buried in the ground just outside the town of Morioh. The man has no memory of his name or previous life; the only thing he remembers about himself is how to use his Stand, a supernatural ability that takes the form of a humanoid creature. The stranger is quickly given a name, Jousuke, and Joushuu's father Norisuke decides to adopt him into the Higashikata household until he can find his own home.\n\nAs Jousuke begins to investigate his past, it becomes apparent that he is no ordinary amnesiac. There is much more to his identity than he first suspected, and, as he is thrust into a series of high-stakes Stand battles, he soon begins unravelling a deadly conspiracy that encompasses the entire town.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "JoJo no Kimyou na Bouken Part 8: JoJolion", null, "ジョジョの奇妙な冒険 Part8 ジョジョリオン", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/25515/JoJo_no_Kimyou_na_Bouken_Part_8__JoJolion", 27 },
                    { 25541, "", 17, new DateTime(2006, 5, 18, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/41101.jpg", 48873, null, new DateTime(2003, 9, 18, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 3, "This is a spin-off of the Fuuma Kojirou and spend a few years after the events present in the original work of Masami Kurumada. The remaining members of Fuuma clan are Kojiro and his disciples, Komomo, older, and Tora. At this point arises Renya Yagyu Ranko brother was determined to obtain the legendary sword Fuurin Kazan, which was said to belong to Kojiro. However, this was only a prelude to something bigger. A portion of obscure Yagyu family, which forms the Karmasho clan, is determined to resurrect a mysterious and evil, sacrificing many people it takes, is Himeko Hojo or priestess of Fuuma. Many characters known by readers of the original manga return, in an environment full of intrigues and conspiracies.\n\nThe story and art are made by Yuri Satoshi, which has a trace similar to Masami Kurumada, the original author of the work.", "Fuuma no Kojirou: Yagyuu Ansatsuchou", null, "風魔の小次郎 柳生暗殺帖", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/25541/Fuuma_no_Kojirou__Yagyuu_Ansatsuchou", 3 },
                    { 25592, "", 12, new DateTime(1997, 2, 28, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/41179.jpg", 48883, null, new DateTime(1996, 1, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Kisaragi Honey is an average teenage girl until her father is kidnapped by the evil Panther Claw organization. Donning a magical choker and ring she transforms into Cutey Honey and begins a mission of justice!", "Cutie Honey Flash", null, "キューティーハニーF", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/25592/Cutie_Honey_Flash", 4 },
                    { 25594, "Evangelion: ANIMA, written by Evangelion mecha designer Ikuto Yamashita, presents an alternate universe look at the world of Neon Genesis Evangelion if Shinji had stopped Third Impact during End of Evangelion. The series was published digitally in English as Neon Genesis Evangelion: ANIMA by Seven Seas Entertainment under the Airship imprint from August 22, 2019 to June 24, 2021, and in print from October 29, 2019 to August 3, 2021.", 45, new DateTime(2013, 2, 24, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/244538.jpg", 4874, 7.29m, new DateTime(2007, 11, 23, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Three years after Shinji Ikari prevented Third Impact during the Battle at NERV HQ, the Earth is at peace once more. NERV has been reorganized under the command of Misato Katsuragi, and Shinji leads the EVA team with the help of his friends Asuka Langley Souryuu and Rei Ayanami. Advancements in technology have led the organization to upgrade its Evangelions, and three Series-0.0 units have been placed into low Earth orbit to watch over the planet.\n\nJust as NERV is on the verge of upgrading Shinji's Unit-01 Type-F, one of the Unit-0.0s goes out of control and crashes near Tokyo-3. Soon after, NERV is attacked by a mysterious Angel Carrier—an oddly modified Mass Production Evangelion. It is now up to Shinji, Asuka, and Rei to stop this attack and identify their mysterious new enemy.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Evangelion: ANIMA", "Neon Genesis Evangelion: ANIMA", "エヴァンゲリオン ANIMA", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/25594/Evangelion__ANIMA", 5 },
                    { 25632, "", 13, new DateTime(2009, 9, 25, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/41714.jpg", 18482, 6.2m, new DateTime(2007, 5, 25, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The series is the \"first official super-deformed series\" based on Neon Genesis Evangelion. The Gainax/Khara franchise spin-off spoofs the psychological science fiction drama by reimagining the characters as classmates in Tokyo-3's Nerv School, headed by Principal Gendou Ikari and Misato-sensei. The student body includes three different Rei \"sisters,\" the EVA-01 mobile weapon reimagined as the school bully Evanchou, and the ill-fated Jet Alone robot as JA-ko, a \"hidden character\" in the form of a shy android girl.", "Petit Eva: Evangelion@School", null, "ぷちえゔぁ〜EVANGELION@SCHOOL〜", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/25632/Petit_Eva__EvangelionSchool", 1 },
                    { 25633, "", 19, new DateTime(2009, 7, 25, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/41715.jpg", 48881, null, new DateTime(2007, 10, 25, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Alternative version of Petit Eva.", "Petit Eva Bokura Tanken Doukoukai", null, "ぷちえヴぁ ぼくら探検同好会", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/25633/Petit_Eva_Bokura_Tanken_Doukoukai", 1 },
                    { 25665, "Shinsengumi was digitally published in English as The Shinsengumi by Digital Manga Guild on May 22, 2016.", 5, new DateTime(1963, 8, 31, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/175756.jpg", 8198, 7.04m, new DateTime(1962, 11, 30, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "This is the tale of a young man who joins a band of Ronin who are fighting against the end of the Samurai era in order to find his father's killer. But bit by bit he becomes disillusioned with the people he has thrown in with and wonders if there is another way...\n\n(Source: MU)", "Shinsengumi", "The Shinsengumi", "新選組", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/25665/Shinsengumi", 1 },
                    { 25822, "", 36, new DateTime(2015, 11, 25, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/147435.jpg", 48910, null, new DateTime(2010, 6, 25, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Shin Kidou Senki Gundam Wing: Frozen Teardrop is a novel that takes place approximately 22 years after the events of the Shin Kidou Senki Gundam Wing TV series and Endless Waltz OVA and movie in the new \"Mars Century\" (M.C.) era.", "Shin Kidou Senki Gundam Wing: Frozen Teardrop", "New Mobile Report Gundam Wing: Frozen Teardrop", "新機動戦記ガンダムW Frozen Teardrop", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/25822/Shin_Kidou_Senki_Gundam_Wing__Frozen_Teardrop", 13 },
                    { 25916, "Saint Seiya: The Lost Canvas - Meiou Shinwa Gaiden was published in Brazilian Portuguese as Os Cavaleiros do Zodíaco: The Lost Canvas Gaiden by Editora JBC from August 2012 to November 2016.", 90, new DateTime(2016, 3, 11, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/129599.jpg", 730, 8.01m, new DateTime(2011, 5, 18, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A series of side stories focusing each of the Gold Saints from Saint Seiya: The Lost Canvas exploring their lives, mostly events which occurred before.\n\n(Source: MU)", "Saint Seiya: The Lost Canvas - Meiou Shinwa Gaiden", null, "聖闘士星矢 THE LOST CANVAS 冥王神話 外伝", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/25916/Saint_Seiya__The_Lost_Canvas_-_Meiou_Shinwa_Gaiden", 16 },
                    { 26123, "", 90, new DateTime(2007, 5, 13, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/159354.jpg", 48954, null, new DateTime(2005, 7, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A demon with a riceball-shaped head named Taizou comes to Earth looking for legendary girls with star-shaped nipples.", "Taizou Mote King Saga", null, "太臓もて王サーガ", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/26123/Taizou_Mote_King_Saga", 8 },
                    { 26133, "", 2, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/275375.jpg", 2741, 7.53m, new DateTime(2011, 6, 2, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Short stories featured in the Bleach: Official Character Book 3 UNMASKED include \"not be, but be,\" a short manga depicting Ulquiorra Cifer's past \"Nestle to Night\"; a short story written by Matsubara Makoto depicting the fates of Tier Harribel, Emilou Apacci, Franceska Mila Rose, and Cyan Sung-Sun after the battle with Aizen; and a short story about a conversation between Rangiku Matsumoto and Izuru Kira about Gin Ichimaru.", "Bleach Unmasked Short Stories", null, "BLEACH UNMASKED", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/26133/Bleach_Unmasked_Short_Stories", null },
                    { 26178, "Donten ni Warau was published digitally in English as Laughing Under the Clouds by Tokyopop from March 15, 2021, to September 29, 2021, and in print from April 20, 2021, to February 1, 2022. It was also released in Spanish Riendo bajo las nubes by Milky Way Ediciones from March 28, 2019, to January 30, 2020.", 29, new DateTime(2013, 5, 14, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/254936.jpg", 589, 8.09m, new DateTime(2010, 10, 14, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "In the dawn of the Meiji period, the Gokumonjou, an inescapable prison, has been established in the middle of an enormous lake to counter the soaring crime rates the new era has brought. Serving as the ferrymen are the famous Kumou brothers: the eccentric family head, Tenka; the reckless but noble second son, Soramaru; and the guileless youngest, Chuutarou. In spite of their grim work, the three lead relatively peaceful lives in the ever-cloudy town of Oumi, together with their housekeeper, Shirasu Kinjou.\n\nBut buried in the long history of Oumi is the legend of the terrifying Orochi, a serpentine beast that awakens every three hundred years in a human vessel. Unbeknownst to Soramaru and Chuutarou, the actual job of the Kumou family is to seal the Orochi away before it fully revives—or the world will be plunged into destruction. Amid the monster's next resurrection, the Kumou family must find the resolve to keep laughing under the clouds.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]\n\nIncluded one-shot:\nVolume 1: Utakata ni Warau (2 parts)", "Donten ni Warau", "Laughing Under the Clouds", "曇天に笑う", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/26178/Donten_ni_Warau", 6 },
                    { 26373, "", 3, new DateTime(2011, 8, 20, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/50851.jpg", 12082, 6.79m, new DateTime(2011, 6, 20, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Dragon Ball: Episode of Bardock is a three chapter manga created by Ooishi Naho and based on the video game Dragon Ball Heroes. It features a spin-off scenario taking place after the events of the TV special Dragon Ball Z: Bardock - The Father of Goku, in which Bardock survives after his confrontation against Frieza and turns into a Super Saiyan. \n\n(Source: Dragonball Wikia)", "Dragon Ball: Episode of Bardock", "Dragon Ball: Episode of Bardock", "ドラゴンボール エピソード オブ バーダック", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/26373/Dragon_Ball__Episode_of_Bardock", 1 },
                    { 26751, "", 4, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/183220.jpg", 17722, 6.32m, new DateTime(2009, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Akira and Miki from Devilman are visiting the Getter Robo base when it happens to be attacked.  But who are the attackers? The demon Silene has joined with the Dinosaur Empire! Will our heroes prevail?!", "Devilman vs Getter Robo", null, "デビルマン対ゲッターロボ", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/26751/Devilman_vs_Getter_Robo", 1 },
                    { 27643, "", 3, new DateTime(1988, 1, 4, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/44527.jpg", 49090, null, new DateTime(1983, 1, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Zaji, a young stranger who is characterized by carrying a scar below his left eye and a cold stare, escapes from the organization \"Home\" to find someone. Having grown up and been educated, trained and probably changed to \"Home\" as a soldier first, they send their murderers to make him pay his betrayal.", "Raimei no Zaji", null, "雷鳴のZAJI", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/27643/Raimei_no_Zaji", 1 },
                    { 27861, "", 13, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/44827.jpg", 755, 8m, new DateTime(2011, 8, 13, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Nitro+ will be releasing a novel of Mahou Shoujo Madoka☆Magica, using the original animation's series composition/script written by Gen Urobuchi. Nitro+'s Hajime Ninomae (一 肇), active in Kadokawa Sneaker Bunko and Shogakukan Gagaga Bunko, will be the novel writer. Yuupon (ゆーぽん), from the Nitro+Chiral shounen-ai branch, will be doing the illustrations.\nThe novel is split into two volumes of 304 pages and 328 pages length. It will be officially released as a limited edition with a third volume of 32 full-color pages on August 14, 2011. A prerelease will be held at Comiket 80 between August 12 and August 14, 2011.", "Mahou Shoujo Madoka★Magica", null, "魔法少女まどか★マギカ", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/27861/Mahou_Shoujo_Madoka★Magica", 2 },
                    { 28075, "", 23, new DateTime(2013, 8, 23, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/60581.jpg", 8539, 7.02m, new DateTime(2011, 9, 23, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Iori is a high school girl who doesn't know what she wants to do with her future, and tends to run away from things. One day, she is attacked by strange dead-eyed people on her way to school, only to be saved by an equally mysterious long-haired man. Later that day, her friend at school, Jion, seems to fall under the same murderous influence. To her surprise, she finds herself capable of defending herself from his violent attack. Afterward, the long-haired man she met in the morning, Zerozaki Soushiki, arrives once more, this time to invite her to become his little sister. What has Iori become involved with, and will she be able to survive this change to her life?\n\n(Source: MangaHelpers)", "Zerozaki Soushiki no Ningen Shiken", null, "零崎双識の人間試験", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/28075/Zerozaki_Soushiki_no_Ningen_Shiken", 5 },
                    { 28103, null, null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/117967.jpg", 2099, 7.63m, new DateTime(2011, 9, 1, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, null, "Ao no Exorcist", null, "青の祓魔師(エクソシスト)", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/28103/Ao_no_Exorcist", null },
                    { 28961, "", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/110093.jpg", 5917, 7.2m, new DateTime(2011, 9, 11, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "The girls of the popular seinen magical girl series are re-imagined in a different scenarios across all sorts of genres by various mangaka.", "Mahou Shoujo Madoka★Magica: Anthology Comic", null, "魔法少女まどか★マギカ [アンソロジーコミック]", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/28961/Mahou_Shoujo_Madoka★Magica__Anthology_Comic", null },
                    { 29391, "", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/148281.jpg", 49303, null, new DateTime(2011, 6, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "Ensign Reccoa Londe has provided the AEUG with information regarding possible mobile suit development at the civilian colonies of Green Noa. Lieutenant Quattro (Char Aznable) with his wingmen Lieutenant JGs Apolly (Andy) and Roberto (Ricardo) head to the colony to investigate. On Green Noa 1, Kamille Bidan is rushing to the spaceport where the Temptation, a ship a former One Year War ace is on, is docking. He's hoping to get an autograph from the famed Captain Bright Noa. As Bright explains that he's on duty, Jerid and company interrupt the two. Jerid smacktalks Bright for receiving a two rank demotion upon refusing to join the Titans and grabs Kamille's photo saying he should sign it as an elite member of the Federation. The two get into a scuffle and Kamille is hauled off for questioning. Matosh questions Kamille about being an AEUG insider but just then he's freed after his story checks out. Just as the handcuffs come off, the Gundam MK-II crashes into the building...\n\n(Source: MU)", "Kidou Senshi Z Gundam Define", null, "機動戦士Ζガンダム Define", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/29391/Kidou_Senshi_Z_Gundam_Define", null },
                    { 29733, "Rurouni Kenshin: Meiji Kenkaku Romantan - Maki no Ni was published in Brazilian Portuguese as Samurai X: Crônicas de Um Samurai na Era Meiji by Editora JBC in November 2006.", 22, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/48927.jpg", 2447, 7.57m, new DateTime(1997, 10, 2, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "It retells stories featured in the manga and anime series.\n\nThe novel is composed of two short stories, both already published in the manga: Yahiko's Fight and Black Hat.\n\nIn the first story, Yaahiko in order to protect the young Tsubame, has to face a group of dangerous outlaws. At first, he is defeated, but his samurai pride doesn't allow him to give up. So he faces those men again, ending up with a strategy that allows him to turn the advantage in his favor.\n\nIn the second story, the protagonists are Udou Jinne, a former Shinsengumi, and Kenshin. In order to force Himura to fight against him, Jinne kidnaps Kaoru and using Nikaido, a sort of hypnotic technique, he puts her in a condition of being incapable of breathing. This awakes Kenshin's fury, and the two samurai will have to fight a death match.\n\n(Source: RK Sword of Justice)", "Rurouni Kenshin: Meiji Kenkaku Romantan - Maki no Ni", null, "るろうに剣心 -明治剣客浪漫譚- 巻之二", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/29733/Rurouni_Kenshin__Meiji_Kenkaku_Romantan_-_Maki_no_Ni", 1 },
                    { 30541, null, 18, new DateTime(2013, 3, 3, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/85903.jpg", 15419, 6.55m, new DateTime(2011, 8, 10, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, null, "Bleach 4-koma: Komaburi", null, "BLEACH4コマ コマブリ", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/30541/Bleach_4-koma__Komaburi", 2 },
                    { 30591, "", 25, new DateTime(1988, 3, 9, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/111861.jpg", 49428, null, new DateTime(1987, 4, 9, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "In U.C. 0093, Char Aznable returns as leader of Neo Zeon, and is determined to drop the asteroid base Axis on Earth. Opposing him is the task-force Londo Bell, led by Amuro Ray and his Gundam. The final battle will take place over the Earth Sphere.\n\n(Source: Gundam Wikia)", "Kidou Senshi Gundam: Gyakushuu no Char - High Streamer", null, "機動戦士ガンダム 逆襲のシャア ハイ・ストリーマー", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/30591/Kidou_Senshi_Gundam__Gyakushuu_no_Char_-_High_Streamer", 3 },
                    { 30593, "", 14, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/148119.jpg", 5447, 7.24m, new DateTime(1988, 2, 19, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "This is Tomino's alternate version of \"Char's Counterattack\" which he proposed for the movie adaptation. He drew up a new story outline which added Beltorchika and turned Amuro into a family man. The sponsors didn't like the idea, and reverted to the original \"High Streamer\" storyline, but Tomino decided to write this new novel based on his rejected movie plot.\n\nIn U.C. 0093, Char Aznable returns as leader of Neo Zeon, and is determined to drop the asteroid base Axis on Earth. Opposing him is the task-force Londo Bell, led by Amuro Ray and his Gundam. The final battle will take place over the Earth Sphere.\n\n(Source: Gundam Wikia)", "Kidou Senshi Gundam: Gyakushuu no Char - Beltorchika's Children", null, "機動戦士ガンダム 逆襲のシャア ベルトーチカ・チルドレン", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/30593/Kidou_Senshi_Gundam__Gyakushuu_no_Char_-_Beltorchikas_Children", 1 },
                    { 30723, "", 10, new DateTime(1976, 6, 30, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/53969.jpg", 19276, 5.95m, new DateTime(1975, 8, 31, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The story tells about Hiroshi Shiba, a car racer who is mortally wounded on a laboratory accident, but restored to life by his father, Professor Shiba, a talented scientist/archeologist, who is incidentally investigating the relics of the ancient Yamatai Kingdom. The professor discovers a tiny bronze bell with sorcerous powers, and shortly afterwards he is murdered by the henchmen of Queen Himika, the ruler of the Yamatai (sometimes translated as Jamatai) Kingdom, who wants to seize the ancient bell and its power.", "Koutetsu Jeeg", null, "鋼鉄ジーグ", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/30723/Koutetsu_Jeeg", 1 },
                    { 30725, "", null, new DateTime(2008, 1, 24, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/54167.jpg", 49439, null, new DateTime(2002, 9, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Set before Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam, the story follows the Titans Test Team, Black Otter Team, on their mission to test new mobile suits for the Titans. It begins with Eliard Hunter, an Earth Federation mobile suit pilot being assigned to the Titans and transferring to the Aswan, an Alexandria class carrier. There he meets Carl Matsubara, another new Titans recruit, Audrey April a skilled pilot and chief of test operations and data gathering, and Wes Murphy, a veteran of the One Year War and the Delaz Conflict. The Black Otter team doesn’t just carry out test runs, it also participates in real combat missions against Zeon Remnants and later, against AEUG.\n\n(Source: Gundam Wikia)", "Advance of Z: Titans no Hata no Moto ni", null, "ADVANCE OF Ζ ティターンズの旗のもとに", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/30725/Advance_of_Z__Titans_no_Hata_no_Moto_ni", 2 },
                    { 30859, "High School DxD was published in English by Yen Press from May 27, 2014 to November 13, 2018; in Italian by Panini Comics under the Planet Manga imprint since January 25, 2014, in Polish by Studio JG under the Osiem Macek imprint since May 4, 2016, and in Spanish by Ivrea España since September 30, 2016.", 78, new DateTime(2018, 2, 8, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/206676.jpg", 2589, 7.55m, new DateTime(2010, 7, 19, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "\"Would you mind dying right now?\" are not the words that high school student and lifelong pervert Issei Hyoudou expects to hear from his first girlfriend, especially not before being brutally murdered on their first date. Luckily for Issei, he's saved when he summons the beautiful Rias Gremory, a high-ranking Devil, who reincarnates him as a Devil servant. As Issei learns more about the conflict that has raged between Devils and Angels, he discovers that his \"girlfriend\" was actually a Fallen Angel named Raynare, sent to destroy him because he possesses a \"Sacred Gear,\" a divine weapon given to humans by the Gods.\n\nIssei is then made a member of the Occult Research Club, the headquarters for the House of Gremory, where he meets the rest of Rias' servants. Given the rank \"Pawn,\" Issei decides that he will rise through the ranks so that he can create his own harem of beautiful girls. However, many grave dangers lie ahead, as Issei must face the Fallen Angels and rogue Exorcists, whilst also trying to master the power of his Sacred Gear.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "High School DxD", "High School DxD", "ハイスクールD×D", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/30859/High_School_DxD", 11 },
                    { 30861, "", 2, new DateTime(2011, 10, 11, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/55109.jpg", 49443, null, new DateTime(2011, 10, 4, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Hundreds of years have passed during the space age that began with man’s settlement of the space colonies. While an era of peace had arrived, it did not last long. Following the sudden appearance of an unknown enemy, the peaceful days were lost. And so, the curtain rises on a new battle that has continued for one hundred years.", "Kidou Senshi Gundam AGE: Hajimari no Monogatari", null, "機動戦士ガンダムAGE 〜始まりの物語〜", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/30861/Kidou_Senshi_Gundam_AGE__Hajimari_no_Monogatari", 1 },
                    { 30987, "", 1, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/275330.jpg", 3500, 7.43m, new DateTime(2011, 4, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "After watching the largely unknown Karasuno High School overwhelmingly win a volleyball practice match, soon-to-be first-year high school student Shouyou Hinata aspires to join their team as the ace. Unfortunately, his short stature and lack of experience in playing any sort of official game earns him the ire of Karasuno's current members, including the team's famous setter Tobio Kageyama. Determined to prove that he has what it takes—and with a strong desire to show Kageyama he is wrong—Hinata begins to train and hone his skills in order to soar above them all.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Haikyuu!!", null, "ハイキュー!!", 3, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/30987/Haikyuu", null },
                    { 31011, "", 1, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/229821.jpg", 49458, null, new DateTime(2004, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "This is a special original chapter included in the Ring ni Kakero Real databook.", "Ring ni Kakero: Jun to Jun! Hikari to Kage no Maki", null, "リングにかけろ順と殉！光と影の巻", 3, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/31011/Ring_ni_Kakero__Jun_to_Jun_Hikari_to_Kage_no_Maki", null },
                    { 31079, "", 9, new DateTime(2011, 11, 20, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/95619.jpg", 4004, 7.37m, new DateTime(2011, 5, 8, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Saiki Kusuo has a wide array of superpowers at his command, including telepathy and telekinesis. This might sound awesome, but, in Kusuo's experience, superpowers are not all they're cracked up to be. He tries to live a normal life, despite his annoying abilities.\n\n(Source: MangaHelpers)\n\nIncluded one-shots: Mikami Shounen Tantei File, Boku no Watashi no Yuushagaku (Special Chapter)", "Chounouryokusha Saiki Kusuo no Ψ-nan 0", null, "超能力者斉木楠雄のΨ難 0 麻生周一短編集", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/31079/Chounouryokusha_Saiki_Kusuo_no_Ψ-nan_0", 1 },
                    { 31499, "Nisekoi was published in English as Nisekoi: False Love by VIZ Media under the Shonen Jump imprint from January 7, 2014 to January 2, 2018. It has been published in Italian by Star Comics since March 1, 2014; in Spanish by Ivrea since April 4, 2015; and in Indonesian by Elex Media.", 229, new DateTime(2016, 8, 7, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/181212.jpg", 1665, 7.71m, new DateTime(2011, 11, 6, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "When Raku Ichijou was young, he made a heartfelt promise to his childhood friend that if they were to meet again, they would marry each other. Ten years have passed since that fateful day, leaving Raku's memory of her faded. But he still holds a relic of their relationship together—a locked pendant, which his childhood friend holds the key to. He hopes to reunite with her one day, despite not remembering what she looks like.\n\nNow a first-year student at Bonyari High School, Raku attempts to live a normal life, dreaming of becoming a public servant and marrying his crush Kosaki Onodera. However, this isn't as easy as it seems, as he is the unwilling heir to a large yakuza family, and Raku can't escape from his duties when the American Bee Hive gang wages war on his family's turf. In order to forge peace between the two feuding families, Raku is forced into a fake romantic relationship with Chitoge Kirisaki, the beautiful daughter of the Bee Hive's leader. The two quickly come to hate each other, but have to learn to live together and pretend to be deeply in love in order to keep their families at bay. \n\nHowever, Raku's quest for the key to his pendant isn't becoming easier as more girls—who were all involved with his pendant in some way—enter his life. Join Raku as he juggles his false relationship, maintains the balance between warring families, and unravels the identity of the girl who will unlock his heart.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Nisekoi", "Nisekoi: False Love", "ニセコイ", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/31499/Nisekoi", 25 },
                    { 31521, "", 3, new DateTime(2010, 8, 25, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/58043.jpg", 4695, 7.31m, new DateTime(2010, 7, 25, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A crossover manga with Kodomo no Omocha and Honey Bitter.\n\nShuri is a private detective with a special ability to read minds. She usually handles all sorts of cases, but this time she is faced with a rather unusual request. The famous actress Kurata Sana is going to play in a new film as a detective. She wants to be able to impersonate her character as best as possible so she asks Shuri if she can stick around to learn a few things that real detectives do and how they act. Despite this childish request, Shuri also recieves a more intimate request from Sana's manager, Sagami Rei, who wants to find out the reason why Sana and her husband, Hayama Akito, have decided to live separate one from another.\n\n(Source: Evil Flowers)", "Deep Clear", null, "Deep Clear 「Honey Bitter」×「こどものおもちゃ」特別番外編", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/31521/Deep_Clear", 1 },
                    { 31845, "", 8, new DateTime(2005, 2, 28, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/73895.jpg", 14758, 6.6m, new DateTime(2004, 2, 29, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The story takes place in the year Correct Century 2343, showing the past of Loran and training for global operations.", "Turn A Gundam: Tsuki no Kaze", null, "∀ガンダム: 月の風", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/31845/Turn_A_Gundam__Tsuki_no_Kaze", 1 },
                    { 31935, "Koukaku Kidoutai: Stand Alone Complex was published in English as Ghost in the Shell: Stand Alone Complex by Kodansha Comics USA from May 24, 2011, to March 6, 2012. It was also released in Spanish by Planeta Cómic from July 2, 2019, to October 6, 2020.", 42, new DateTime(2012, 12, 16, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/142929.jpg", 5036, 7.28m, new DateTime(2009, 12, 13, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Stand Alone Complex takes place in the year 2030, in the fictional Japanese city of New Port. The story follows the members of Public Security Section 9, a special-operations task-force made up of former military officers and police detectives. The manga presents individual cases that Section 9 investigates, along with an ongoing, more serious investigation into the serial killer and hacker known only as “The Laughing Man.”\n\n(Source: Kodansha)", "Koukaku Kidoutai: Stand Alone Complex", "Ghost in the Shell: Stand Alone Complex", "攻殻機動隊STAND ALONE COMPLEX", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/31935/Koukaku_Kidoutai__Stand_Alone_Complex", 5 },
                    { 31939, "", 4, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/259305.jpg", 11149, 6.85m, new DateTime(1992, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Universal Century 0153, where the team of Use along with a scrap dealer in the fight against the remnants of batlha Zanscare.", "Kidou Senshi V Gundam Gaiden", null, "機動戦士Vガンダム外伝", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/31939/Kidou_Senshi_V_Gundam_Gaiden", 1 },
                    { 32037, "Drug & Drop has been published in English by Dark Horse since January 20, 2015.", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/84971.jpg", 2838, 7.51m, new DateTime(2011, 11, 3, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "Long-awaited continuation of the manga \"Legal Drug,\" by bestselling group CLAMP. It picks up from where the plot in Legal Drug left off, with a short prologue catching readers up to the main events of the previous series.\n\nKazahaya has always had the ability to see the memories of items and people that he touches. When he collapses in the snow, desperately clinging to life, he is rescued by Rikuou, who takes him back to Green Drugstore, a pharmacy dealing in more than just your everyday items.\n\nKazahaya finds himself working in the store, indebted to the owner, Kakei, for giving him a job and a place to lodge. Somehow, Kakei knows about Kazahaya's abilities, and soon he and Rikuou are sent on the occasional side job, involving the use of their unique talents.\n\nAs the story progresses, more is revealed about the mysterious pasts of the two main characters. Why did Kazahaya end up collapsed in the snow? Who is the mysterious girl that Kazahaya keeps seeing in Rikuou's mind, and what exactly happened to her?", "Drug & Drop", "Drug & Drop", "ドラッグ＆ドロップ", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/32037/Drug___Drop", null },
                    { 32347, "JoJo's Bizarre Adventure: Over Heaven was one of three novels released in celebration of the 25th anniversary of the JoJo no Kimyou na Bouken series.", 82, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/270480.jpg", 1303, 7.8m, new DateTime(2011, 12, 15, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A novel centered on Dio.", "JoJo's Bizarre Adventure: Over Heaven", null, "JOJO'S BIZARRE ADVENTURE OVER HEAVEN", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/32347/JoJos_Bizarre_Adventure__Over_Heaven", 1 },
                    { 32409, "", 1, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/59421.jpg", 4283, 7.34m, new DateTime(2011, 6, 9, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The town of Krowatol was once known as an oasis in the middle of a great desert, a beacon of hope for weary travelers. Now its water supply is almost entirely gone, and the town is as dry as the landscape surrounding it. When two mysterious travelers arrive, Krowatol resident Rosé Tomas discovers that they are the infamous alchemist duo known as the Elric Brothers Edward and Alphonse. As word of their arrival reaches the town's governor Arzen, the brothers are invited to his estate to hear out Arzen's strange and dangerous request.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Full Metal Alchemist: Prototype", null, "鋼の錬金術師プロトタイプ", 3, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/32409/Full_Metal_Alchemist__Prototype", null },
                    { 32799, "", 53, new DateTime(2016, 3, 25, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/173478.jpg", 6350, 7.17m, new DateTime(2011, 11, 25, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Kidou Senshi Cross Bone Gundam: Ghost is set in the year UC 0153—two decades after the Cross Bone Gundam series and in the story timeframe of the Kidou Senshi V Gundam anime. The first Cross Bone Gundam series followed the conflict between the burgeoning Jupiter Empire and a small resistance force in UC 0133. Kidou Senshi Cross Bone Gundam Skull Heart and Koutetsu no Nananin show the aftermath of the conflict three years later.\n\n(Source: ANN)", "Kidou Senshi Crossbone Gundam: Ghost", "Mobile Suit Cross Bone Gundam: Ghost", "機動戦士クロスボーン・ガンダム ゴースト", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/32799/Kidou_Senshi_Crossbone_Gundam__Ghost", 12 },
                    { 32899, "", 20, new DateTime(1977, 2, 28, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/60133.jpg", 16271, 6.48m, new DateTime(1975, 9, 30, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Although similar in name to the Go Nagai work, this version by Gosaku Ota is vastly different from Nagai's work.", "UFO Robo Grendizer", "UFO Robot Grendizer", "UFOロボグレンディザー", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/32899/UFO_Robo_Grendizer", 5 },
                    { 32913, "Ultraman has been published in English by VIZ Media under the VIZ Signature imprint since August 18, 2015 and it has also been simulpub through VIZ Manga. The series has been published in Brazil by Jbc since September 2015.", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/149472.jpg", 6524, 7.16m, new DateTime(2011, 10, 31, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "Shinjirou is an ordinary teenager, but his father is the legendary Shin Hayata. When he learns that his father passed on the \"Ultraman Factor\" to him and that he possesses incredible powers, nothing will ever be the same again.\n\n(Source: VIZ Media)", "Ultraman", null, "ULTRAMAN", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/32913/Ultraman", null },
                    { 32991, "The Book: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure 4th Another Day was first announced in 2000 but proved difficult to complete. In 2004, author Otsuichi claimed that he had written over 2000 pages but had scrapped them all. The novel was finally released in 2007, coinciding with the series 20th anniversary.", 5, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/60351.jpg", 2503, 7.56m, new DateTime(2007, 11, 25, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The novel is about a normal day in Morioh, from the point of view of a new character named Takuma Hasumi. His stand is called The Book, has the appearance of a normal book, and possesses the power to record everything he sees or feels. Josuke and the rest of the Part IV heroes appear as antagonists.\n\nThe story takes place in Morioh, in the year 2000. Three days before the end of winter break. Koichi and Rohan find a blood-stained cat outside a convenience store. They go searching for the cat's owner, and find a woman's strange-looking corpse inside the house. By using Heaven's Door, they find a clue: \"a male student with red scratch marks under his arm.\" Over the span of 3 months, the curtain opens on this incident.", "The Book: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure 4th Another Day", null, "“The Book” jojo's bizarre adventure 4th another day", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/32991/The_Book__JoJos_Bizarre_Adventure_4th_Another_Day", 1 },
                    { 33297, "", 20, new DateTime(2015, 6, 1, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/181438.jpg", 510, 8.14m, new DateTime(2011, 12, 26, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Yoshioka Futaba has a few reasons why she wants to \"reset\" her image and life as a new high school student. Because she's cute, she was ostracized by her female friends in junior high, and because of a misunderstanding, she couldn't get her feeling across to the one boy she has always liked, Tanaka-kun.\n\nNow in high school, she is determined to be as unladylike as possible so that her friends won't be jealous of her. While living her life this way contentedly, she meets Tanaka-kun again, but he now goes under the name of Mabuchi Kou. He tells her that he felt the same way as she did when they were younger, but now things can never be the same again. Will Futaba be able to continue her love that never even started from three years ago?", "Ao Haru Ride", null, "アオハライド", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/33297/Ao_Haru_Ride", 6 },
                    { 33327, "Tokyo Ghoul was nominated for the 38th Kodansha Manga Award in the General category in 2014. The manga ranked 12th in the 2015 Kono Manga ga Sugoi! for the Male Readers division. The series was published in English by VIZ Media under the VIZ Signature imprint from June 16, 2015, to August 15, 2017. It was also released in German by Kazé Manga from May 2, 2014, to July 2016; in Spanish by Norma Editorial from March 20, 2015, to June 23, 2016; in Polish by Waneko from April 15, 2015, to May 15, 2017; in Brazilian Portuguese by Panini Comics from July 2015 to September 2017; in Czech by CREW from August 31, 2016, to April 17, 2019; and in Argentina by Editorial Ivrea since December 9, 2016, to March 9, 2018. An artbook for the manga titled Tokyo Ghoul [zakki] was released on October 17, 2014. The series was adapted into two Japanese live-action films; the first was released on July 29, 2017. A sequel film was released on July 19, 2019.", 144, new DateTime(2014, 9, 17, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/114037.jpg", 132, 8.53m, new DateTime(2011, 9, 7, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Lurking within the shadows of Tokyo are frightening beings known as ghouls, who satisfy their hunger by feeding on humans once night falls. An organization known as the Commission of Counter Ghoul (CCG) has been established in response to the constant attacks on citizens and as a means of purging these creatures. However, the problem lies in identifying ghouls as they disguise themselves as humans, living amongst the masses so that hunting prey will be easier. Ken Kaneki, an unsuspecting university freshman, finds himself caught in a world between humans and ghouls when his date turns out to be a ghoul after his flesh.\n\nBarely surviving this encounter after being taken to a hospital, he discovers that he has turned into a half-ghoul as a result of the surgery he received. Unable to satisfy his intense craving for human meat through conventional means, Kaneki is taken in by friendly ghouls who run a coffee shop in order to help him with his transition. As he begins what he thinks will be a peaceful new life, little does he know that he is about to find himself at the center of a war between his new comrades and the forces of the CCG, and that his new existence has caught the attention of ghouls all over Tokyo.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Tokyo Ghoul", "Tokyo Ghoul", "東京喰種トーキョーグール", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/33327/Tokyo_Ghoul", 14 },
                    { 33617, "", 8, new DateTime(2001, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/172663.jpg", 16701, 6.44m, new DateTime(1999, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "1. Sanchuushuu Katsugeki (Smelly Action in the Mountains)\n2. Bobobo-bo Bo-bobo (Akamaru Jump Version)\n3-6. Bobobo-bo Bo-bobo\n7. Mutekin\n8. Gekisen!! Jankenjima (Fierce!! Rock, Paper, Scissors Island)", "Bobobo-bo Bo-bobo?", null, "ボボボーボ・ボーボボ？ 澤井啓夫短編集", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/33617/Bobobo-bo_Bo-bobo", 1 },
                    { 33699, "", 23, new DateTime(2013, 9, 17, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/120981.jpg", 1584, 7.73m, new DateTime(2011, 12, 16, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Manga adaptation of the 1st arc of the Mahouka Koukou no Rettousei series.\n\n\"Magic\" is a product of neither legends nor fairy tales. It has become a technology of reality for nearly a century. Various countries in the world are locked in a race in nurturing \"Magicians.\"\n\nShiba Tatsuya is an honors student without magic capability at First High School, a magic high school along with his sister who happens to the top student among the freshmen. What will happen to him, and how will he live his school life where he is one of the many reserves in the school looked down upon by the chosen magical students?\n\n(Source: jCafe24)", "Mahouka Koukou no Rettousei: Nyuugaku-hen", null, "魔法科高校の劣等生 入学編", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/33699/Mahouka_Koukou_no_Rettousei__Nyuugaku-hen", 4 },
                    { 34127, "Mahouka Koukou no Rettousei originally was published as a web novel series on Shousetsuka ni Narou website (小説家になろう) between October 12, 2008 and March 21, 2011. The first official volume was published on July 8, 2011 by Ascii Media Works under Dengeki Bunko label. The series has been published in English as The Irregular at Magic High School by Yen Press under the Yen On imprint since April 19, 2016.", null, new DateTime(2020, 9, 9, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/62151.jpg", 485, 8.16m, new DateTime(2011, 7, 7, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The year is 2095. Magic has been tamed as another form of technology, and the practice of magic is now a rigorous discipline. Brother and sister Tatsuya and Miyuki Shiba are just about to start their first year at the renowned First Magic High School of Japan. But the school's ironclad rules mean that the brilliant Miyuki enters the prestigious Course 1, while her older brother, Tatsuya, is relegated to Course 2—and that's just the beginning of their troubles!\n\n(Source: Yen Press)", "Mahouka Koukou no Rettousei", "The Irregular at Magic High School", "魔法科高校の劣等生", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/34127/Mahouka_Koukou_no_Rettousei", 32 },
                    { 34335, "Durarara!! Saika-hen adapts the second novel in the series. Durarara!! Saika-hen was published in English as Durarara!! Saika Arc by Yen Press from March 26, 2013 to January 21, 2014. The series has also been published in Chinese by Kadokawa Taiwan Corporation from December 21, 2012 to August 16, 2013; in Italian by Star Comics from January 11, 2014 to May 10, 2014; and in Polish by Waneko from October 9, 2015 to February 5, 2016.", 16, new DateTime(2013, 1, 17, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/154267.jpg", 1183, 7.83m, new DateTime(2011, 9, 16, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The old anonymous group chat consisting of some of Ikebukuro's most peculiar residents receives a sudden addition: Saika, a cryptic user who occasionally pops up and sends messages that make little sense. Although everyone simply discards it as spam, a curious connection between Saika's messages and a recent string of slashing assaults soon forms.\n\nDubbed the \"Slasher\" by the media, their rampage continues. At the same time, Anri Sonohara is advised to stay away from a teacher with a history of dating minors. Although she now has friends, Anri still suffers from bullying; during one incident, she comes face-to-face with the Slasher, becoming the first person to survive the encounter unscathed.\n\nMeanwhile, a reporter following a story about the so-called strongest man in Ikebukuro is viciously attacked by the Slasher. As the number one contender for the title of strongest man, Shizuo Heiwajima sets out on a hunt to find the mysterious aggressor. In his latest uncovering, the infamous information broker Izaya Orihara reveals that the Slasher might just be Ikebukuro's next supernatural threat.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Durarara!! Saika-hen", "Durarara!! Saika Arc", "デュラララ!! 罪歌編", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/34335/Durarara_Saika-hen", 3 },
                    { 34485, "High School DxD: Asia & Koneko no Himitsu no Keiyaku!? was both digitally & physically published in English as High School DxD: Asia & Koneko's Secret Contract!? by Yen Press on December 16, 2014.", 6, new DateTime(2012, 3, 8, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/144667.jpg", 5004, 7.28m, new DateTime(2011, 9, 8, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The naturally clumsy Sister Asia and taciturn cutie Koneko form an unlikely devilish duo in this spin-off of the mega-hit High School DxD! The two head out to answer summons from humans with requests, but...th-th-they want Koneko and Sister Asia to do what?! These two little devil beauties get to work! But can they really fulfill every desire?!\n\n(Source: Yen Press)", "High School DxD: Asia & Koneko no Himitsu no Keiyaku!?", "High School DxD: Asia & Koneko's Secret Contract?!", "ハイスクールD×D アーシア＆小猫の ヒミツのけいやく!?", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/34485/High_School_DxD__Asia___Koneko_no_Himitsu_no_Keiyaku", 1 },
                    { 34837, null, 80, new DateTime(2017, 5, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/4/155412.jpg", 4306, 7.34m, new DateTime(2010, 10, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, null, "Angel Heart 2nd Season", null, "エンジェル・ハート 2ndシーズ", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/34837/Angel_Heart_2nd_Season", 16 },
                    { 35003, "Yamada-kun to 7-nin no Majo was published in English as Yamada-kun and the Seven Witches by Kodansha Comics USA from March 31, 2015 to January 24, 2023, and was simulpub by Crunchyroll since January 8, 2014. The series has also been published in Italian by Star Comics since March 22, 2014.", 246, new DateTime(2017, 2, 21, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/191685.jpg", 681, 8.04m, new DateTime(2012, 2, 21, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A junior at Suzaku High, Ryuu Yamada is infamous for being a hardliner and a delinquent. One day, after being reprimanded for his poor performance and attitude toward school, he spots Urara Shiraishi, the grade's top student. As Shiraishi is walking up the stairs, Yamada attempts to provoke her, only to trip and fall, taking her down with him. \n\nEventually, he wakes up in the infirmary. To his surprise, he discovers that he is not in his own body. It turns out that he swapped bodies with Shiraishi, and upon confronting her, he finds out that the catalyst for the swap was an accidental kiss during the fall. With the knowledge of this new ability, Yamada's eventful high school life has just begun!\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Yamada-kun to 7-nin no Majo", "Yamada-kun and the Seven Witches", "山田くんと7人の魔女", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/35003/Yamada-kun_to_7-nin_no_Majo", 28 },
                    { 35243, "Haikyuu!! won the 61st Shogakukan Manga Award in the Shounen category in 2015. The series was published in English by VIZ Media under the Shonen Jump imprint from July 5, 2016, to August 3, 2021. The publisher later released the manga in 3-in-1 omnibus volumes. It has also been published in Polish by Studio JG since May 6, 2022.", 407, new DateTime(2020, 7, 19, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/258225.jpg", 30, 8.85m, new DateTime(2012, 2, 19, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The whistle blows. The ball is up. A dig. A set. A spike.\n\nVolleyball. A sport where two teams face off, separated by a formidable, wall-like net.\n\nThe \"Little Giant,\" standing at only 170 centimeters, overcomes the towering net and the wall of blockers. The awe-inspired Shouyou Hinata looks on at the ace's crow-like figure. Determined to reach great heights like the Little Giant, small-statured Hinata finally manages to form a team in his last year of junior high school, and enters his first volleyball tournament. However, his team is utterly defeated in their first game against the powerhouse school Kitagawa Daiichi, led by the genius, but oppressive setter dubbed the \"King of the Court,\" Tobio Kageyama.\n\nHinata enrolls into Karasuno High School seeking to take revenge against Kageyama in an official high school match and to follow in the Little Giant's footsteps—but his plans are ruined when he opens the gymnasium door to find Kageyama as one of his teammates.\n\nNow, Hinata must establish himself on the team and work alongside the problematic Kageyama to overcome his shortcomings and to fulfill his dream of making it to the top of the high school volleyball world.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]\n\nIncluded one-shot:\nVolume 14: Nisekyuu!!", "Haikyuu!!", "Haikyu!!", "ハイキュー!!", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/35243/Haikyuu", 45 },
                    { 35281, "", null, new DateTime(2000, 2, 29, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/64055.jpg", 49724, null, new DateTime(1999, 9, 30, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "This story is set thousands of years in the future. The people of Earth have forgotten the space wars of the past, reverting back to a pre-industrial existence. But the lunar settlers known as the Moonrace, who have retained their high technology, now plan to seize their mother planet for themselves. As the war of the worlds begins, a young Moonrace citizen named Loran Cehack, pilot of the legendary Turn A Gundam, struggles to bridge the gap between humanity's long-separated branches.", "Turn A Gundam", null, "∀（ターンエー）ガンダム", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/35281/Turn_A_Gundam", 5 },
                    { 35317, "", 9, new DateTime(2012, 7, 31, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/282838.jpg", 49729, null, new DateTime(2011, 10, 31, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Daiki is lead to meet the mobile suit Gundam by words left behind by his father: “grand wings”. So he sets off on an adventure into the great unknown of outer space.", "Kidou Senshi Gundam Age: Treasure Star", null, "機動戦士ガンダムAGE　トレジャースター", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/35317/Kidou_Senshi_Gundam_Age__Treasure_Star", 2 },
                    { 35319, "", 11, new DateTime(2012, 7, 25, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/64165.jpg", 49728, null, new DateTime(2011, 9, 25, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "In A.G. 101 (the 101st year of the Advanced Generation calendar) a mysterious entity known only as \"UE\", or \"unknown enemy\", attacks and destroys the space colony Angel. This brutal attack becomes infamous as the \"The Day the Angel Fell\", and marks the beginning of humanity's war for survival. The series begins in A.G. 108 when the UE attack the space colony Ovan, where Flit Asuno now lives after he escaped colony Angel before its destruction. Flit's mother shortly before she is killed by the UE, she gives her son an object called \"AGE Device\". Within it he discovers the blueprints for a powerful weapon from the past—the ancient messiah named \"Gundam.\"\n\nFrom these blueprints, Flit spends the next several years studying engineering at an Earth Federation base on the Nora space colony and designing the Gundam AGE-1. Seven years later, in A.G. 115, Flit completes the Gundam AGE-1 Normal, just as the UE attack Nora, and make use of it to aid the crew of Federation's battleship \"Diva\" in evacuating the colony's citizens before it is destroyed. Determined to bring the battle to the U.E. for destroying his home twice, Flit agrees to serve at Diva's mobile suit squad piloting the Gundam. After obtaining enough data and military power to establish a course of action, the crew of Diva and their allies launch a sucessful attack that destroyed the U.E.'s secret fortress in the Ambat asteroid. There they learn that the U.E. are actually the descendants of a supposedly failed human mission sent to colonize Mars, left for dead by the Earth Federation, who formed their own nation on the red planet called Veigan.", "Kidou Senshi Gundam AGE: First Evolution", "Mobile Suit Gundam AGE: First Evolution", "機動戦士ガンダムAGE First Evolution", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/35319/Kidou_Senshi_Gundam_AGE__First_Evolution", 3 },
                    { 35321, "", 7, new DateTime(2012, 8, 9, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/282840.jpg", 49729, null, new DateTime(2012, 2, 9, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "25 years after the battle at Ambat, the war between the Federation and the Veigans keeps escalating with no end at sight as the Veigans rejected all offers for a peace treaty. Flit, now married and father of two is a commander of the Earth forces determined to win the war and decides that the time has come to his son Asemu to succeed him as the pilot for the Gundam, entrusting him with the AGE Device on his 17th birthday. On an attack on his city, Asemu pilots the Gundam AGE-1 hidden at the family's stable for the first time to repel the Veigan offensive.\n\n(Source: Gundam Wikia)", "Kidou Senshi Gundam AGE: Second Evolution", null, "機動戦士ガンダムAGE -Second Evolution-", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/35321/Kidou_Senshi_Gundam_AGE__Second_Evolution", 2 },
                    { 35609, "", 1, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/64641.jpg", 4324, 7.34m, new DateTime(2011, 7, 26, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The \"0th volume\" of the Mahou Sensei Negima! manga was released with the Mahou Sensei Negima! Anime Final film. It contains a side story and production materials such as the anime storyboards he drew for the opening animation footage of the original anime DVD project. (Source: ANN)", "Mahou Sensei Negima! Volume 0", null, "魔法先生ネギま! 0", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/35609/Mahou_Sensei_Negima_Volume_0", 1 },
                    { 35907, "", 8, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/270478.jpg", 3020, 7.49m, new DateTime(2001, 5, 27, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Coni (Coniglio) is a shy and introverted girl, without friends, originally from Rome. For a series of bizarre events, she is now in Venice, to take the place of the grandmother who died in an accident in a large hotel, as a cleaning woman, dragging her existence in a routine. But Coni has a secret: she is a Stand user, a presence that she has never understood.\n\nThe story takes place in Venice, after the group betray the Boss. It primarily centers on Fugo and his encounters with three new stand users. A series of mass killings have been occurring, and Fugo can be seen at each crime scene - as they are apparently a result of his stand Purple Haze going berserk.", "JoJo no Kimyou na Bouken II: Golden Heart/Golden Ring", null, "ジョジョの奇妙な冒険II ゴールデンハート／ゴールデンリング", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/35907/JoJo_no_Kimyou_na_Bouken_II__Golden_Heart_Golden_Ring", 1 },
                    { 36277, "Time Killers was published in English by VIZ Media under the Shonen Jump imprint on September 2, 2014 and in Italian by Panini Comics under the Planet Manga imprint on May 10, 2014.", 11, new DateTime(2008, 8, 31, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/65561.jpg", 3950, 7.38m, new DateTime(2000, 7, 31, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A collection of one shots by Kato Kazue, including the original pilot for Ao no Exorcist.\n\n1. Boku to Usagi\n2. Akanasu\n3. Akai Daichi ni Umareta Senshi no Hanashi\n4. USA Boy!!!\n5. Hime Goro mo Torisetsu Manga\n6. Jinsei Kaidou Hagure Hoshi\n7. Nirai\n8. Nushi to Bou\n9. Otome no Inori\n10. HoshiOta (Astronerd)\n11. Miyama Uguisutei Jiken (Ao no Exorcist pilot)", "Time Killers", "Time Killers: Kazue Kato Short Story Collection", "TIME KILLERS 加藤和恵短編集", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/36277/Time_Killers", 1 },
                    { 36729, "", 5, new DateTime(2011, 8, 10, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/66289.jpg", 2178, 7.62m, new DateTime(2003, 10, 5, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Compilation book featuring all of Ryūhei Tamura's early oneshots illustrated before he started on Beelzebub. The compilation also includes the Beelzebub Pilot Chapter and an extra chapter.\n\nContains:\n- Beelzebub \n- Oumiya Jet \n- Nirai Kanai Yori \n- URA BEAT \n- Beelzebub Extra", "Beelzebub Maou Gaiden", null, "べるぜバブ魔王外伝: 田村隆平短編集", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/36729/Beelzebub_Maou_Gaiden", 1 },
                    { 36933, "Ore Monogatari!! placed first on the female ranking of 2013 Kono Manga ga Sugoi!, was awarded the 37th Kodansha Manga Award for Best Shoujo Manga in 2013, and the for the same category in 2015. The series was published in English as My Love Story!! by VIZ Media under the Shojo Beat imprint from July 1, 2014 to September 5, 2017. It has also been published in Spanish by Ivrea España since December 2015. The manga was adapted into a Japanese live-action film directed by Hayato Kawai that was screened on October 31, 2015.", 52, new DateTime(2016, 7, 12, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/180382.jpg", 569, 8.11m, new DateTime(2011, 12, 12, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "High school student Takeo Gouda has an intimidating physique that often scares strangers away. Despite his looks, he is appreciated for his kind and manly nature, making him well liked and respected among those who truly know him. However, he has had no luck with romance. Instead, every girl he likes always ends up taking interest in his best friend—the quiet and handsome Makoto Sunakawa. \n\nOne day, Takeo falls in love with the cute and petite Rinko Yamato after saving her from an unpleasant situation. Little does he know, Rinko fell in love with him too! Oblivious, Takeo believes that Yamato is interested in Sunakawa, so soft-hearted Takeo decides to help bring the two together, even if he has to abandon his love story.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Ore Monogatari!!", "My Love Story!!", "俺物語!!", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/36933/Ore_Monogatari", 13 },
                    { 37303, "Rurouni Kenshin: Tokuhitsuban was published in English as Rurouni Kenshin: Restoration by VIZ Media under its Shonen Jump imprint from June 4, 2013, to January 7, 2014. It was also released in Brazilian Portuguese as Rurouni Kenshin: Versão do Autor by Editora JBC from February 2016 and March 2016.", 11, new DateTime(2013, 6, 3, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/132973.jpg", 6481, 7.16m, new DateTime(2012, 5, 1, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "During the violent upheaval of the Bakumatsu era, Hitokiri Battosai was a feared and ruthless assassin. But now that the Meiji Restoration has begun to heal the wounds of civil war, Battosai has taken up a new name…and a new calling! He is now Himura Kenshin, a rurouni wanderer who has vowed to only draw his sword to protect those in need.\n\nBut not everyone is pleased with Kenshin’s new direction, and enemies from his dark past have vowed to bring him down!\n\n(Source: VIZ Media)", "Rurouni Kenshin: Tokuhitsuban", "Rurouni Kenshin: Restoration", "るるろうに剣心 -特筆版-", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/37303/Rurouni_Kenshin__Tokuhitsuban", 2 },
                    { 37405, "", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/68041.jpg", 3289, 7.45m, new DateTime(2007, 11, 17, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "Sword Art Online: Material Edition is a compilation of the original web novel version of Sword Art Online published as a self-published books.", "Sword Art Online: Material Edition", null, "ソードアート・オンライン マテリアル・エディション", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/37405/Sword_Art_Online__Material_Edition", null },
                    { 37561, "Devilman Grimoire was published in English by Seven Seas Entertainment from October 31, 2017, to December 31, 2018. It was also released in Spanish by Editorial Ivrea from December 13, 2018, to October 3, 2019.", 22, new DateTime(2013, 12, 18, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/189772.jpg", 14279, 6.64m, new DateTime(2012, 3, 18, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "When demons begin taking over the bodies of humans, only the strongest survive. When a practicing young witch named Miki Makimura asks her friend Akira Fudou for help with a ritual, the spell is interrupted and Akira is left on the brink of death. His body is overtaken by a powerful being named Amon. Now torn between his humanity and the demon within him, Akira uses his abilities to fight in the war between demons and humans for the future of the world itself!\n\n(Source: Seven Seas Entertainment)", "Devilman Grimoire", "Devilman Grimoire", "デビルマンG〈グリモワール〉", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/37561/Devilman_Grimoire", 5 },
                    { 37683, "Kidou Senshi Gundam Thunderbolt has been published in English as Mobile Suit Gundam Thunderbolt by VIZ Media under the VIZ Signature imprint since November 15, 2016. Shogakukan Asia has been publishing the series in English in the Southeast Asia region since April 22, 2015.", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/179767.jpg", 1160, 7.84m, new DateTime(2012, 3, 22, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "The Universal Century began with mankind moving its burgeoning population into outer space. The year is UC0079. The cluster of colonies furthest from the Earth, Side 3, proclaim themselves the Principality of Zeon and launch a war of independence against the Earth Federation. Now, it is nearly one year since the war broke out. In the \"Thunderbolt sector,\" a reef section of space where a large quantity of wreckage from battleships and destroyed space colonies from the war lies, a violent battle plays out as the Earth Federation Forces set their sights on recapturing the Zeon controlled sector.\n\n(Source: Zeonic-Republic)", "Kidou Senshi Gundam Thunderbolt", "Mobile Suit Gundam Thunderbolt", "機動戦士ガンダム サンダーボルト", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/37683/Kidou_Senshi_Gundam_Thunderbolt", null },
                    { 37701, "", 10, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/67733.jpg", 16089, 6.5m, new DateTime(2002, 7, 16, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The ultimate cross over manga featuring Mazinger Z, Great Mazinger, Grendizer, Getter Robo, Getter Robo G and Jeeg! These all-stars band together in order to defend Earth from cosmic evil. This manga is in the same vein as all those old Toei cross over movies, and the self-parody gets pretty strong later on.\n\n(Source: Dynamic Pro Scanlations)", "Super Robot Retsuden", null, "スーパーロボット列伝", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/37701/Super_Robot_Retsuden", 1 },
                    { 37755, "", 290, new DateTime(2018, 7, 25, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/179613.jpg", 308, 8.3m, new DateTime(2012, 5, 13, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Kusuo Saiki is not your typical high schooler—behind his glasses, pink hair, and antenna-like appendages exists a being of unfathomable psychic power. Telekinesis, teleportation, and astral projection might sound exciting to the average person, but from Saiki's viewpoint, they are nothing but an annoyance. Psychic powers are unnecessary—this is all that Saiki has believed since he was a kid.\n\nAs a secret esper with the sole dream of living an ordinary life, Saiki tries to use his psychic abilities to stay out of the public's gaze. However, having to clean up after his odd classmates and their antics, all the while keeping his psychic powers a secret, makes it rather difficult to achieve the peaceful life he desires.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]\n\nIncluded one-shots:\nVolume 1: Chounouryokusha Saiki Kusuo no Ψ-nan (pilot)\nVolume 2: Omaenchi, Obake Yashiki\nVolume 3: Gekidan! Improvisation\nVolumes 4, 6: Saiki Kusuo no Ψ-nan &amp; Ansatsu Kyoushitsu: Korosense VS Saiki Kusuo - Iruma-shi Saishuu Kessen\nVolume 12: Terrace House Dust\nVolume 25: Seishounen Yuugai Kankyou Kiseihou", "Saiki Kusuo no Ψ-nan", null, "斉木楠雄のΨ難", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/37755/Saiki_Kusuo_no_Ψ-nan", 26 },
                    { 37999, "", 35, new DateTime(2014, 3, 14, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/68243.jpg", 14675, 6.61m, new DateTime(2011, 10, 14, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The continuation of Inazuma Eleven ten years later.", "Inazuma Eleven Go", null, "イナズマイレブンGO", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/37999/Inazuma_Eleven_Go", 7 },
                    { 39875, "", 11, new DateTime(2002, 12, 15, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/268070.jpg", 7028, 7.12m, new DateTime(2002, 8, 22, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The story takes place between Poseidon and Hades.\n\nAthena and their knights must fight against powerful giants who lives on mount Etna, in Italy.", "Saint Seiya: Gigantomachia", null, "聖闘士星矢 GIGANTOMACHIA", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/39875/Saint_Seiya__Gigantomachia", 2 },
                    { 39883, "Ansatsu Kyoushitsu ranked first in the 2014 Kono Manga ga Sugoi! in the Male Readers division. The manga was named the best work of 2013 on the Book of the Year list by Nippon Shuppan Hanbai. It was nominated for the 2013 Manga Taishou Award, ranking sixth, and the 19th Tezuka Osamu Annual Prize in 2015. The series has sold over 20 million copies as of 2016. The series was published in English as Assassination Classroom by VIZ Media under the Shonen Jump Advanced imprint from December 2, 2014, to April 3, 2018. It was also released in Italian by Planet Manga from May 10, 2014, to September 14, 2017; in Brazilian Portuguese by Panini Comics from 2020 to 2022; in Spanish by Panini Comics from October 1, 2014, to February 22, 2018; and in Polish as Klasa skrytobójców by Japonica Polonica Fantastica from December 14, 2017, to September 2021. A VOMIC version was broadcast in Sakiyomi Jan Bang! from January to June 2013; the series has received a fanbook, databook, spin-off manga, and an illustrated English language guidebook called Koro-tan. A live-action film of the series was released in Japan on March 21, 2015, which opened first at the box office; a second film was released on March 25, 2016.", 187, new DateTime(2016, 4, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/243932.jpg", 361, 8.25m, new DateTime(2012, 7, 1, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "In the blink of an eye, the night sky is forever changed when, with a great explosion, the moon is blasted into a permanent crescent. Confronting the governments of the world, a yellow tentacled monster boasts that it was the one responsible for the catastrophe, and in a year's time, it will do the same to Earth. Zooming around at Mach 20, the creature makes a peculiar demand: a teaching position at the prestigious Kunugigaoka Junior High School. Desperate to keep the creature in one place, the government agrees, and so the students of Class 3-E find themselves faced with an impossible task—assassinate the creature responsible for destroying the moon.\n\nAlthough the fate of the world now rests on their shoulders, the class has more personal issues to deal with. Trapped at the bottom of Kunugigaoka's hierarchical education system, they face harsh discrimination from both teachers and students alike. Defeatism abound, they don't believe themselves capable of success in daily life, let alone against a monster that surpasses the abilities of any human. But as the enigmatic creature—whom they dub Koro-sensei—educates them in both assassination and academia, the children slowly find the courage to rise up and take aim at their target: the greatest teacher the world has ever seen.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]\n\nIncluded one-shot:\nVolume 21: Tokyo Department Sensou Taikenki (Tokyo Department Store War Chronicles)", "Ansatsu Kyoushitsu", "Assassination Classroom", "暗殺教室", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/39883/Ansatsu_Kyoushitsu", 21 },
                    { 40053, "", 39, new DateTime(2016, 8, 8, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/185073.jpg", 3087, 7.48m, new DateTime(2010, 8, 9, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A series of 4-panel comic strips that touch on the days of Aincrad in a comedic viewpoint.", "Sword Art☆Online.", null, "そーどあーと☆おんらいん。", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/40053/Sword_Art☆Online", 3 },
                    { 40225, "", 14, new DateTime(2015, 8, 3, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/70963.jpg", 2343, 7.59m, new DateTime(2010, 8, 3, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "1. Naruto: Dokonjou Ninden (Tale of the Utterly Gutsy Shinobi)\n2. Naruto: Dojunjou Ninden (The Tale of the Utterly Purehearted Shinobi)", "Naruto Ninden Series", null, "NARUTO -ナルト- 忍伝シリーズ", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/40225/Naruto_Ninden_Series", 2 },
                    { 40281, "", 2, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/4/73281.jpg", 7044, 7.12m, new DateTime(2012, 5, 3, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A doujinshi co-authored by Kawahara Reki, under the pen-name of Kunori Fumio, and ponz on Sword Art Online.\n\nNote: Part comic/novel doujinshi. Novel by Kawahara Reki, manga by ponz.\n\nThe contents are:\n\"Sound of Water, Sound of Hammer\" - Kunori Fumio\n\"Extraordinary Ordinary Days\" - ponz", "Sword Art Online dj - Lisbeth Edition", null, "ソードアート・オンライン リズベット・エディション", 6, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/40281/Sword_Art_Online_dj_-_Lisbeth_Edition", 1 },
                    { 40549, "", 1, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/176822.jpg", 6072, 7.19m, new DateTime(2012, 7, 22, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A special one-shot connected to the movie.", "Road to Ninja: Naruto the Movie", null, "ROAD TO NINJA -NARUTO THE MOVIE-", 3, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/40549/Road_to_Ninja__Naruto_the_Movie", null },
                    { 41027, "", 3, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/159662.jpg", 3638, 7.41m, new DateTime(2011, 6, 9, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The alternative version to the Caliber SS from volume 8, where they decided not to save Freyja in the dungeon. The SS in the title means 少し失敗 (sukoshi shippai) which translates to Slight Failure.", "Sword Art Online SS: Calibur SS-han", null, "ソードアート・オンライン SS キャリバーSS（すこししっぱい）版", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/41027/Sword_Art_Online_SS__Calibur_SS-han", null },
                    { 41145, "", 9, new DateTime(2008, 12, 17, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/72203.jpg", 50000, null, new DateTime(2007, 4, 17, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Kobato Jougorou is a boy who wants to improve his habit of deductive reasoning and over-analyzing everything; Osanai Yuki is a girl who is avoided by others because of her strange tendencies. Both of them desire nothing more than to have a simple and peaceful high school life. This is a story about two people who are aiming and working together to be inconspicuous citizens.\n\n(Source: jCafe24)", "Shunki Gentei Ichigo Tart Jiken", null, "春期限定いちごタルト事件", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/41145/Shunki_Gentei_Ichigo_Tart_Jiken", 2 },
                    { 41539, "Mahouka Koukou no Yuutousei was published in English as The Honor Student At Magic High School by Yen Press from November 17, 2015 to June 29, 2021.", 81, new DateTime(2020, 6, 26, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/81456.jpg", 3022, 7.49m, new DateTime(2012, 4, 26, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A century has passed since magic—true magic, the stuff of legends—has returned to the world. It is spring, the season of new beginnings, and a new class of students is about to begin their studies at the First National Magic University Affiliated High School, nickname: First High. A manga spin-off of the immensely popular light novel series The Irregular at Magic High School, The Honor Student at Magic High School follows the events of the original series as seen through the eyes of Miyuki Shiba, Tatsuya's sister. The life of an honor student comes with a lot of expectations...and unexpected hidden feelings?!\n\n(Source: Yen Press)", "Mahouka Koukou no Yuutousei", "The Honor Student At Magic High School", "魔法科高校の優等生", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/41539/Mahouka_Koukou_no_Yuutousei", 11 },
                    { 41835, "", 4, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/73731.jpg", 1473, 7.76m, new DateTime(2012, 8, 16, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Four short stories about adventures of little sisters:\n\n1. Stray dog ~Leave it to Nana!~ (Nana ni Omakase!)\n2. Paper doll ~Changing doll Mikan~ (Kisekae Mikan)\n3. Family trouble ~Yui's papa is shamless!?~ (Yui no Papa wa Harenchi!?)\n4. Secret feelings ~Momo and angel's flute~ (Momo to Tenshi no Fue)", "To LOVE-Ru Darkness: Little Sisters", null, "To LOVEる ダークネス Little Sisters", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/41835/To_LOVE-Ru_Darkness__Little_Sisters", 1 },
                    { 41865, "Hajishirazu no Purple Haze: JoJo no Kimyou na Bouken yori was one of three novels released in celebration of the 25th anniversary of the JoJo no Kimyou na Bouken series.", 8, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/270479.jpg", 480, 8.16m, new DateTime(2011, 9, 15, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "An original story about Fugo Pannacotta, set six months after the end of JoJo no Kimyou na Bouken Part 5: Ougon no Kaze.", "Hajishirazu no Purple Haze: JoJo no Kimyou na Bouken yori", "Purple Haze Feedback", "恥知らずのパープルヘイズ －ジョジョの奇妙な冒険より－", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/41865/Hajishirazu_no_Purple_Haze__JoJo_no_Kimyou_na_Bouken_yori", 1 },
                    { 42439, "", null, new DateTime(2011, 11, 30, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/230102.jpg", 50114, null, new DateTime(2010, 8, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Van Asiliaino, Danica McGuire, and her older brother, Ernest McGuire. The destiny of these three individuals with a connection stronger than family starts to change in a big way since the Zeon Forces invaded Earth during the One Year War. According to the author, Junichi Kamino, AOZ is the chronicle of their conflicts and growth. A story that draws a line of belief while seeking truth in a world without hope. It carries a message of finding hope by yourself in a closed society. Another Z Gundam sidestory, “Advance of Z: The Traitor to Destiny” was created with a new staff, new mecha, characters and setting establishment differing from that of \"Advance of Zeta: The Flag of Titans\".\n\n(Source: Gundam Wiki)", "Advance of Z: Toki ni Aragaishi Mono", "Advance of Z: The Traitor to Destiny", "ADVANCE OF Ζ 刻に抗いし者", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/42439/Advance_of_Z__Toki_ni_Aragaishi_Mono", 4 },
                    { 42441, null, 5, new DateTime(2012, 9, 30, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/4/105217.jpg", 50113, null, new DateTime(2012, 6, 14, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, null, "Kidou Senshi Gundam AGE: Climax Hero", null, "機動戦士ガンダムAGE 〜クライマックスヒーロー〜", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/42441/Kidou_Senshi_Gundam_AGE__Climax_Hero", 1 },
                    { 42571, "", 1, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/4/108975.jpg", 50130, null, new DateTime(1990, 3, 29, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "At some point after the end of the One Year War on U.C. 0080, a ship comes under attack by mobile suits piloted by Zeon remnants, knowing the ship is going down a member of the crew tells Professor Minovsky to board the shuttle and evacuate in one of the escape shuttles. Unfortunately a Zaku II begis to open fire on the area of the ship where Professor Minovsky, had been sitting only moments before.\n\nTrenov Y. Minovsky was born in 1983 (U.C. 0015) in the Ural regions near Chernobyl, Ukraine. At age three, Trenov witnesses the Chernobyl Disaster. After moving to America in 1999 (U.C. 0031) he enrolled in school and began research on a fictitious particle known as \"Minovsky Physics\". But at the time his research was far too unrealistic, and no one understood where he was going with it. However, one of his buddies, Ionesco, informs him that Anaheim Electronics has agreed to sponsor his research. He is thrilled at this, much to the chagrin of Ionesco. Shortly thereafter in U.C. 0040, the Minovsky particle is discovered. However, at a scientific conference, it is determined that the Minovsky particle has no relation to nuclear fusion reactors and that his thesis has no conclusive evidence. The reason behind it comes from Ionesco saying that it only has conventional technological applications. Ionesco also refutes Minovsky's research by stating that a particle with a special nature like it was never detected. As of this, he was deemed an impostor and forever banned from the scientific community. A short time later, he is approached by a representative of Zeon Zum Deikun and later moves to Side 3 in U.C. 0045, and around the same time he created a nuclear fusion generator which was then used to create a artificial Sun for the Colony. At the same time, the \"Minovsky Physics Society\" is established and weapons development is started. However, as he becomes increasingly obsessed with weapons development, which leads to his wife leaving him. Following the death of Zeon Zum Deikun in U.C. 0070, Minovsky receives an award for his developments, but tosses it aside in front of the entire Zabi family. From here he goes back to Earth to once again visit what remains his home of Chernobyl. Presumably sometime in U.C. 0080 he declares silently to himself that he \"beat you\" in reference to the RX-78-2 Gundam, as Minovsky existence alone had brought about more destruction than the Gundam's existence, he also goes on to say that he also probably lost to you in the end anyhow. \n\n(Source: gundam.wikia)", "Stampede: The Story of Professor Minovsky", null, "STAMPEDE ミノフスキー博士物語", 3, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/42571/Stampede__The_Story_of_Professor_Minovsky", null },
                    { 42737, "", 36, new DateTime(2015, 9, 3, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/164178.jpg", 1326, 7.79m, new DateTime(2011, 3, 3, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Who were the legendary \"Generation of Miracles\" that led Teikou Middle School to three consecutive basketball championship titles? The group consisted of five prodigies—alongside their \"Phantom Sixth Member\"—and dominated the courts, striking down any who stood in their way. Outside of the sport, these talented players were simply middle school boys dealing with their own problems, such as getting through the midterm season and surviving an unlucky day.\n\nKuroko no Basuke: Replace captures the off-court adventures of Tetsuya Kuroko and the Generation of Miracles during their days at Teikou.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Kuroko no Basket: Replace", null, "黒子のバスケ -Replace-", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/42737/Kuroko_no_Basket__Replace", 6 },
                    { 42755, "", 35, new DateTime(2015, 9, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/163640.jpg", 12547, 6.76m, new DateTime(2012, 5, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Manga adaptation of the movie 009 Re:Cyborg.", "009 Re:Cyborg", null, "009 RE：CYBORG", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/42755/009_Re_Cyborg", 6 },
                    { 43605, "", 28, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/76783.jpg", 1045, 7.88m, new DateTime(2012, 6, 3, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Follows the events during the seventeen month timeskip after the Aizen battle, involving the eighth generation Kenpachi and a revived Szayel Aporro Granz.", "Bleach: Spirits Are Forever with You", null, "BLEACH Spirits Are Forever With You", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/43605/Bleach__Spirits_Are_Forever_with_You", 2 },
                    { 43607, "", 7, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/77703.jpg", 2786, 7.52m, new DateTime(2012, 9, 3, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A novel set during the seventeenth month timeskip after the battle with Aizen.", "Bleach: The Death Save the Strawberry", null, "BLEACH The Death Save The Strawberry", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/43607/Bleach__The_Death_Save_the_Strawberry", 1 },
                    { 43921, "Sword Art Online: Progressive is a retelling of the Aincrad story arc. The series has been published in English by Yen Press under the Yen On imprint since March 24, 2015. It has also been released in Polish by Kotori since June 28, 2019; and in Spanish by Planeta Cómic since November 17, 2020.", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/77447.jpg", 362, 8.25m, new DateTime(2012, 10, 9, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "One month has passed since Akihiko Kayaba's deadly game began, and the body count continues to rise. Two thousand players are already dead.\n\nKirito and Asuna are two very different people, but they both desire to fight alone. Nonetheless, they find themselves drawn together to face challenges from both within and without. Given that the entire virtual world they now live in has been created as a deathtrap, the surviving players of Sword Art Online are starting to get desperate, and desperation makes them dangerous to loners like Kirito and Asuna. As it becomes clear that solitude equals suicide, will the two be able to overcome their differences to find the strength to believe in each other, and in so doing survive?\n\n(Source: Yen Press)", "Sword Art Online: Progressive", "Sword Art Online: Progressive", "ソードアート・オンライン プログレッシブ", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/43921/Sword_Art_Online__Progressive", null },
                    { 44021, null, 1, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/77631.jpg", 50227, null, null, 2, null, "Violence Jack: Jigoku Machihen", null, "バイオレンスジャック", 3, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/44021/Violence_Jack__Jigoku_Machihen", null },
                    { 44227, "Monogatari Series: Final Season was published in English by Vertical Inc. with Tsukimonogatari as Tsukimonogatari: Possession Tale on April 30, 2019; Koyomimonogatari as Koyomimonogatari: Calendar Tale from June 17, 2019, to August 15, 2019; Owarimonogatari as Owarimonogatari: End Tale from December 16, 2019, to October 27, 2020; and Zoku Owarimonogatari on December 15, 2020.", 231, new DateTime(2014, 9, 17, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/181554.jpg", 31, 8.83m, new DateTime(2012, 9, 27, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "This is a story. The end to the saga of Koyomi Araragi.\n\nThis half-human, half-vampire has stood on the line between reality and the supernatural for far too long. The end to his indecision has finally come. Piece by piece, his humanity was falling away, starting with his reflection. He was becoming one of them—a vampire.\n\nNow, Araragi must choose which world to live in and which to give up. To remain human, he must abandon the friends he made through encounters with the supernatural. On the other hand, he would have to sacrifice his humanity to stay with those he holds dear. \n\nKoyomi Araragi must decide, and his decision will haunt him until the very end. Either way, tragedy seems inevitable, a culmination of every choice made since the very beginning.\n \n[Written by MAL Rewrite]\n\nThis entry includes the final season of the Monogatari Series.", "Monogatari Series: Final Season", null, "〈物語〉シリーズ ファイナルシーズン", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/44227/Monogatari_Series__Final_Season", 6 },
                    { 44319, "Mahou Shoujo Madoka★Magica: The Different Story is loosely adapted from \"Farewell Story,\" the third drama CD made from the story of Mahou Shoujo Madoka★Magica that covers the backstory of Mami and Kyouko. The series was published in English as Puella Magi Madoka Magica: The Different Story by Yen Press from March 25, 2014, to October 28, 2014. It was also published in Brazilian Portuguese by NewPOP Editora.", 12, new DateTime(2012, 11, 11, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/78173.jpg", 512, 8.14m, new DateTime(2012, 6, 11, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Ninth-grader Mami Tomoe is not your average middle schooler. While she regularly attends Mitakihara Middle School, she also works as a magical girl—one who has made a wish in exchange for magical powers and a new duty to seek out and destroy otherworldly beings known as witches. But Mami is also a special case among magical girls—while most fight for their own sake, Mami prefers to work with others, becoming a guardian of justice who destroys any evil creatures she can find, whether it be a witch or a mere familiar. It is this selfless lack of self-interest that often distances her from other magical girls, and as a result, Mami is often lonely.\n\nDuring one of her usual witch hunts, she finds a novice magical girl struggling against a particularly strong witch. After Mami lends her help, the magical girl introduces herself as Kyouko Sakura from the city of Kazamino. Impressed by Mami's skill and hospitality, Kyouko quickly requests to team up with her and become her apprentice.\n\nBeginning as an adaptation of one of the hit anime's drama CDs, Mahou Shoujo Madoka★Magica: The Different Story is a tale of the relationship between two magical girls shown from an alternate perspective.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Mahou Shoujo Madoka★Magica: The Different Story", "Puella Magi Madoka★Magica: The different story", "魔法少女まどか☆マギカ ～The different story～", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/44319/Mahou_Shoujo_Madoka★Magica__The_Different_Story", 3 },
                    { 44347, "One Punch-Man is the manga remake of the original web comic by ONE. In 2014, the series was nominated for the 7th annual Manga Taishou Award and was ranked 7th place. The manga is published in English by VIZ Media under the Shonen Jump imprint; digitally since February 18, 2014, and physically since September 1, 2015. The English version was nominated for the 2015 Eisner Award for Best U.S. Edition of International Material—Asia. It is also published in Polish by J.P. Fantastica since December 5, 2015, in Spanish by Ivrea España since December 31, 2015, in Portuguese (Brazil) by Panini Comics since March 19, 2016, and has been published in Italian by Panini Comics under the Planet Manga imprint since April 7, 2016.", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/80661.jpg", 52, 8.73m, new DateTime(2012, 6, 13, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "After rigorously training for three years, the ordinary Saitama has gained immense strength which allows him to take out anyone and anything with just one punch. He decides to put his new skill to good use by becoming a hero. However, he quickly becomes bored with easily defeating monsters, and wants someone to give him a challenge to bring back the spark of being a hero.\n\nUpon bearing witness to Saitama's amazing power, Genos, a cyborg, is determined to become Saitama's apprentice. During this time, Saitama realizes he is neither getting the recognition that he deserves nor known by the people due to him not being a part of the Hero Association. Wanting to boost his reputation, Saitama decides to have Genos register with him, in exchange for taking him in as a pupil. Together, the two begin working their way up toward becoming true heroes, hoping to find strong enemies and earn respect in the process.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "One Punch-Man", "One-Punch Man", "ワンパンマン", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/44347/One_Punch-Man", null },
                    { 44357, "Trigun: Multiple Bullets was published in English by Dark Horse on March 19, 2013.", 8, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/5/86599.jpg", 8368, 7.03m, new DateTime(2011, 12, 27, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A Trigun anthology.\n\n1-2. Gekijouban Trigun Badlands Rumble: Bangaihen\n3. Trigun: The Lost Plant\n4. Suna no Wakusei no Tami (Denizens of the Sand Planet)\n5. Les Enfants\n6. Eisei Mil Mer TV (Mil/Mer TV)\n7. Raijin: Risin (Trigun: Rising)\n8. Cutting is Fighting", "Trigun: Multiple Bullets", "Trigun: Multiple Bullets", "トライガン・マルチプルバレッツ", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/44357/Trigun__Multiple_Bullets", 1 },
                    { 44485, "Nanatsu no Taizai won the 39th Kodansha Manga Awards in the shounen manga demographic category, alongside Yowamushi Pedal. The series was published in English as The Seven Deadly Sins by Kodansha Comics USA from March 25, 2014 to January 26, 2021; in Spanish by Norma Editorial since September 26, 2014; in French by Pika Edition since March 19, 2014; in Italian by Star Comics since March 29, 2014; in German by Carlsen Manga since March 17, 2015; and in Brazil by JBC since March 21, 2015.", 364, new DateTime(2020, 3, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/153111.jpg", 3267, 7.45m, new DateTime(2012, 10, 9, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "In a world where injustice prevails, the Holy Knights of Britannia protect their homeland with their unparalleled magic and strength. Their most sought-after targets are \"The Seven Deadly Sins\": a group of criminals once regarded as the strongest of Britannia's Holy Knights. Their supposed conspiracy to overthrow the Kingdom of Liones led to their defeat at the hands of the Holy Knights, but rumors persist that the seven infamous knights still live. \n\nTen years later, the Holy Knights ironically stage a coup d'état themselves and capture the King of Liones, installing themselves as the new rulers of the kingdom. Elizabeth Liones, the third princess of the kingdom, sets out on a journey to find the Seven Deadly Sins and request their aid when she stumbles upon a bar owned by Meliodas, the Dragon's Sin of Wrath and the former leader of the disgraced knights. The pair sets out to find Meliodas' old comrades, but will it be hope or despair that awaits them in their travels?\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Nanatsu no Taizai", "The Seven Deadly Sins", "七つの大罪", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/44485/Nanatsu_no_Taizai", 41 },
                    { 44733, "Sword Art Online: Fairy Dance was published in English by Yen Press from June 24, 2014 to March 24, 2015.", 14, new DateTime(2014, 4, 9, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/137905.jpg", 8130, 7.04m, new DateTime(2012, 4, 9, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Kazuto Kirigaya has survived the death game of Aincrad masterminded by Akihiko Kayaba, programmer of Sword Art Online, and made it back to the real world. Unfortunately, the same cannot be said for Asuna Yuuki (aka Asuna the Flash), the girl Kirito fell in love with in the game world and who has yet to awaken from her seemingly endless slumber. As his sister, Suguha, sadly looks on, Kazuto continues to visit Asuna in the hospital in the hope of finding answers... But one day, the answers suddenly find him in the form of a man who claims to be Asuna's fiancé?! With him, the man brings an in-game screenshot of someone who looks a lot like Asuna being held captive! Now Kirito must dive into an all-new VRMMORPG, ALfheim Online, to bring Asuna home!!\n\n(Source: Yen Press)", "Sword Art Online: Fairy Dance", "Sword Art Online: Fairy Dance", "ソードアート・オンライン フェアリィ・ダンス", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/44733/Sword_Art_Online__Fairy_Dance", 3 },
                    { 44933, "Kanshikan Tsunemori Akane is adaptation of studio 's original TV anime series Psycho-Pass, told from the point of view of Akane Tsunemori. The series was published in Brazilian Portuguese as Inspector Akane Tsunemori by Panini Comics since February 22, 2018; in French by Kana; in German by Kazé Germany; in Italian by Planet Manga; and in Polish by Waneko since April 25, 2017.", 27, new DateTime(2014, 12, 3, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/144917.jpg", 833, 7.96m, new DateTime(2012, 11, 1, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "In futuristic Japan, the human soul is analyzed and digitized. A flawless structure called the Sibyl System assesses this data and creates a perfect life for each citizen while also evaluating their potential for crime—otherwise known as one's \"Psycho-Pass.\" Even so, incidents still occur, requiring the existence of the Ministry of Welfare's Public Safety Bureau (MWPSB).\n\nShort on personnel, MWPSB employs latent criminals as Enforcers—morally corrupt individuals whose Psycho-Pass surpasses the allowed threshold—in service of the capable Inspectors. They make use of Dominators, special guns designed to read one's Psycho-Pass, and work together to apprehend wrongdoers.\n\nBeing one of the few people the System considers adequate for MWPSB, Akane Tsunemori is assigned as Criminal Investigation Division's new Inspector of Division 01. Secured by her strong sense of justice, Tsunemori's Psycho-Pass is unwavering in the face of incurable fugitives on both the just and rotten sides of the system. But early into her career, Tsunemori encounters a person thought impossible: a criminal with the Psycho-Pass of a righteous man.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Kanshikan Tsunemori Akane", "Inspector Akane Tsunemori", "監視官 常守朱", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/44933/Kanshikan_Tsunemori_Akane", 6 },
                    { 45996, "Hunter x Hunter: Kurapika Tsuioku-hen was included with Hunter x Hunter Volume 0, which was given as a gift to the first one million guests who attended the theatrical screenings of Hunter x Hunter Movie 1: Phantom Rouge. The series was published digitally in English as Hunter x Hunter: Kurapika's Memories by VIZ Media from December 17, 2012, to December 24, 2012.", 2, new DateTime(2012, 12, 8, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/263115.jpg", 2016, 7.64m, new DateTime(2012, 12, 1, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The people of the Kurta Clan live deep in the forest, far from the presence of outsiders. Susceptible to prejudice and discrimination because of their scarlet eyes, they remain hidden from the general public, letting only a distinct few clan members venture outside.\n\nBut after helping Sheila—a woman who found herself stranded in the forest—Kurapika and his best friend Pyro become fascinated with the outside world. In order to achieve his dreams of exploring life beyond the forest, Kurapika must pass the clan elder's three tests in order to be granted permission.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Hunter x Hunter: Kurapika Tsuioku-hen", "Hunter x Hunter: Kurapika's Memories", "HUNTER×HUNTER クラピカ追憶編", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/45996/Hunter_x_Hunter__Kurapika_Tsuioku-hen", 1 },
                    { 46010, "xxxHOLiC: Rei was published in English by Kodansha Comics USA from April 29, 2014 to August 15, 2017. It is also being published in Spanish by Norma Editorial since August 20, 2014.", 56, new DateTime(2017, 3, 12, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/243539.jpg", 459, 8.18m, new DateTime(2013, 3, 3, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 3, "A new story begins with Watanuki and Yuuko, while guests wishes are granted.\n\n(Source: LuffyNoTomo)", "xxxHOLiC: Rei", "xxxHOLiC Rei", "xxxHOLiC・戻", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/46010/xxxHOLiC__Rei", 4 },
                    { 46222, "", 2, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/81604.jpg", 10794, 6.87m, new DateTime(2012, 11, 17, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A doujinshi co-authored by Kawahara Reki, under the pen-name of Kunori Fumio, and Kurusu Tatsuya on Sword Art Online.\n\nNote: Part comic/novel doujinshi. Novel by Kawahara Reki, manga by Kurusu Tatsuya.\n\nThe contents are:\n\"The Final Promise\"\n\"A Spot of Sunshine in the Winter\"", "Sword Art Online dj - Silica Edition", null, "ソードアート・オンライン シリカ・エディション", 6, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/46222/Sword_Art_Online_dj_-_Silica_Edition", 1 },
                    { 46582, "", 11, new DateTime(2013, 6, 25, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/82322.jpg", 2270, 7.6m, new DateTime(2012, 10, 23, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Two side stories bundled with limited editions of anime Blu-ray/DVD.", "Sword Art Online Side Stories", null, "ソードアート・オンライン", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/46582/Sword_Art_Online_Side_Stories", 2 },
                    { 46604, "Jorge Joestar was one of three novels released in commemoration of the 30th anniversary since Araki's debut and the 25th anniversary of the JoJo no Kimyou na Bouken series as a part of 'ARAKI 30th & JOJO 25th / 2011-2012 JUMP j BOOKS Presents Special Project\"VS JOJO\"' project.", 16, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/82348.jpg", 11291, 6.84m, new DateTime(2012, 9, 18, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "After Jonathan's death, his son, George Joestar II travels with Erina to live in La Palma of the Canary Islands in Spain. There he pledges his love to Lisa Lisa and eventually grows to be a World War I Air pilot.\n\n(Source: JoJo's Bizarre Encyclopedia Wikia)", "Jorge Joestar", null, "JORGE JOESTAR", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/46604/Jorge_Joestar", 1 },
                    { 47102, "Aho Girl was published in English as Aho-Girl: A Clueless Girl by Kodansha Comics USA since July 18, 2017 to April 16, 2019.", 155, new DateTime(2017, 12, 8, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/184551.jpg", 10414, 6.9m, new DateTime(2012, 11, 27, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "This 4-koma style manga features Yoshiko, a genuinely stupid girl (she can even manage to get all 0's on multiple choice tests). She hangs out at school with her childhood friend, who she claims to like, and he has to put up with all her ridiculous behavior!\n\n(Source: MangaHelpers)\n\nIncluded one-shot:\nVolume 12: Nandemo Shiteageru (I'd do anything for you.)", "Aho Girl", "Aho-Girl: Clueless Girl", "アホガール", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/47102/Aho_Girl", 12 },
                    { 47248, "", 6, new DateTime(2013, 1, 25, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/282844.jpg", 50500, null, new DateTime(2012, 9, 25, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "After deploying several sleeper agents around the globe, the Vagans launch a surprise attack that finally brings the war to the Earth. To counter the invasion, Flit activates the recently completed Gundam AGE-3 and entrusts it to Kio. Just like his father and grandfather before him, Kio enlists into the Diva as part of its mobile suit squad to confront the Vagans.\n\n(Source: Gundam Wikia)", "Kidou Senshi Gundam AGE: Final Evolution", null, "機動戦士ガンダムAGE Final Evolution", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/47248/Kidou_Senshi_Gundam_AGE__Final_Evolution", 1 },
                    { 47363, "Kamisama no Iutoori 2 starts at the same time as the original but follows the survival story of new characters. The series was published digitally in English as As the Gods Will: The Second Series by Kodansha USA from November 3, 2015, to October 10, 2017.", 186, new DateTime(2016, 12, 27, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/187899.jpg", 1224, 7.82m, new DateTime(2013, 1, 15, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "High school student Yasuto Akashi's day begins like any other, but a fight with his best friend—Senichi Aoyama—causes him to skip school. Akashi realizes that he is in the wrong, and so he immediately returns to school. However, instead of open gates, he finds the school completely sealed off from the outside world. Soon after, a giant cat's head blasts through the windows, and Akashi spots Aoyama dressed in a rat costume while drenched in blood.\n\nOnly three students manage to leave school alive that day, and similar occurrences are reported throughout the world. Akashi is not free from harm, however, as he is invited to partake in a deadly game whose participants are composed of those who missed school on that fateful day.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Kamisama no Iutoori 2", "As the Gods Will: The Second Series", "神さまの言うとおり弐", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/47363/Kamisama_no_Iutoori_2", 21 },
                    { 47533, "", 1, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/83837.jpg", 17030, 6.41m, new DateTime(2012, 12, 21, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A standalone one-shot published by Araki, accompanying the multi-media campaign for his window illustrations on the new collection of the fashion brand Gucci.\n\nThe story is about Jolyne Kujo, who goes on a fantastic adventure when she tries to unravel the mystery behind a vintage piece she inherited from her mother's Gucci collection.\n\n(Source: Japan Daily Press)", "Jolyne, Gucci de Tobu", null, "徐倫、GUCCIで飛ぶ", 3, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/47533/Jolyne_Gucci_de_Tobu", null },
                    { 47551, "Danball Senki is based on the 2011 PlayStation Portable video game of the same name. The series was published in English as LBX: Little Battlers Experience by VIZ Media under the Perfect Square imprint from November 4, 2014, to July 7, 2015. The manga was also released in Spanish by Planeta DeAgostini Comics from January 13, 2015, to January 12, 2016.", 28, new DateTime(2013, 2, 14, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/109525.jpg", 50521, null, new DateTime(2011, 1, 14, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "By the 2040s, technology has advanced to the point where Professor Junichirou Yamano is able to build mini-robots possessing massive destructive power. He names them Little Battlers eXperience (LBX), and he believes that they will one day change the world. But Yamano's fate proves cruel, as the plane carrying him and his fellow designers vanishes above the Pacific Ocean, never to be seen again.\n\nYears later, the invention of extremely durable cardboard inspires the production of small-scale scenic battlefields. Within these miniature arenas, kids remotely control their LBXs, engaging in exciting combat showdowns. Professor Yamano's son, Ban, shares his father's passion for LBX, but his mother forbids him to get one. However, that changes when an injured woman in a lab coat hands him a mysterious suitcase before fleeing from her pursuers. Inside the case is LBX AX-00, a unique model that becomes Ban's robot partner Achilles—and eventually humanity's last hope.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Danball Senki", "LBX: Little Battlers Experience", "ダンボール戦機", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/47551/Danball_Senki", 6 },
                    { 48321, "", 42, new DateTime(2016, 6, 19, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/95927.jpg", 3627, 7.42m, new DateTime(2013, 3, 12, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Manga adaption of Koukaku Kidoutai: Arise anime.\n\nAlso contains a short story, Natsu no Owari ni.", "Koukaku Kidoutai: Arise - Sleepless Eye", null, "攻殻機動隊ARISE～眠らない眼の男 Sleepless Eye～", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/48321/Koukaku_Kidoutai__Arise_-_Sleepless_Eye", 7 },
                    { 49305, "", 75, new DateTime(2021, 3, 30, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/175669.jpg", 3091, 7.48m, new DateTime(2012, 9, 28, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "\"Hey, you said you wanted a little sister, right?\" First year high school student, Toujou Basara, was suddenly asked by his father and fell into a state of panic. On top of that, the eccentric father told him he will be getting remarried. He then departed overseas after bringing Basara two beautiful step-sisters. But Mio and Maria's true forms are actually the newbie Demon Lord and a succubus!? Basara was almost entered into a master and servant contract with Mio, but a \"reversed\" contract was formed by mistake, and Basara is now the master!? Moreover, Basara is being hit by ecchi situation one after another due to the contract, but Mio's life is being pursued by other demon tribes and hero tribes!! The most powerful contractor's desire action drama begins!\n\n(Source: MU)", "Shinmai Maou no Testament", "The Testament of Sister New Devil", "新妹魔王の契約者〈テスタメント〉", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/49305/Shinmai_Maou_no_Testament", 13 },
                    { 49547, "Durarara!! Kokinzoku-hen adapts the third novel in the series. It was published in English as Durarara!! Yellow Scarves Arc by Yen Press from September 23, 2014 to July 21, 2015. The series has also been released in Polish as Durarara!! Yellow Flag Orchestra by Waneko since October 6, 2016.", 19, new DateTime(2014, 10, 17, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/149952.jpg", 1451, 7.76m, new DateTime(2013, 4, 17, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "As Izaya Orihara wildly enjoys holding all the information about Ikebukuro's main players, Mikado Ryuugamine and Masaomi Kida stay by Anri Sonohara's side while she recovers. However, Kida seems to be faking a smile. Enraged by the circumstances that led to Anri's harm and his own helplessness, Kida returns to the world he vowed to never come back to after Izaya interfered with them—the Yellow Scarves gang.\n\nOnce the Yellow Scarves' leader, Kida knows that many of his old team members may now be a part of the Dollars, but they are losing their trust in the group's misdirected ideals. With the power of the Yellow Scarves' unwavering loyalty behind him, Kida swears to clean up Ikebukuro's streets of all wrongdoers, especially those in support of the recently faced criminal, the Slasher. But his aspirations and determination are put to the test, as Izaya is not the only one powerful enough to stand in his way.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Durarara!! Kokinzoku-hen", "Durarara!! Yellow Scarves Arc", "デュラララ!! 黄巾賊編", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/49547/Durarara_Kokinzoku-hen", 3 },
                    { 49551, "", 5, new DateTime(2013, 7, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/121603.jpg", 19473, 5.81m, new DateTime(2013, 3, 25, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The god of war and guardian of his namesake planet, Mars, was once sealed away by Seiya, but time has passed and his revival is at hand. Meanwhile, Saori Kido (Athena) is raising the boy Kouga, whose life Seiya saved, and he's been training every day to become a Saint in order to prepare for the coming crisis... \n\nUnaware of his destiny, when Kouga awakens to the power of his Cosmo hidden inside him, the curtain will rise upon the legend of a new Saint.", "Saint Seiya Omega: New Cross Tanjou-hen", null, "聖闘士星矢Ω 新生聖衣（ニュークロス）誕生編", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/49551/Saint_Seiya_Omega__New_Cross_Tanjou-hen", 1 },
                    { 49567, "", 120, new DateTime(2017, 10, 19, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/145019.jpg", 710, 8.02m, new DateTime(2012, 7, 19, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Die-hard otaku Tomoya Aki never imagined himself falling for a girl in real life until one of his spring breaks, when he experienced a picturesque encounter with a mysterious beauty. Reminiscing about the brief yet enchanting event, he decides to produce a bishoujo game—a game focused on attractive girls—with the sole purpose of capturing the allure of that idyllic scene.\n\nDays fly by, and Tomoya enters his second year of high school having made no progress on his game. On top of that, he is shocked to discover that the girl he met is his unremarkable classmate, Megumi Katou. Determined to make his game a reality, Tomoya ropes Megumi into the project and sets out to convince his childhood friend Eriri Spencer Sawamura and upperclassman Utaha Kasumigaoka to help with its development. Tomoya soon finds out, however, that working with friends on such an ambitious project is much more difficult than he initially thought.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Saenai Heroine no Sodatekata", "How to Raise a Boring Girlfriend", "冴えない彼女〈ヒロイン〉の育てかた", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/49567/Saenai_Heroine_no_Sodatekata", 13 },
                    { 49859, "Neon Genesis Evangelion: Comic Tribute was published in English by Dark Horse on February 20, 2013.", 19, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/181288.jpg", 12945, 6.73m, new DateTime(2010, 4, 2, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "If you thought Evangelion's characters have a tough time in the anime, wait until you see what happens when some of Japan's most unhinged manga artists get their ink-stained hands on them! Neon Genesis Evangelion: Comic Tribute is an officially authorized one-shot anthology of parody stories assaulting Evangelion from all directions. \n\n(Source: Dark Horse Comics)\n\nTable of contents:\n1, 15, 16. Neon Genesis Revolutionary Legend Evangelion [by Kawata Yushi and Yukito]\n2. Drowning in L.C.L.\n3. Let's Study with NERV! [by Teri Terio]\n4. Neon Genesis Tanakagelion [by Tanaka Keiichi]\n5. Misato Katsuragi's The Shinji Ikari Raising Project Report\n6, 19. Tony Takezaki's Neon Genesis Evangelion [by Tony Takezaki]\n7. Neon Genesis Evandoglion [by Karasawa Nawoki]\n8. Mr.Director Anno\n9. Shinji and Asuka's Hot Day [by Igarashi Ran]\n10. Don't You Dance Like You Want to Win!\n11. In Sickness Unto Sudden Death Overtime\n12. Eva-san\n13. Decisive Battle! Evangelion Online!\n14. Angel Fight\n17. Eternal Fourteen\n18. I Forgave You Long Ago", "Shinseiki Evangelion: Comic Tribute", "Neon Genesis Evangelion: Comic Tribute", "新世紀エヴァンゲリオン コミックトリビュート", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/49859/Shinseiki_Evangelion__Comic_Tribute", 1 },
                    { 50117, "", null, new DateTime(2013, 10, 1, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/88513.jpg", 907, 7.93m, new DateTime(2012, 6, 8, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 3, "The dark fantasy follows a high school sophomore named Akihito Kanbara. Although the boy appears human, he is half yōmu and invulnerable to wounds because he can heal quickly. One day, Akihito meets freshman Mirai Kuriyama when it seems she is about to jump from the school rooftop. Mirai is isolated because of her ability to manipulate blood, which is unique even among members of the spirit world. Disturbing events begin to unfold after Akihito saves Mirai.\n\n(Source: ANN)", "Kyoukai no Kanata", null, "境界の彼方", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/50117/Kyoukai_no_Kanata", 3 },
                    { 50161, null, null, new DateTime(2013, 3, 31, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/88607.jpg", 50690, null, new DateTime(2011, 11, 30, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, null, "Inazuma Eleven Go Anthology!", null, "イナズマイレブンGO アンソロジー!", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/50161/Inazuma_Eleven_Go_Anthology", 1 },
                    { 51023, "Absolute Duo was published in English by Seven Seas Entertainment since August 29, 2017 to November 27, 2018.", 24, new DateTime(2017, 7, 26, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/148013.jpg", 11251, 6.84m, new DateTime(2013, 4, 26, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "To avenge the death of his younger sister, Tooru Kokonoe enters the prestigious Koryo Academy, a high school dedicated to training its students to wield Blaze—individualized weapons that are manifestations of one's soul. While the future of a student is often determined by the form their weapon takes, Tooru is an Irregular, whose Blaze appears as a shield instead of a melee weapon. How can Tooru possibly learn to use his defensive abilities to fight effectively? That's when the Duo system comes in, a program where students are paired up as battle mates, classmates, and roommates. Tooru's is paired with a silver-haired girl from Scandinavia named Julie Sigtuna, who possesses a power the likes of which has never been seen, and shares his thirst for revenge.\n\n(Source: Seven Seas Entertainment)", "Absolute Duo", "Absolute Duo", "アブソリュート・デュオ", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/51023/Absolute_Duo", 4 },
                    { 51025, "", 84, new DateTime(2016, 7, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/175374.jpg", 5345, 7.25m, new DateTime(2012, 8, 22, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 3, "After losing a loved one, Tooru Kokonoe enrolls at Kouryou Academy so as to gain a 《Blaze》, a weapon that is his soul manifestation, for the sake of revenge. He was expecting a weapon... What he got was a shield... How is he to seek revenge with something that isn't even a weapon?!\n\n(Source: MU)", "Absolute Duo", null, "アブソリュート・デュオ", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/51025/Absolute_Duo", 11 },
                    { 51309, "Saenai Heroine no Sodatekata was published in English as How To Raise A Boring Girlfriend by Yen Press from January 26, 2016 to December 19, 2017.", 42, new DateTime(2016, 8, 8, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/182516.jpg", 3650, 7.41m, new DateTime(2013, 1, 8, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The life of Tomoya Aki, a high school otaku working part time to support his BD hoarding. With remarkable luck, he bumps head-first into, Megumi Katou, the most beautiful girl he has ever seen. Naturally, the meeting twists his life into a complicated torrent of relationships. Eriri Spencer Sawamura, his half-foreigner childhood friend who's always valued her relationship with MC. Utaha Kasumigaoka, a cold, composed renowned literary genius who shoves everyone aside from our protagonist. What is this? An eroge introduction?\n\nThe tale of a small not quite doujin circle, but not quite indie studio's journey through the tough territory of Comiket and beyond.", "Saenai Heroine no Sodatekata", "How to Raise a Boring Girlfriend", "冴えない彼女〈ヒロイン〉の育てかた", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/51309/Saenai_Heroine_no_Sodatekata", 8 },
                    { 51313, "", 15, new DateTime(2014, 5, 1, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/181003.jpg", 8020, 7.05m, new DateTime(2013, 2, 3, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A high school otaku named Aki Tomoya runs into his dream girl one day... only to find that she has the faintest presence to his chagrin!\n\nNow with his otaku passions, Tomoya wants to turn the girl into a heroine in the only realm he is familiar with: 2D dating simulation game. To accomplish this objective, he scouts Eriri Spencer Sawamura, his half-foreigner childhood friend equipped with artistic talent, as the illustrator, and Kasumigaoka Utaha, a famous prodigy writer, as the script writer.\n\n(Source: Batoto)", "Saenai Heroine no Sodatekata: Egoistic-Lily", null, "冴えない彼女〈ヒロイン〉の育てかた ～egoistic-lily～", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/51313/Saenai_Heroine_no_Sodatekata__Egoistic-Lily", 3 },
                    { 51755, "Shinmai Maou no Testament was published in English as The Testament of Sister New Devil by Seven Seas Entertainment from January 19, 2016 to July 31, 2018. It has also been published in Italian and Brazilian Portuguese by Panini Comics under the Planet Manga imprint since June 6, 2015 and July 2016, respectively.", 46, new DateTime(2017, 4, 25, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/105683.jpg", 6684, 7.15m, new DateTime(2013, 5, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "\"Hey, you said you wanted an little sister, right?\" First year high school student, Toujo Basara, was suddenly asked by his farther and fell into a state of panic. On top of that, the eccentric father told him he will be getting remarried. He then departed overseas after bringing Basara two beautiful step-sisters. But Mio and Maria's true forms are actually the newbie Demon Lord and a succubus!? Basara was almost entered into a master and servant contract with Mio, but a \"reversed\" contract was formed by mistake, and Basara is now the master!? Moreover, Basara is being hit by ecchi situation one after another due to the contract, but Mio's life is being pursued by other demon tribes and hero tribes!! The most powerful contractor's desire action drama begins!\n\n(Source: MU)", "Shinmai Maou no Testament", "The Testament of Sister New Devil", "新妹魔王の契約者〈テスタメント〉", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/51755/Shinmai_Maou_no_Testament", 9 },
                    { 52277, "Sword Art Online: Progressive was published in English by Yen Press from January 5, 2015, to December 11, 2018. It was also released in Spanish by Planeta Cómic from June 23, 2020, to March 23, 2022.", 47, new DateTime(2018, 2, 27, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/164933.jpg", 922, 7.92m, new DateTime(2013, 6, 28, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "\"This game is impossible to clear. It's just a matter of when, where and how you die.\"\n\nKayaba Akihiko's death game has been up for one month. This incredibly difficult VRMMO has already claimed 2000 victims. It's the day of the 1st floor boss strategy meeting. The solo player Kirito, who's decided to only strengthen himself, meets a rare female player on the current front lines, while heading to the meeting around noon. Fighting alone against the strong monsters, she was like a meteor cutting the night sky.", "Sword Art Online: Progressive", "Sword Art Online: Progressive", "ソードアート・オンライン プログレッシブ", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/52277/Sword_Art_Online__Progressive", 7 },
                    { 52353, "", 25, new DateTime(2014, 1, 3, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/114119.jpg", 19187, 6m, new DateTime(2012, 12, 2, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "One Piece spin-off starring Chopper.", "Chopperman", null, "チョッパーマン", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/52353/Chopperman", 5 },
                    { 52389, "", 1, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/92509.jpg", 7351, 7.1m, new DateTime(2013, 6, 12, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "\"Ao Haru Ride\" and \"Ore Monogatari!!\" special collaboration one-shot, celebrating \"Bessatsu Margaret\" 50th anniversary since launch.", "Ore Ride!!", null, "俺ライド!!", 3, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/52389/Ore_Ride", null },
                    { 54627, "Ginga Patrol Jaco was published in English as Jaco the Galactic Patrolman by VIZ Media under the Shonen Jump imprint on January 6, 2015. It was also published in Spanish by Planeta Cómic in March 2015, and in Polish by J.P.Fantastica in May 2018. A VOMIC version of the first two chapters was broadcast in Sakiyomi JanBang! program in January 2014.", 12, new DateTime(2013, 9, 29, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/120565.jpg", 9112, 6.98m, new DateTime(2013, 7, 12, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Retired scientist Omori lives alone on a deserted island while continuing his research into time-travel. His quiet life in interrupted when galactic patrolman Jaco crash-lands and decides to move in with him. This agent from space claims to be elite, but sometimes it can a little hard to believe. Can Jaco get along with the old man long enough to save the earth from a dangerous threat?\n\n(Source: VIZ Media)", "Ginga Patrol Jaco", "Jaco the Galactic Patrolman", "銀河パトロール ジャコ", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/54627/Ginga_Patrol_Jaco", 1 },
                    { 54697, "", 1, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/97209.jpg", 8698, 7.01m, new DateTime(2012, 8, 17, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Fairy Tail: Houou no Miko - Hajimari no Asa is a special prologue chapter to Fairy Tail Movie 1: Houou no Miko, introducing Éclair and depicting the accidental creation of her best friend, Momon, while also showing the start of their journey across Fiore. \n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Fairy Tail: Houou no Miko - Hajimari no Asa", null, "劇場版 FAIRY TAIL 序章 「はじまりの朝」", 3, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/54697/Fairy_Tail__Houou_no_Miko_-_Hajimari_no_Asa", null },
                    { 54761, "Saint Seiya: Saintia Shou was published in English by Seven Seas Entertainment from February 20, 2018, to January 17, 2023. It was also released in French by Kurokawa from February 12, 2015, to September 8, 2022; in Brazilian Portuguese as Os Cavaleiros do Zodíaco: Saintia Shô by JBC from October 22, 2016, to May 24, 2023; and in Spanish as Los Caballeros Del Zodiaco: Saintia Sho by Editorial Ivréa from June 16, 2017, to October 5, 2023.", 88, new DateTime(2021, 7, 18, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/154143.jpg", 6456, 7.16m, new DateTime(2013, 8, 18, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The whole Sanctuary was misled into danger due to the civil war instigated by the Gemini Gold Saint, Saga. Our story begins right after the end of those events... This is a story of the girls protecting Athena. These are the records of love and fierce fights they meet while opposing destiny on their way to maturity...\n\n(Source: MangaSeven)", "Saint Seiya: Saintia Shou", "Saint Seiya: Saintia Shou", "聖闘士星矢 セインティア翔", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/54761/Saint_Seiya__Saintia_Shou", 16 },
                    { 55157, "", 90, new DateTime(2017, 11, 1, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/158128.jpg", 7228, 7.1m, new DateTime(2013, 7, 1, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "With the sudden appearance of the monsters that came to be called Dragons, the world had completely changed. Before long, within the human race supernatural girls with the power of the dragons, called \"D\", were born. The secret existence of the only male \"D\", the boy Mononobe Yuu, was forcefully thrown into the school where the girls of \"D\" gathered - Midgar, where he saw the naked body of one of the students, Iris. Furthermore, meeting his long lost sister Mitsuki, Yuu seems to have been enrolled into this school...!? \"When there's really no other choice, Iris, I will — kill you.\" \"Can I really... believe you?\" The curtains open as the \"one and only story\" about the boy who was supposed to become the strongest assassin and the incompetent girl unfolds—! Unlimited School Battle Action!\n\n(Source: Baka-Tsuki)", "Juuou Mujin no Fafnir", null, "銃皇無尽のファフニール", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/55157/Juuou_Mujin_no_Fafnir", 15 },
                    { 55867, "", 21, new DateTime(2014, 7, 1, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/97365.jpg", 1148, 7.84m, new DateTime(2013, 7, 7, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A prequel to the 2013 Kyoto Animation series Free!.\n\nThe first novel is about sixth grader Haruka Nanase, who sets up a relay team with his childhood friend Makoto Tachibana, a cheerful junior called Nagisa Hazuki and a newly transferred student, Rin Matsuoka.\n\nThe second novel is set in Haruka and Makoto's first year at middle school, and tells about their experiences at the swim team along with two new characters, Ikuya Kirishima and Asahi Shiina.", "High☆Speed!", null, "ハイ☆スピード!", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/55867/High☆Speed", 2 },
                    { 55875, "Sword Art Online: Girls Ops was published in English by Yen Press from May 19, 2015 to September 6, 2022.", 47, new DateTime(2021, 1, 7, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/156370.jpg", 5806, 7.21m, new DateTime(2013, 6, 9, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Follows the heroines from the Aincrad arc through their various adventures in the real world at the SAO Survivor School and in the virtual world of ALfheim Online.", "Sword Art Online: Girls Ops", "Sword Art Online: Girls' Ops", "ソードアート・オンライン ガールズ・オプス", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/55875/Sword_Art_Online__Girls_Ops", 8 },
                    { 56011, "", 5, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/97547.jpg", 5424, 7.24m, new DateTime(2009, 8, 2, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Based on the popular manga To-Love-Ru, the novel begins with Haruna and her friends at karaoke, having a \"girly talk\" something risque... Haruna has an erotic dream and says to her friends?! Saki working as a nurse?! This new publication, full of splendid illustrations, shows a facet of heroines that can not be viewed in the manga.", "To LOVE-Ru: Abunai Girls Talk", null, "To Loveる 危ないガールズトーク", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/56011/To_LOVE-Ru__Abunai_Girls_Talk", 1 },
                    { 56169, "", 2, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/97903.jpg", 16304, 6.48m, new DateTime(2013, 5, 5, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "1. The Fourteenth Autumn (十四回目の秋); Aincrad 35th floor, October 4, 2024\nBrief story about Silica and Kirito approximately one month before the clearing of SAO. Also introduces the «Angel's Ring», which is used later in Sword Art Online: Girls Ops.", "Sword Art Online dj - Pina Edition", null, "ソードアート・オンライン ピナ・エディション", 6, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/56169/Sword_Art_Online_dj_-_Pina_Edition", 1 },
                    { 56725, "", 9, new DateTime(2013, 3, 5, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/98669.jpg", 10076, 6.92m, new DateTime(2012, 3, 9, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Collection of special chapters that were published for 2011 Great East Japan Earthquake Relief Effort Project.", "3.11 wo Wasurenai Tame ni Heroes Comeback", null, "3.11を忘れないために ヒーローズ・カムバック", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/56725/311_wo_Wasurenai_Tame_ni_Heroes_Comeback", 1 },
                    { 56743, "Dungeon ni Deai wo Motomeru no wa Machigatteiru Darou ka has been published in English as Is It Wrong to Try to Pick Up Girls in a Dungeon? by Yen Press under the Yen On imprint since December 16, 2014. It has also been published in Italian by J-POP since June 30, 2016.", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/186978.jpg", 381, 8.23m, new DateTime(2013, 1, 14, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "In Orario, fearless adventurers band together in search of fame and fortune within the monstrous underground labyrinth known as Dungeon. But while riches and renown are incentive enough for most, Bell Cranel, would-be hero extraordinaire, has bigger plans. He wants to pick up girls.\n\nIs it wrong to face the perils of Dungeon alone, in a single-member guild blessed by a failed goddess? Maybe. Is it wrong to dream of playing hero to hapless maidens in Dungeon? Maybe not. After one misguided adventure, Bell quickly discovers that anything can happen in the labyrinth—even chance encounters with beautiful women. The only problem? He's the one who winds up the damsel in distress!\n\n(Source: Yen Press)", "Dungeon ni Deai wo Motomeru no wa Machigatteiru Darou ka", "Is It Wrong to Try to Pick Up Girls in a Dungeon?", "ダンジョンに出会いを求めるのは間違っているだろうか", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/56743/Dungeon_ni_Deai_wo_Motomeru_no_wa_Machigatteiru_Darou_ka", null },
                    { 56945, "As part of the JUMP START initiative, the first three chapters of ēlDLIVE were published in English in VIZ Media's digital Weekly Shonen Jump from September 29 to October 20, 2014. The series was published digitally by VIZ Media under the Shonen Jump imprint from April 25, 2017 to October 22, 2019.", null, new DateTime(2018, 11, 4, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/173532.jpg", 13062, 6.72m, new DateTime(2013, 7, 31, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "For as long as he can remember, 14-year-old Chuuta Kokonose has been pestered by a mysterious voice in his head. Due to this, his unknowing classmates tease him for having an odd habit of talking to himself. One day, Chuuta is followed home by a three-eyed, jellyfish-like creature who abruptly shoots him with a beam of light. He suddenly finds himself in a room filled with even more strange-looking creatures—in a place he soon discovers to be a space police station. There, he is told by Laine Brick, the chief of the solar system bureau, that he has been selected as a suitable candidate to join their agency ēlDLIVE.\n\nBut Misuzu Sonokata—Chuuta's classmate and crush who turns out to be an ēlDLIVE member—is opposed to him joining, arguing that he does not have the qualities of an officer. Provoked by Misuzu's remarks and at the insistence of the voice in his head, Chuuta decides to take the qualifying exam to join the agency. However, the exam leads to him discovering that the identity of the strange voice in his head was an alien living in his body all along.\n\nēlDLIVE follows Chuuta, Misuzu, and the rest of the solar system bureau as they endeavor to protect the citizens and the public order of the universe.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "ēlDLIVE", "élDLIVE", "エルドライブ 【ēlDLIVE】", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/56945/ēlDLIVE", 11 },
                    { 57051, "", 14, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/270475.jpg", 2012, 7.64m, new DateTime(1993, 11, 3, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The story in this book recounts events that are completely unknown in the manga that take place in the course of the adventures of Jotaro Kujo and his comrades. Their march to the lair of Dio Brando is interrupted by three powerful Stand users.", "JoJo no Kimyou na Bouken", null, "ジョジョの奇妙な冒険", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/57051/JoJo_no_Kimyou_na_Bouken", 1 },
                    { 57095, "Naruto: Takigakure no Shitou Ore ga Hero dattebayo! was published in English as Naruto - Mission: Protect the Waterfall Village! by VIZ Media under the Shounen Jump imprint on October 16, 2007.", 16, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/261417.jpg", 12784, 6.74m, new DateTime(2003, 12, 14, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "It was supposed to be just an ordinary, C-rank assigment—but nothing about ninjutsu is as simple as it seems...\n\nSquad Seven's latest job is a real snore—escorting a young, cowardly leader named Shibuki back to the remote Hidden Waterfall Village. They arrive without a problem, but get stuck cleaning the village pond! While Naruto and his pals pick up the trash, Kakashi is called back to his home village on urgent business.\n\nThen, without warning, a brilliant rogue ninja shows up in tow with his evil henchmen. Suien desperately desires the Hidden Waterfall's most precious possession, a secret potion called the Hero's Water. And as Squad Seven quickly discovers, the guy will do absolutely anything to get it! With their fearless sensei gone, Naruto, Sasuke, and Sakura find themselves in the most deadly situation of their young lives.\n\n(Source: VIZ Media)", "Naruto: Takigakure no Shitou Ore ga Hero dattebayo!", "Naruto - Mission: Protect the Waterfall Village!", "NARUTO 滝隠れの死闘 オレが英雄だってばよ!", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/57095/Naruto__Takigakure_no_Shitou_Ore_ga_Hero_dattebayo", 1 },
                    { 57101, "", 171, new DateTime(2018, 6, 14, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/177486.jpg", 6255, 7.18m, new DateTime(2012, 11, 14, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The series takes place in a private high school involving the concept of \"saviors.\" They are known as people who possess awakened memories of their past lives. The story tells of a young boy named Moroha Haimura who comes to this private school.\n\nAt the school, there are two types of people: Saviors, who fight enemies with weapons and techniques gleaned from the Puraana powers from their own bodies, and Kuroma, who wipe out enemies with magic to manipulate the Maana powers that surpass physics. Moroha Haimura is the first person with past lives of both Shirogane and Kuroma.\n\n(Source: ANN, edited)", "Seiken Tsukai no World Break", null, "聖剣使いの禁呪詠唱〈ワールドブレイク〉", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/57101/Seiken_Tsukai_no_World_Break", 22 },
                    { 57239, "Dungeon ni Deai wo Motomeru no wa Machigatteiru Darou ka was published in English as Is It Wrong to Try to Pick Up Girls in a Dungeon? by Yen Press from May 19, 2015 to January 22, 2019. It has been licensed in Spanish by Norma Editorial.", 89, new DateTime(2018, 9, 20, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/121555.jpg", 2347, 7.59m, new DateTime(2013, 8, 1, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 1, "The huge labyrinth city, Orario, is the gateway to the huge underground maze commonly known as the \"Dungeon.\" Its strange name causes excitement, a place to gain honor, and maybe even a romance with a pretty girl. A place where people hold their breath, hoping to gain all they wish for, a place where a solitary young man meets a little \"god\"...\n\nThe fated meeting of a boy who wants to become an adventurer, and the failed god who doesn't even have a single follower.\n\n(Source: Baka-Tsuki)", "Dungeon ni Deai wo Motomeru no wa Machigatteiru Darou ka", "Is It Wrong to Try to Pick Up Girls in a Dungeon?", "ダンジョンに出会いを求めるのは間違っているだろうか", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/57239/Dungeon_ni_Deai_wo_Motomeru_no_wa_Machigatteiru_Darou_ka", 10 },
                    { 57249, "", 86, new DateTime(2022, 4, 4, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/5/124315.jpg", 1141, 7.85m, new DateTime(2013, 12, 23, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Set 300 years after Utakata ni Warau, and 300 years before Donten ni Warau, during the turbulent Sengoku period, it is the story of a young man named Ishida Sakichi, whose mission leads him to encounter a pair of mysterious twins at the Kumo Shrine.", "Rengoku ni Warau", null, "煉獄に笑う", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/57249/Rengoku_ni_Warau", 14 },
                    { 57765, "UQ Holder! was published in English by Kodansha Comics USA from March 18, 2014 to March 21, 2023, and in Brazilian Portuguese by Jbc since April 2016.", 193, new DateTime(2022, 2, 8, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/112577.jpg", 3230, 7.46m, new DateTime(2013, 8, 27, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Twelve-year-old Touta Konoe has spent his whole life in a rural town. He dreams of one day going to the capital, where there is a tower that reaches into space. To fulfill his dream, he has been tasked to defeat his teacher and caretaker, Yukihime, who will then permit him to go to the capital.\n\nTouta's life turns upside down when a bounty hunter arrives to claim a prize on Yukihime's head. In a desperate attempt to save both his mentor and friends, Touta follows Yukihime's instruction to drink her blood, turning him into an immortal monster capable of defeating the bounty hunter.\n\nYukihime reveals herself to be Evangeline Athanasia Katherine McDowell, a centuries-old vampire. With her identity now exposed, she and Touta flee to the capital and embark on an exciting adventure that will change both of their lives forever.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "UQ Holder!", "UQ Holder!", "UQ HOLDER!", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/57765/UQ_Holder", 28 },
                    { 57897, "", 36, new DateTime(2015, 11, 18, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/167756.jpg", 1478, 7.75m, new DateTime(2012, 11, 18, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "After finally defeating Dr. Hell, Kabuto Kouji has to battle the forces of the Mikene Empire. Against an enemy unknown even to Minerva X, who has seen countless alternate timelines, Mazinger Z faces his most desperate moments!", "Shin Mazinger Zero vs Ankoku Daishougun", null, "真マジンガーZERO vs 暗黒大将軍", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/57897/Shin_Mazinger_Zero_vs_Ankoku_Daishougun", 8 },
                    { 57927, "", 102, new DateTime(2020, 4, 2, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/167812.jpg", 8976, 6.99m, new DateTime(2013, 4, 18, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A spin-off of Ao no Exorcist, following Okumura Yukio as the main protoganist.", "Salaryman Exorcist: Okumura Yukio no Aishuu", null, "サラリーマン祓魔師〈エクソシスト〉 奥村雪男の哀愁", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/57927/Salaryman_Exorcist__Okumura_Yukio_no_Aishuu", 4 },
                    { 58193, "", 2, new DateTime(2013, 9, 12, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/100739.jpg", 13320, 6.7m, new DateTime(2013, 9, 1, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Crossover between Ore Monogatari!! and Nisekoi series.", "Ore Koi!!", null, "俺コイ!! 俺物語×ニセコイ!!", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/58193/Ore_Koi", null },
                    { 58217, "", 39, new DateTime(2014, 1, 24, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/100809.jpg", 42954, null, new DateTime(2010, 10, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Remake of original manga. Set two years after the end of Cat's Eye, the story focuses on Ai, the youngest of the three sisters.", "Cat's♥Eye", null, "キャッツ♥愛", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/58217/Cats♥Eye", 8 },
                    { 58391, "Kill la Kill was published in English by Udon Entertainment from October 15, 2015, to September 20, 2016. It was also released in Spanish by Editorial Ivrea from December 18, 2015, to February 19, 2016; and in Brazilian Portuguese by Editora JBC from July 2015 to September 2015.", 17, new DateTime(2015, 2, 3, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/108467.jpg", 11964, 6.79m, new DateTime(2013, 10, 3, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The story centers around two fiercely fighting schoolgirls, Ryuuko Matoi and Satsuki Kiryuuin. On a campus ruled by force, a transfer student wielding a Basami sword brings about upheaval.\n\n(Source: ANN)", "Kill la Kill", "KILL la KILL", "キルラキル", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/58391/Kill_la_Kill", 3 },
                    { 60553, "Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku wo! was published in English as Konosuba: God's Blessing on This Wonderful World! by Yen Press under the Yen On imprint from February 21, 2017 to August 2, 2022.", 127, new DateTime(2020, 4, 30, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/174932.jpg", 93, 8.6m, new DateTime(2013, 9, 30, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Kazuma Satou lives a laughable and pathetic life, being a shut-in NEET with no distinguishable qualities other than an addiction to video games. On his way home, Kazuma dies trying to save a girl from an oncoming truck—or so he believes. In reality, the \"truck\" was a slow-moving tractor, and he merely died from shock.\n\nWaking up in limbo between death and heaven, Kazuma finds himself facing the arrogant goddess Aqua. Here, he must choose between two options: go on to heaven or be sent to a fantasy world that needs his help to defeat the Demon King. Initially unimpressed by the challenging prospect of fighting a Demon King, Kazuma changes his mind after Aqua tells him he can bring any one item he wants. What better choice does Kazuma have than the goddess standing before him?\n\nUnfortunately, after the two arrive in their new world, two things become clear: Aqua is useless beyond belief, and life in this fantasy realm will be anything but smooth sailing. From paying for food and accommodations to trying to learn new skills, the duo's problems are just starting to take shape—and the arrival of eccentric allies may only make things worse.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku wo!", "Konosuba: God's Blessing on This Wonderful World!", "この素晴らしい世界に祝福を！", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/60553/Kono_Subarashii_Sekai_ni_Shukufuku_wo", 17 },
                    { 60593, "", 1, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/4/148041.jpg", 13306, 6.71m, new DateTime(2013, 4, 9, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The story is set at the end of the Fairy Dance Arc after Kirigaya Kazuto (Kirito) enrolled to the SAO Survivor School and features an episode involving a bike he received as a celebration gift for the occasion. \n\n(Source: Sword Art Online Wiki)", "Sword Art Online: Celeste no Yousei", null, "ソードアート・オンライン チェレステの妖精", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/60593/Sword_Art_Online__Celeste_no_Yousei", null },
                    { 60973, "", 32, new DateTime(2016, 5, 17, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/120979.jpg", 1389, 7.78m, new DateTime(2013, 10, 17, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Manga adaptation of the 2nd arc of the Mahouka Koukou no Rettousei series.\n\nThere are currently nine magic high schools affiliated with the National University of Magic throughout the country. In an effort to address the current limitations, magic high schools are trained to the highest degree, while they are trying to increase the limited pool of instructors.\n\nFor that purpose, a measure was put in place so as to fuel the student's aspirations through competitions between the 9 magic schools. The largest of these is the summer Nine Schools Competition. It is a nationwide magic high school magic tournament.\n\nEvery year a selection of magic high school students from across the country meet, putting their pride on the line, and unfold a story of frustration and glory. With a huge crowd including not only government officials and those interested in magic but also businesses, overseas companies, researchers and scouts, this is the greatest stage for magic high school students to shine.\n\nThis year too, the curtains of that momentous event will be raised again.", "Mahouka Koukou no Rettousei: Kyuukousen-hen", null, "魔法科高校の劣等生 九校戦編", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/60973/Mahouka_Koukou_no_Rettousei__Kyuukousen-hen", 5 },
                    { 60975, "", 24, new DateTime(2015, 9, 17, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/120977.jpg", 3546, 7.42m, new DateTime(2013, 10, 17, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Manga adaptation of the 3rd arc of the Mahouka Koukou no Rettousei series.\n\nThe Thesis Competition, an event with as much importance as the Nine School Competition. This competition has the particularity of having its competitors compete to see which one has more mastery on magic theory. However, things may not go smoothly... And \"disturbance\" may unfold...\n\n(Source: MU)", "Mahouka Koukou no Rettousei: Yokohama Souran-hen", null, "魔法科高校の劣等生 横浜騒乱編", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/60975/Mahouka_Koukou_no_Rettousei__Yokohama_Souran-hen", 5 },
                    { 60977, "", 17, new DateTime(2015, 7, 26, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/128657.jpg", 1193, 7.83m, new DateTime(2014, 2, 26, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "\"Three years ago, he had the same posture. Three years ago, he had stood behind Miyuki. Yes.... Compared to three years ago, it had changed.\"\n\nSet 3 years prior to the present time, Tsuioku-hen tells the events that would change Miyuki's world drastically, as well as the events that led Tatsuya to become what he is now.\n\n(Source: MangaHere)", "Mahouka Koukou no Rettousei: Tsuioku-hen", null, "魔法科高校の劣等生 追憶編", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/60977/Mahouka_Koukou_no_Rettousei__Tsuioku-hen", 3 },
                    { 61959, "Kishibe Rohan wa Ugokanai has been published in English as Thus Spoke Rohan Kishibe by VIZ Media under the Shonen Jump imprint since September 27, 2022. The series has been adapted into a live-action TV series since December 28, 2020.", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/210302.jpg", 1221, 7.82m, new DateTime(1997, 6, 23, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "The spin-off focusing on Kishibe Rohan, an eccentric mangaka with the ability to read people's memories, an ability called \"Heaven's Door.\" He seeks out the supernatural to see for himself what his mysterious ability is all about.\n\nVolume 1\n1. Episode #16: Zangeshitsu (At a Confessional)\n2. Episode #02: Mutsukabezaka (Mutsukabe Hill)\n3. Episode #05: Fugou Mura (Millionaire Village)\n4. Episode #06: Mitsuryou Kaigan (Poaching Seashore)\n5. Kishibe Rohan Gucci e Iku (Rohan Goes to Gucci)\n\nVolume 2\n1. Episode #04: Mochizuki-ke no Otsukimi (The Harvest Moon)\n2. Episode #07: Getsuyoubi: Tenki - Ame (A Rainy Monday)\n3. Episode #08: D.N.A\n4. Episode #09: The Run", "Kishibe Rohan wa Ugokanai", "Thus Spoke Rohan Kishibe", "岸辺露伴は動かない", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/61959/Kishibe_Rohan_wa_Ugokanai", null },
                    { 62083, "", 51, new DateTime(2018, 4, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/150334.jpg", 867, 7.94m, new DateTime(2013, 8, 23, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Spin-off of the SaeKano novel series focusing on the unlikely relationship between famed author Kasumigaoka Utaha and average otaku Aki Tomoya.\n\nDown in a rut and out of lacking creativity, infatuation develops after a fan-signing for 'Love Metronome' and Aki becomes the estranged \"assistant\" of one of his school's top idols.\n\n(Source: fourberie)", "Saenai Heroine no Sodatekata: Koisuru Metronome", null, "冴えない彼女〈ヒロイン〉の育てかた 恋するメトロノーム", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/62083/Saenai_Heroine_no_Sodatekata__Koisuru_Metronome", 10 },
                    { 62393, "", 1, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/109759.jpg", 10455, 6.89m, new DateTime(2013, 12, 19, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Oneshot crossover between Yankee-kun to Megane-chan and Yamada-kun to 7-nin no Majo.", "Yankee-kun na Yamada-kun to Megane-chan to Majo", null, "ヤンキー君な山田くんとメガネちゃんと魔女", 3, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/62393/Yankee-kun_na_Yamada-kun_to_Megane-chan_to_Majo", null },
                    { 62671, "Gekijouban Mahou Shoujo Madoka★Magica: Shinpen - Hangyaku no Monogatari was published in English as Puella Magi Madoka Magica: The Movie -Rebellion- by Yen Press from December 15, 2015, to February 23, 2016. The series was also published as a 3-in-1 omnibus on August 22, 2023. It was released in Brazilian Portuguese by NewPOP Editora.", 9, new DateTime(2014, 1, 9, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/107535.jpg", 616, 8.08m, new DateTime(2013, 11, 11, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "With a single, hopeful wish, young women can become magical girls and take on the thankless task of getting rid of the hidden chaos of the world. Despite this, the magical girls of Mitakihara are enjoying themselves, leading normal middle school lives by day and working together as a brilliant magical girl team by night.\n\nAnd yet... was the world always this way? Were the battles of magical girls supposed to be like this? These are the thoughts of Homura Akemi, a very shy girl who has recently transferred schools and became a member of the Mitakihara magical girls. The seemingly perfect lives that she and her friends lead has caused Homura to start doubting and observing the world. And as she slowly isolates herself from the group to explore the world in secret, she finds that things are not what they seem—after all, one of these girls shouldn't even exist...\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Gekijouban Mahou Shoujo Madoka★Magica: Shinpen - Hangyaku no Monogatari", "Puella Magi Madoka★Magica: The Movie - Rebellion", "劇場版 魔法少女まどか★マギカ [新編] 叛逆の物語", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/62671/Gekijouban_Mahou_Shoujo_Madoka★Magica__Shinpen_-_Hangyaku_no_Monogatari", 3 },
                    { 62673, "Mahou Shoujo Suzune★Magica was published in English as Puella Magi Suzune Magica by Yen Press from September 22, 2015, to May 24, 2016. It was also released in Brazilian Portuguese by NewPOP Editora from February 2018 to April 2018.", 16, new DateTime(2014, 11, 21, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/107537.jpg", 12586, 6.75m, new DateTime(2013, 11, 11, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "There is a macabre story circulating throughout the halls of Akanegasaki Middle School: unsuspecting teenage girls will hear the sound of a bell when they are walking alone at night, and suddenly, a woman in a long coat will appear. Known as the Ripper, the story goes that she will ask their name and then stab them repeatedly after they answer.\n\nHaruka Kanade, Arisa Narumi, Chisato Shion, and Matsuri Hinata have all heard the rumors, but they know full well that the stories stem from actual murders taking place in a neighboring city. And unlike most, the girls feel confident that they can do something to stop it, as each of them have contracted with a cat-like creature named Kyuubey to become magical girls. As they are patrolling one night, they stumble upon the so-called Ripper but are left shaken by the encounter—after all, the killer is also a magical girl.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Mahou Shoujo Suzune★Magica", "Puella Magi Suzune★Magica", "魔法少女すずね★マギカ", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/62673/Mahou_Shoujo_Suzune★Magica", 3 },
                    { 62687, "", 16, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/107561.jpg", 43432, null, new DateTime(2011, 12, 26, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The first volume features different stories about the original cast's training sessions and special techniques. It fills in gaps that were never explained before and offers a new point of view about some in-game scenes.\n\nThe second volume recreates the world seen in the videogame \"Inazuma Eleven Strikers\" for Wii, from the point of view of Inazuma Japan. It features many characters from every season and situations only seen in said game.", "Inazuma Eleven: Baku Gaidenshuu", null, "イナズマイレブン 爆外伝集", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/62687/Inazuma_Eleven__Baku_Gaidenshuu", 2 },
                    { 63329, "", 27, new DateTime(2017, 2, 8, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/108457.jpg", 10687, 6.88m, new DateTime(2012, 6, 7, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Peace has settled in Mitakihara City, beginning a new era where magical girls and \"witches\" coexist. While they are no longer in constant peril, the magical girls at Mitakihara Middle School now face an equally troubling problem: experiencing a fulfilling youth!\n\nWanting to create a place where everyone can gather, Mami Tomoe suggests to Madoka Kaname and Sayaka Miki that they start a magical girl club. Joined by the eager Homura Akemi, the preliminary arrangements progress smoothly until the Student Council, led by Kyuubey and its cohorts, announces that their application has been rejected. The committee's demands push the girls to continue their efforts to establish the club—a venture that will lead them into absurd conflicts and rowdy quarrels with their schoolmates and even each other!\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Mahou Shoujo-bu Madoka★Magica", null, "魔法少女部まどか★マギカ", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/63329/Mahou_Shoujo-bu_Madoka★Magica", 3 },
                    { 63545, "Bikachou Shinshi Kaikoroku was simulpub in English as Memoirs of Amorous Gentlemen by Crunchyroll. It was also published digitally by Cork.", 16, new DateTime(2018, 3, 7, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/164764.jpg", 4963, 7.28m, new DateTime(2013, 11, 7, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Perverts are people who know the shape of their desires. They have carefully traced those contours like a blind man using both hands to measure the shape of a vase. Colette works in a brothel in early 20th century Paris, an occupation she can't escape. She and the other girls support each other, satisfying the desires of their clients, day in, day out. The one source of hope in her difficult life was her trysts with Leon. But Colette could never be sure if Leon really loved her... The strength of women in their pleasurable confines; the naked desires of the 'amorous gentlemen.' Welcome to a beautiful, bewitching bordello of love and desire...\n\n(Source: Crunchyroll)", "Bikachou Shinshi Kaikoroku", "Memoirs of Amorous Gentlemen", "鼻下長紳士回顧録", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/63545/Bikachou_Shinshi_Kaikoroku", 2 },
                    { 63547, "", 9, new DateTime(2013, 10, 14, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/169025.jpg", 43543, null, new DateTime(2013, 3, 14, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Year 2055, 4 years after the events in Danball Senki W. LBXs have become the world's largest hobby, big enough for pro leagues to be established, and people to make their entire living off being an LBX player. 14-year-old Arata is a new transfer student at Kamui Daimon Integrated Academy on Kamui Island, near Japan. Known to be the most prestigious institution in the world for raising LBX players and mechanics, entrance to the academy requires an extremely competitive hurdle of being the champion of at least 3 official tournaments. Along with other members of his platoon, they face rivals and delve into the secrets lurking within the academy.\n\n(Source: ANN)", "Danball Senki Wars", null, "ダンボール戦機WARS", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/63547/Danball_Senki_Wars", 2 },
                    { 64565, "", 1, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/110375.jpg", 15505, 6.54m, new DateTime(2013, 12, 24, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Hiro Mashima of Fairy Tail and Nakaba Suzuki of Nanatsu no Taizai team up for a special Christmas story, based on each other's work: Meliodas, Elizabeth Liones, and Hawk are visiting the city of Magnolia for Christmas, and Meliodas' offer to buy a present for Elizabeth goes awry. Upon returning from a job, Natsu Dragneel and Happy spot a suspicious visitor on the roof of their guild, which leads to an odd confrontation.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Fairy Tail x Nanatsu no Taizai Christmas Special", null, "『FAIRY TAIL』＆『七つの大罪』合作漫画", 3, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/64565/Fairy_Tail_x_Nanatsu_no_Taizai_Christmas_Special", null },
                    { 64849, "", 1, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/110761.jpg", 18872, 6.1m, new DateTime(2009, 2, 19, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Side story of Get Backers created two years after the conclusion of the main series.", "GetBackers Bangai-hen", null, "GetBackers -奪還屋- 番外編", 3, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/64849/GetBackers_Bangai-hen", null },
                    { 65051, "", 12, new DateTime(2015, 4, 2, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/111109.jpg", 5427, 7.24m, new DateTime(2013, 6, 3, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A spin-off of the Nisekoi manga series comprised of short stories.", "Nisekoi: Urabana", null, "ニセコイ ウラバナ", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/65051/Nisekoi__Urabana", 3 },
                    { 65169, "", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/186509.jpg", 43743, null, new DateTime(2013, 12, 18, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "The Mythology is the plan of the gods. A perfect story created by them, that should never be changed in any way. However, there where mortals who altered the Mythology with their own hands. Pegasus Seiya, Ryuji Takane, Kojiro of the Fuuma, and many others were brought to this prison, where they're going to be erased to restore the Mythology to its original course... But they're not going to disappear without fighting for their existence.", "Kurumada Suikoden: Hero of Heroes", null, "車田水滸伝～HERO OF HEROES～", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/65169/Kurumada_Suikoden__Hero_of_Heroes", null },
                    { 65499, "", 54, new DateTime(2011, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/112305.jpg", 43766, null, new DateTime(2009, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The main character, Endou Mamoru, is a very talented goalkeeper and the grandson of one of the strongest goalkeepers in Japan, who died before he was born. Even though his skills are incredible his school lacks a real soccer club as the 6 other members don't appear very interested even in training. But as soon as a mysterious forward called Gouenji moves to Endou's town, the young goalkeeper sets out to find and recruit members for his soccer team.\n\n(Source: Wikipedia)", "Inazuma Eleven: Special", null, "イナズマイレブンSPECIAL", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/65499/Inazuma_Eleven__Special", 3 },
                    { 65643, "Area no Kishi Gaiden: Enokou Early Days was simultaneously published in Japanese, Chinese and English (as The Knight in the Area) on DeNA's Manga Box app.", 7, new DateTime(2014, 8, 27, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/137945.jpg", 13019, 6.72m, new DateTime(2013, 12, 4, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Their pass work has become splendid! The captain observes the field! In the ever-popular Enoshima soccer manga, \"The Knight in the Area,\" serialized in Weekly Shonen Magazine, Iwaki Teppei progresses from being a young soccer coach to a professional soccer player. The story from his high school days is about to unfold! How did this young soccer boy evolve into a genius midfielder?! The long awaited spin off of the number one selling soccer manga is here!!\n\n(Source: MangaBox)", "Area no Kishi Gaiden: Enokou Early Days", "The Knight in the Area", "エリアの騎士 外伝 ～江ノ高アーリーデイズ～", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/65643/Area_no_Kishi_Gaiden__Enokou_Early_Days", 1 },
                    { 65669, "Takato Shounen no Jikenbo was simultaneously published in Japanese, Chinese and English (as Kindaichi Case Files: Takato's Side) on DeNA's Manga Box app and ran for 16 chapters. When the published volume was released, these chapters were compiled together into 7 chapters.", 7, new DateTime(2014, 4, 1, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/125799.jpg", 12240, 6.78m, new DateTime(2013, 12, 3, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The son of a genius magician, Yoichi Takato has been something of a polymath ever since his high school days. However, his high school days are marked by boredom and an inability to open his heart to others. When he happens to join the magic club, he meets with friends whom he can finally open his heart to. But then, the curtain rises on a terrifying murder show! A spinoff story with Hajime Kindaichi’s nemesis from \"Kindaichi Case Files\", \"the hellish puppet master\" Yoichi Takato must solve this murder case, even though he is still in high school!!\n\n(Source: MangaBox)", "Takato Shounen no Jikenbo", "Kindaichi Case Files: Takato's Side", "高遠少年の事件簿", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/65669/Takato_Shounen_no_Jikenbo", 1 },
                    { 65685, "Real Account was published in English by Kodansha Comics USA from March 22, 2016 to August 29, 2023. It has also been published in French by Kurokawa.", 194, new DateTime(2019, 11, 8, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/147381.jpg", 7925, 7.06m, new DateTime(2014, 1, 8, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Real Account is a popular social media app that enables its users to link their account to reality. From socializing to buying things in real life, the app has become indispensable in daily life, especially for second-year high school student Ataru Kashigawa. He uses Real Account as a means to escape reality and he feels a sense of belonging and connection to his followers, whom he considers as his friends.\n\nHowever, Ataru's views on friendship drastically change when he gets plunged into the virtual world of Real Account and is forced to participate in horrific death games alongside ten thousand other users. But these are far from ordinary online death games as dying in the world of Real Account means that you and all your followers die in reality. To make matters worse, having no followers also means certain death. As Aratu begins to participate in these death games, he discovers the existence of Yuuma Mukai, a teenager who looks just like him. This discovery creates a twist in events.\n\nBetrayed by his so-called friends one by one, Ataru is left with one anonymous follower. In this virtual world where a single follower could be the difference between life or death, Ataru must survive and complete these games in order to return to the real world.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Real Account", "Real Account", "リアルアカウント", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/65685/Real_Account", 24 },
                    { 65869, null, 16, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/112993.jpg", 43821, null, new DateTime(1998, 2, 28, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, null, "Kaze no Yukue - Shin Kidou Senki Gundam W Parody Kyousakushuu", null, "風の行方 新機動戦記ガンダムW パロディ競作集", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/65869/Kaze_no_Yukue_-_Shin_Kidou_Senki_Gundam_W_Parody_Kyousakushuu", 1 },
                    { 65909, "Mahou Shoujo Oriko★Magica: Betsu-hen was published in English as Puella Magi Oriko Magica: Extra Story by Yen Press on March 24, 2015. It was also released in Brazilian Portuguese by NewPOP Editora in June 2015.", 6, new DateTime(2013, 6, 9, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/115727.jpg", 13114, 6.72m, new DateTime(2012, 8, 8, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "1. Noisy Citrine\n2. Symmetry Diamond\n3. The Last Agate", "Mahou Shoujo Oriko★Magica: Betsu-hen", "Puella Magi Oriko★Magica: Extra Story", "魔法少女おりこ★マギカ [別編]", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/65909/Mahou_Shoujo_Oriko★Magica__Betsu-hen", 1 },
                    { 66025, "", 2, new DateTime(2008, 1, 27, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/113233.jpg", 9323, 6.96m, new DateTime(2006, 11, 27, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Story showing what happend some time after the events in the last chapter.\n\nNote: On hiatus.", "Hachimitsu to Clover Spin-off", null, "ハチミツとクローバー スピンオフ", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/66025/Hachimitsu_to_Clover_Spin-off", null },
                    { 66161, null, 30, new DateTime(2014, 2, 3, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/201121.jpg", 14006, 6.66m, new DateTime(2012, 4, 12, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, null, "Cyborg 009 Kanketsu-hen: Conclusion God's War", null, "サイボーグ009完結編 conclusion GOD'S WAR", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/66161/Cyborg_009_Kanketsu-hen__Conclusion_Gods_War", 5 },
                    { 66433, "Dungeon ni Deai wo Motomeru no wa Machigatteiru Darou ka Gaiden: Sword Oratoria has been published in English as Is It Wrong to Try to Pick Up Girls in a Dungeon? On the Side: Sword Oratoria by Yen Press under the Yen On imprint since November 1, 2016.", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/121553.jpg", 928, 7.92m, new DateTime(2014, 1, 14, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "Aiz Wallenstein, the Sword Princess, is known as one of the most powerful warriors from one of the most powerful groups in the city of Orario: Loki Familia. With them, she ventures into the deepest parts of the labyrinthine Dungeon beneath the city, stalking the monstrous denizens that lurk there and vanquishing them with the blazing light of her sword. But when she meets a certain white-haired boy, the encounter will change both of them forever...\n\n(Source: Yen Press)", "Dungeon ni Deai wo Motomeru no wa Machigatteiru Darou ka Gaiden: Sword Oratoria", "Is It Wrong to Try to Pick Up Girls in a Dungeon? On the Side: Sword Oratoria", "ダンジョンに出会いを求めるのは間違っているだろうか外伝 ソード・オラトリア", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/66433/Dungeon_ni_Deai_wo_Motomeru_no_wa_Machigatteiru_Darou_ka_Gaiden__Sword_Oratoria", null },
                    { 66685, "Kekkon Yubiwa Monogatari was published digitally in English as Tales of Wedding Rings by Crunchyroll since June 1, 2015, and by Square Enix through Manga UP! The volumes have been published by Yen Press since March 6, 2018.", 86, new DateTime(2024, 8, 22, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/188970.jpg", 7925, 7.06m, new DateTime(2014, 3, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "When Satou's best friend, Hime, tells him that she's moving, he decides to follow. After crashing her wedding in another world, he ends up as the groom when she suddenly kisses him! Prophecy states that her husband is destined to be the Ring King-a hero of immense power who will save the world from the Abyssal King! Is Satou up for the challenge, or is his new marriage going to end before it even begins?\n\n(Source: Yen Press)", "Kekkon Yubiwa Monogatari", "Tales of Wedding Rings", "結婚指輪物語", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/66685/Kekkon_Yubiwa_Monogatari", 15 },
                    { 66695, "", 3, new DateTime(2014, 7, 22, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/114245.jpg", 17450, 6.36m, new DateTime(2014, 1, 30, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Nadeko Sengoku is an average, carefree middle school student. On the road to school one day, she runs into Ran Hokkyokusei, who she soon finds out is a new transfer student. When Ran tries to flirt with Nadeko, he is intercepted by Sui, her childhood friend, who claims that Nadeko belongs to him.\n\nKimi to Nadekko! revolves around Nadeko and the two boys as their rivalry and determination to make Nadeko’s heart sway toward them intensifies.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Kimi to Nadekko!", null, "キミとなでっこ！", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/66695/Kimi_to_Nadekko", 1 },
                    { 66809, "", 32, new DateTime(2014, 9, 7, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/126881.jpg", 11773, 6.81m, new DateTime(2014, 2, 9, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Supernatural creatures live alongside humans, but these \"rares\" are being hunted to extinction over time. An organization is being formed to protect these rares, and allow them to live their lives as they like. The starting members of this organization are few; there's the masked Fukumen, the Black Vampyr king AxL, and they are soon joined by the sweet-voiced mermaid Mirror. Together, they will protect the rares from the deadly hunters!\n\n(Source: MangaHelpers)\n\nIncluded one-shots:\nVolume 4: Dark Pawn: Yami no Shichiya, Tsukumogami, Nurarihyon no Mago Gaiden", "Illegal Rare", null, "ILLEGAL RARE", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/66809/Illegal_Rare", 4 },
                    { 66879, "Yuri Kuma Arashi was published in English as Yuri Bear Storm by Tokyopop under the Love x Love imprint from January 22, 2019 to March 12, 2019.", 27, new DateTime(2016, 4, 29, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/147723.jpg", 8240, 7.03m, new DateTime(2014, 2, 27, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Some time ago, the asteroid Kumaria exploded in the depths of space.\n\nThe resulting fragments became a meteor shower that rained down on Earth, and for some reason, bears all over the world rose up and attacked humanity! In \"Man vs. Bear,\" the bears ate the humans and the humans shot the bears, resulting in a seemingly unending battle and a cycle of hatred. In the end, a giant \"Wall of Extinction\" was erected between the humans and bears and a state of mutual nonaggression came to pass...\n\nThe human world.\n\nOne morning, Arashigaoka Academy students Kureha Tsubaki and Sumika Izumino were by themselves and saw the \"Yuri Flower\" that bloomed in a flower bed. The two are friends as well as lovers. The flower bed is an important place to the two. At that moment, the Bear Alarms ring out! The bears are invading the human world, and humans are being attacked! Are they really those bears? One mystery invokes yet another mystery, one after another...\n\n(Source: ANN)", "Yuri Kuma Arashi", "Yuri Bear Storm", "ユリ熊嵐", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/66879/Yuri_Kuma_Arashi", 3 },
                    { 67019, "Fuuka was simulpub in English by Crunchyroll since April 15, 2014. The series was published digitally by Kodansha USA from November 3, 2015 to January 8, 2019.", 204, new DateTime(2018, 4, 3, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/186209.jpg", 3473, 7.43m, new DateTime(2014, 2, 11, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The story follows the life of Yuu Haruna, who recently moved into Tokyo with his sisters after their father is forced to transfer overseas on work.\n\nOn his way to buy dinner while looking at his Twitter account, a high school girl suddenly crashes into him. Thinking he was taking upskirt pictures of her, the girl takes Yuu's phone, breaks it, and slaps him before leaving Yuu lying on the ground. As it turns out, this girl—Fuuka Akitsuki—also goes to the school Yuu is transferring to.\n\nUnlike most people, Fuuka doesn't own a cellphone; she even listens to music using a CD player. Eventually these two become closer, and decide to form a band with their friends and enter the professional world of music. With Fuuka around, what will now become of Yuu's new life in Tokyo?\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Fuuka", "Fuuka", "風夏", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/67019/Fuuka", 20 },
                    { 67297, "Saint Seiya Episode G: Assassin began serialization in Champion RED Ichigo. It moved to Champion Cross in October 2014, and then to Manga Cross in July 2018.", 123, new DateTime(2019, 8, 26, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/187408.jpg", 7648, 7.08m, new DateTime(2014, 4, 4, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "This story starts after events in Episode G.", "Saint Seiya Episode G: Assassin", null, "聖闘士星矢 EPISODE.G アサシン", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/67297/Saint_Seiya_Episode_G__Assassin", 16 },
                    { 67545, "Isobe Isobee Monogatari was initially published as a one-shot manga in Shounen Jump in the 26th and 27th issues of 2013 to fill in a slot temporarily vacated by One Piece at that time; however, due to the tremendous amount of positive feedback it received, the manga got serialized. Starting from the 11th issue of 2015, the series was placed at the end of the magazine and no longer participated in Shounen Jump's ranking system.", 303, new DateTime(2017, 11, 23, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/115627.jpg", 7927, 7.06m, new DateTime(2013, 5, 26, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "In this ukiyoe-style manga, Isobe Isobee is a lazy, slacker samurai with big dreams. He lives with his mother, who thinks highly of him. He lays around the house, sneakily looks at Edo-period pornography without his mother noticing, naps at school... but he plans to become a respectable samurai one day!\n\n(Source: MangaHelpers)", "Isobe Isobee Monogatari: Ukiyo wa Tsurai yo", null, "磯部磯兵衛物語 〜浮世はつらいよ〜", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/67545/Isobe_Isobee_Monogatari__Ukiyo_wa_Tsurai_yo", 16 },
                    { 67615, "Tate no Yuusha no Nariagari has been published in English as The Rising of the Shield Hero by One Peace Books since November 17, 2015 and in Russian by XL Media since February 16, 2016.", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/130759.jpg", 1488, 7.75m, new DateTime(2014, 2, 4, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "Twenty-year-old otaku Naofumi Iwatani is mysteriously transported to the otherworldly kingdom of Melromarc. Appearing before the King, Naofumi and three other summoned individuals learn that they are each one of the Four Cardinal Heroes who are tasked with defeating the malicious \"Waves of Catastrophe.\" \n\nHowever, Naofumi is given only a measly shield and dubbed the \"Shield Hero,\" the weakest of the Four Cardinal Heroes. Owing to his lack of power, none of the kingdom's mercenaries wish to aid him, except for the country's beautiful princess, Malty Melromarc. But Naofumi soon awakens the next day to find himself robbed of all his possessions and falsely accused of rape by Malty. \n\nDue to his status as a Cardinal Hero, Naofumi is not executed, but instead, his erroneous crimes are made public. Struggling to find hospitality, Naofumi buys a demi-human slave girl named Raphtalia to aid his endeavors, and embarks on a perilous journey to deliver retribution to those who ruined him, learning the secrets of this new world along the way.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Tate no Yuusha no Nariagari", "The Rising of the Shield Hero", "盾の勇者の成り上がり", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/67615/Tate_no_Yuusha_no_Nariagari", null },
                    { 67617, "Tate no Yuusha no Nariagari began as a web novel on Shousetsuka ni Narou on October 29, 2012 and completed with 378 web chapters on May 28, 2015. Media Factory began releasing a revised and illustrated version of the series on August 22, 2013 under its MF Books label. Both the development and pacing of the light novel are significantly different from the web novel, with expanded content and altered events. One Peace Books has been publishing Tate no Yuusha no Nariagari in English as The Rising of the Shield Hero since September 15, 2015.", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/115755.jpg", 911, 7.92m, new DateTime(2013, 8, 21, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "Stories of old tell of four otherworldly heroes—wielding the sword, spear, bow, and shield—who defended the land from wave after wave of calamity. With the fate of the world in balance, the kingdom of Melromarc summons these legendary figures; in modern-day Japan, the call is answered, and the unwitting heroes are transported to this fantasy universe.\n\nThrust into Melromarc and given the title of \"Shield Hero,\" otaku Naofumi Iwatani is labeled the weakest due to his lack of offensive capability and apparent inexperience. When the heroes part ways to start their journeys, he only has one willing companion: the beautiful princess Malty Melromarc. However, she soon betrays him, steals all his money, and accuses him of taking advantage of her.\n\nFor his alleged crimes, Naofumi is branded a criminal and made outcast of society. With hatred filling his heart, he sets out alone, vowing vengeance against those who wronged him.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Tate no Yuusha no Nariagari", "The Rising of the Shield Hero", "盾の勇者の成り上がり", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/67617/Tate_no_Yuusha_no_Nariagari", null },
                    { 68273, "Shinmai Maou no Testament: Arashi has been published in English as The Testament of Sister New Devil STORM! by Seven Seas Entertainment since September 26, 2017.", 30, new DateTime(2016, 5, 5, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/147721.jpg", 10624, 6.88m, new DateTime(2014, 2, 6, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "High school student Toujo Basara's life has taken a turn for the strange. Although hesitant about his father's sudden decision to remarry, he can't deny it comes with a couple perks—drop-dead gorgeous step-sisters...who also happen to be members of a demon clan! Mio Naruse is a Demon Lord and Maria Naruse her succubus servant. Chaos and passionate antics ensue as Basara gets acquainted with his new demonic siblings, trying to protect them from dangerous demon rivals and struggling to keep up with their lusty, devilish appetites.\n\n(Source: Seven Seas Entertainment)", "Shinmai Maou no Testament: Arashi", "The Testament of Sister New Devil: Storm!", "新妹魔王の契約者〈テスタメント〉・嵐！", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/68273/Shinmai_Maou_no_Testament__Arashi", 5 },
                    { 68707, "", 107, new DateTime(2023, 3, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/117433.jpg", 4609, 7.31m, new DateTime(2013, 6, 25, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The manga adaptation of Gundam 0083. Years after the One Year War ended, in hopes of resurrecting the Principality of Zeon forces, Anavel Gato (also known as the \"Nightmare of Solomon\") steals a Gundam Unit 02 from the Earth Federation Forces. In the heat of battle Kou Uraki enters Unit 01 to confront Gato.\n\n(Source: Dan of Population GO)", "Kidou Senshi Gundam 0083: Rebellion", null, "機動戦士ガンダム0083 REBELLION", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/68707/Kidou_Senshi_Gundam_0083__Rebellion", 18 },
                    { 68983, "", 4, new DateTime(1998, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/118069.jpg", 44134, null, new DateTime(1997, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "U.C. 0093 - Char Aznable, the infamous \"Red Comet\" of the One Year War, has come out of hiding to lead the Neo-Zeon Army and wage war against the Earth Federation. Only his greatest rival, Gundam pilot Amuro Ray, can stop him from dropping the Axis asteroid on Earth and causing a major global catastrophe.\n\n(Source: ANN)", "Kidou Senshi Gundam: Gyakushuu no Char", null, "機動戦士ガンダム 逆襲のシャア", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/68983/Kidou_Senshi_Gundam__Gyakushuu_no_Char", 1 },
                    { 69047, "Ochibi-san has been published digitally in English as The Diary of Ochibi by Cork.", null, new DateTime(2019, 12, 15, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/118155.jpg", 44141, null, new DateTime(2007, 3, 31, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "\"I can help you laugh, but I can't take away the tears you've shed.\" In Mametsubu-cho, a town somewhere in the ancient Japanese city of Kamakura, Ochibi-san lives a relaxed, easy life. With his friend Nazeni the dog, Jack the naughty kitten, and Pankui the hungry dog, Ochibi-san's year in Mametsubu-cho is filled with encounters and new discoveries! Flower-viewing in spring, swimming in summer, collecting leaves in fall, and eating yummy food in winter.\n\n(Source: Crunchyroll)", "Ochibi-san", "The Diary of Ochibi", "オチビサン", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/69047/Ochibi-san", 10 },
                    { 69073, "Durarara!! SH was published in English by Yen Press under its Yen On imprint from May 25, 2021 to August 23, 2022.", null, new DateTime(2016, 2, 9, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/119931.jpg", 1273, 7.81m, new DateTime(2014, 4, 9, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 3, "In the densely populated district of Ikebukuro, \"normalcy\" is nearly impossible for its residents. This is to be expected with the notorious Headless Rider haunting its winding streets. However, six months after the disbandment of the Dollars, no one has seen the infamous figure. Despite this, the city has hardly settled down, and three new figures emerge to take center stage.\n\nGrowing up in the boonies of Akita, Yahiro Mizuchi has always believed himself to be a \"monster,\" a fact only affirmed by those around him. However, spurred on by the words of a stranger, he sets out to Ikebukuro to witness the monstrous Headless Rider. Meanwhile, Kuon Kotonami is involved with nearly all the dealings going on in Ikebukuro, all with one goal—to make money. For him, the Headless Rider is one of the most lucrative markets out there. Conversely, Himeka Tatsugami wishes to avoid the notorious Rider at all costs; after all, that monster has taken far too much from her.\n\nAs new and old faces collide, the Headless Rider is at the center of it all, and—despite its absence—it continues to influence Ikebukuro, the district that never sleeps.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Durarara!! SH", "Durarara!! SH", "デュラララ!!SH", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/69073/Durarara_SH", 4 },
                    { 69371, "", null, new DateTime(2013, 4, 3, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/118865.jpg", 2026, 7.64m, new DateTime(2013, 2, 3, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Novelization of the anime.", "Psycho-Pass", null, "PSYCHO-PASS サイコパス", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/69371/Psycho-Pass", 2 },
                    { 69375, "", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/123267.jpg", 44162, null, new DateTime(2013, 4, 3, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The story covers the Specimen case three years prior to the anime.\n\nSasayama Mitsuru is an Enforcer who works at the MWPSB Unit 1, searching  the mastermind behind a case involving gruesome murders.", "Psycho-Pass Zero: Namae no Nai Kaibutsu", null, "PSYCHO-PASS 0 名前のない怪物", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/69375/Psycho-Pass_Zero__Namae_no_Nai_Kaibutsu", 1 },
                    { 69415, "", 3, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/118931.jpg", 6403, 7.16m, new DateTime(2010, 5, 16, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "This artbook contains 3 side stories that were not included in the main volumes.\n\n1. Mira-sensei no Henshin Mahou Lesson (Mira-Sensei's Transforming Magic Class)\n2. Yousei no Izumi e Youkoso! (Welcome to Fairy Fountain)\n3. Nagagutsu wo Haita Happy (Happy in Boots)\n\nAlso contains \"Fairy Megane\" (crossover one-shot between \"Fairy Tail\" and \"Yankee-kun to Megane-chan\").\n\n\nNote: Chapter count is 3 and does not include Fairy Megane. Please don't change it.", "Fairy Tail+", null, "FAIRY TAIL+", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/69415/Fairy_Tail_", null },
                    { 69503, null, 125, new DateTime(2017, 10, 17, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/203492.jpg", 4079, 7.36m, new DateTime(2013, 11, 26, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, null, "Kindaichi Shounen no Jikenbo Returns", null, "金田一少年の事件簿R（リターンズ）", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/69503/Kindaichi_Shounen_no_Jikenbo_Returns", 14 },
                    { 69765, "Durarara!!: 3 Way Standoff - Alley is an adaptation of ASCII Media Works' PlayStation Portable game, released on August 25, 2011.", 12, new DateTime(2014, 8, 21, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/119479.jpg", 7232, 7.1m, new DateTime(2013, 7, 21, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The rumors about Ikebukuro spread like wildfire, especially those regarding the dangerous color gangs and the infamous legend surrounding the Black Rider. Miyoshi Yoshimune transfers to Raira Academy due to his parents' work and quickly befriends Mikado Ryuugamine, Masaomi Kida, and Anri Sonohara—who all soon advise him to stay away from the gang members and not believe nonsensical myths for his own protection.\n\nHowever, no one is safe once they cross paths with Izaya Orihara, Shinjuku's notorious information broker. The three friends insist that Izaya is merely making jokes, but when Yoshimune runs into Izaya by himself, Izaya gives him a task: to look into the unknown people who are currently investigating the color gangs and relay the information back to him. Although Yoshimune tries to avoid Ikebukuro's underworld, Izaya's request leads him to a fateful encounter with a girl named Chiaki Igarashi, marking only the first step into uncovering Ikebukuro's biggest scheme yet.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Durarara!!: 3 Way Standoff - Alley", null, "デュラララ!! 3way standoff -alley-", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/69765/Durarara__3_Way_Standoff_-_Alley", 2 },
                    { 69903, "Fairy Tail Zerø was published in English by Kodansha Comics USA on July 12, 2016. It was also released in Spanish by Norma Editorial on October 29, 2016; and in Brazilian Portuguese by Editora JBC on October 30, 2017.", 13, new DateTime(2015, 7, 16, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/167384.jpg", 1032, 7.88m, new DateTime(2014, 7, 15, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Long before she would found Fairy Tail, first master Mavis Vermillion is left under the care of the Red Lizard guild. Abused and belittled at every opportunity, she is forced to complete difficult chores. Despite this horrific treatment, Mavis refuses to cry, for if she did, she would not be able to meet the fairies. However, her life of servitude comes to an abrupt end when the Blue Skull guild raids her home, leaving only Mavis and the guild master's daughter, Zera, alive.\n\nFor many years, Mavis and Zera live alone, taking care of each other. But this all changes when a band of treasure hunters comes to the island in search of the Tenrou Jade—a precious gem that is sacred to the island. With the arrival of new faces, her life begins to change again. Mavis has never stopped wishing to meet the fairies, and now she may finally have the chance to find them.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Fairy Tail Zerø", "Fairy Tail Zero", "FAIRY TAIL ZERØ", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/69903/Fairy_Tail_Zerø", 1 },
                    { 69941, "", 21, new DateTime(2016, 1, 24, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/173352.jpg", 10424, 6.89m, new DateTime(2014, 4, 25, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The series takes place in a private high school involving the concept of \"saviors.\" They are known as people who possess awakened memories of their past lives. The story tells of a young boy named Moroha Haimura who comes to this private school.\n\nAt the school, there are two types of people: Saviors, who fight enemies with weapons and techniques gleaned from the Puraana powers from their own bodies, and Kuroma, who wipe out enemies with magic to manipulate the Maana powers that surpass physics. Moroha Haimura is the first person with past lives of both Shirogane and Kuroma.\n\n(Source: ANN, edited)", "Seiken Tsukai no World Break", "The Swordbringer comes back.", "聖剣使いの禁呪詠唱〈ワールドブレイク〉", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/69941/Seiken_Tsukai_no_World_Break", 4 },
                    { 70117, "", 24, new DateTime(2016, 9, 23, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/149161.jpg", 10324, 6.9m, new DateTime(2014, 8, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Third in the ranking of the \"Assassin Name\" families of the underground assassin community, the \"Zerozaki Ichizoku\" is infamous for their indomitable family unity. Each of its members exhibit combat prowess when it comes to saving one of their kin. Zerozaki Kishishiki is one member of the Zerozaki family, and he utilizes a bat covered in nails to brutally murder his targets. He calls his weapon the \"Praise of Folly (Seamless Bias).\" His next target was supposed to be an ordinary target, just another day for him. He faces a problem when he discovers that he has become prey to a formidable enemy.\n\n(Source: MangaHelpers)", "Zerozaki Kishishiki no Ningen Knock", null, "零崎軋識の人間ノック", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/70117/Zerozaki_Kishishiki_no_Ningen_Knock", 4 },
                    { 70251, "", 6, new DateTime(2011, 1, 7, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/149631.jpg", 3242, 7.46m, new DateTime(2006, 12, 31, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "First collection of Komi Naoshi's short stories.\n\n1. Island\n2. Koi no Kamisama\n3. Williams\n4. Personant\n5. Apple\n6. Nisekoi (pilot)", "Koi no Kamisama", null, "恋の神様 古味直志短編集", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/70251/Koi_no_Kamisama", 1 },
                    { 70259, "Mushoku Tensei: Isekai Ittara Honki Dasu has been published in English as Mushoku Tensei: Jobless Reincarnation by Seven Seas Entertainment since November 24, 2015.", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/181049.jpg", 549, 8.12m, new DateTime(2014, 5, 1, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "A 34-year-old NEET loses his life saving a stranger in a traffic accident, only to wake up to find himself reborn as the baby Rudeus Greyrat in a new world filled with magic. The child of the adventurers Paul and Zenith Greyrat, his innate talent for magic is immediately recognized when he turns two, and the magic tutor Roxy Migurdia is brought to his home to refine him into a mage. With a tremendous amount of magical power and a wealth of knowledge from his original world, Rudeus seeks to fulfill his only desires from his previous life—to not repeat the mistakes of his past and die with no regrets.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Mushoku Tensei: Isekai Ittara Honki Dasu", "Mushoku Tensei: Jobless Reincarnation", "無職転生 ～異世界行ったら本気だす～", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/70259/Mushoku_Tensei__Isekai_Ittara_Honki_Dasu", null },
                    { 70261, "Mushoku Tensei: Isekai Ittara Honki Dasu is a web novel that was serialized on Shousetsuka ni Narou website from November 22, 2012 to April 3, 2015. It made repeated appearances on site's rankings as the most popular work during its serialization. Media Factory published the first volume on January 23, 2014. The series was published in English as Mushoku Tensei: Jobless Reincarnation by Seven Seas Entertainment under the Airship imprint from May 21, 2019 to March 12, 2024.", 330, new DateTime(2022, 11, 24, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/120337.jpg", 33, 8.82m, new DateTime(2014, 1, 22, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Killed while saving a stranger from a traffic collision, a 34-year-old NEET is reincarnated into a world of magic as Rudeus Greyrat, a newborn baby. With knowledge, experience, and regrets from his previous life retained, Rudeus vows to lead a fulfilling life and not repeat his past mistakes.\n\nNow gifted with a tremendous amount of magical power as well as the mind of a grown adult, Rudeus is seen as a genius in the making by his new parents. Soon, he finds himself studying under powerful warriors, such as his swordsman father and a mage named Roxy Migurdia—all in order to hone his apparent talents. But despite his innocent exterior, Rudeus is still a perverted otaku, who uses his wealth of knowledge to make moves on women whom he could never make in his previous life.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Mushoku Tensei: Isekai Ittara Honki Dasu", "Mushoku Tensei: Jobless Reincarnation", "無職転生 ～異世界行ったら本気だす～", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/70261/Mushoku_Tensei__Isekai_Ittara_Honki_Dasu", 26 },
                    { 70307, "Juuou Mujin no Fafnir was published digitally in English as Unlimited Fafnir by Kodansha Comics USA from January 19, 2016 to February 09, 2016.", 21, new DateTime(2015, 12, 6, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/139885.jpg", 15681, 6.53m, new DateTime(2014, 3, 6, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Second Lieutenant Mononobe Yuu has been sent to Midgard, to attend the all-girl's school where his sister Mitsuki is the student council president. The school is specifically for people who have \"D\" powers, who are needed to fight dragons, and both Mitsuki and Yuu fit the criteria. On his arrival, he meets and befriends another classmate named Iris Freya, who is having difficulties with her \"D\"-related schoolwork. They will do their best to succeed in this dangerous world.\n\n(Source: MangaHelpers)", "Juuou Mujin no Fafnir", "Unlimited Fafnir", "銃皇無尽のファフニール", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/70307/Juuou_Mujin_no_Fafnir", 4 },
                    { 70751, "Mahou Shoujo Homura★Tamura: Heikou Sekai ga Itsumo Heikou de Aru to wa Kagiranai no da. was published in English as Puella Magi Homura Tamura: Parallel Worlds Do Not Remain Parallel Forever by Yen Press from August 18, 2015, to September 19, 2017.", 30, new DateTime(2016, 10, 7, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/121481.jpg", 1659, 7.71m, new DateTime(2012, 6, 7, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Having traversed countless parallel worlds in an attempt to save Madoka Kaname from her tragic fate, Homura Akemi knows all too well of the odd divergences that can appear throughout various timelines. Despite these differences, Homura does not waver from her goal—but it does make things challenging, if not unexpectedly amusing.\n\nAside from fighting \"witches\" and gathering \"grief seeds,\" Homura finds herself in numerous absurd and comical scenarios that put to question whether parallel worlds are truly parallel!\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Mahou Shoujo Homura★Tamura: Heikou Sekai ga Itsumo Heikou de Aru to wa Kagiranai no da.", "Puella Magi Homura★Tamura: Parallel Worlds Do Not Remain Parallel Forever", "魔法少女ほむら★たむら ～平行世界がいつも平行であるとは限らないのだ。～", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/70751/Mahou_Shoujo_Homura★Tamura__Heikou_Sekai_ga_Itsumo_Heikou_de_Aru_to_wa_Kagiranai_no_da", 3 },
                    { 70815, "Death Note: L FILE No. 15 is a book that was released alongside the film L: Change the WorLd.", 2, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/121579.jpg", 10202, 6.91m, new DateTime(2008, 1, 24, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "To the wider world, L is a renowned detective, famed for his high success rate and genius intellect. Awe surrounds this figure, but despite people's admiration, L is human much like everyone else. Giving a rare glimpse into the detective's life, Death Note: L FILE No. 15 details L's origin at the Wammy's House orphanage, and outlines what a typical day looks like for the detective.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Death Note: L FILE No. 15", null, "L FILE No. 15", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/70815/Death_Note__L_FILE_No_15", null },
                    { 71253, "Dungeon ni Deai wo Motomeru no wa Machigatteiru Darou ka Gaiden: Sword Oratoria has been published in English as Is It Wrong to Try to Pick Up Girls in a Dungeon? Sword Oratoria by Yen Press since October 31, 2017.", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/150531.jpg", 1481, 7.75m, new DateTime(2014, 5, 21, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "Aiz Wallenstein is the Sword Princess, one of the best fighters from the most powerful group in all of Orario, Loki Familia. She's consumed by one goal: become stronger. Together with her familia, Aiz departs on quests to some of the deepest floors of the dungeon, exploring and fighting the dangerous monsters born below. But when one expedition goes terribly wrong, will Aiz be strong enough to save her familia, or has all her work been for naught...?\n\n(Source: Yen Press)", "Dungeon ni Deai wo Motomeru no wa Machigatteiru Darou ka Gaiden: Sword Oratoria", "Is It Wrong to Try to Pick Up Girls in a Dungeon? Sword Oratoria", "ダンジョンに出会いを求めるのは間違っているだろうか外伝 ソード・オラトリア", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/71253/Dungeon_ni_Deai_wo_Motomeru_no_wa_Machigatteiru_Darou_ka_Gaiden__Sword_Oratoria", null },
                    { 71821, "Kindaichi Shounen no Ippaku Futsuka Shouryokou was simultaneously published in Japanese, Chinese and English (as Kindaichi Case Files: The Mini-Vacation) on DeNA's Manga Box app.", 34, new DateTime(2016, 12, 6, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/186920.jpg", 44373, null, new DateTime(2014, 4, 22, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "With the genius-level reasoning ability he inherited from his grandfather Kousuke Kindaichi, Hajime Kindaichi has solved a great number of very difficult cases. But he is just a regular high school student. Though he wants to get closer to his childhood friend Miyuki, he can't manage to make a move on her because no matter where they go, a terrible crime always occurs! Kindaichi hardens his resolve and invites her on a one-night mini-vacation! \"This time it'll work for sure!\" he says to himself.\n\n(Source: Manga Box)", "Kindaichi Shounen no Ippaku Futsuka Shouryokou", "Kindaichi Case Files: The Mini-Vacation", "金田一少年の1泊2日小旅行", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/71821/Kindaichi_Shounen_no_Ippaku_Futsuka_Shouryokou", 3 },
                    { 72431, "Kidou Senshi Gundam: Gyakushuu no Char - Beltorchika's Children has been published in English as Mobile Suit Gundam: Char's Counterattack - Beltorchika's Children by Denpa since November 14, 2023.", 30, new DateTime(2018, 3, 25, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/215398.jpg", 2893, 7.51m, new DateTime(2014, 6, 25, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "In U.C. 0093, Char Aznable returns as leader of Neo Zeon, and is determined to drop the asteroid base Axis on Earth. Opposing him is the task-force Londo Bell, led by Amuro Ray and his Gundam. The final battle will take place over the Earth Sphere.\n\n(Source: Gundam Wiki)", "Kidou Senshi Gundam: Gyakushuu no Char - Beltorchika's Children", "Mobile Suit Gundam: Char's Counterattack - Beltorchika's Children", "機動戦士ガンダム 逆襲のシャア ベルトーチカ・チルドレン", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/72431/Kidou_Senshi_Gundam__Gyakushuu_no_Char_-_Beltorchikas_Children", 7 },
                    { 73115, "", 1, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/128145.jpg", 15664, 6.53m, new DateTime(2005, 6, 29, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Reborn vs Evil Hitmen is the 176.1st chapter of Akira Amano's Katekyo Hitman Reborn! and is assumed to take place before the Future Arc, therefore this chapter takes place in Namimori present.\n\n(Source: Reborn Wikia)", "Katekyou Hitman Reborn! Reborn VS Kyouaku Hitmen", null, "リボーンVS凶悪ヒットマン", 3, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/73115/Katekyou_Hitman_Reborn_Reborn_VS_Kyouaku_Hitmen", null },
                    { 73397, "The manga portion was published in English as Rurouni Kenshin: Master of Flame in VIZ Media's digital Weekly Shonen Jump.", 8, new DateTime(2014, 9, 3, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/201970.jpg", 3768, 7.4m, new DateTime(2014, 7, 3, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "1-2. Rurouni Kenshin Uramaku: Honoo wo Suberu (Rurouni Kenshin: Master of Flame) [Watsuki Nobuhiro]\n3-8. Sono Kage, Hanaregataku Tsunagitomeru Mono [Kurosaki Kaoru]", "Rurouni Kenshin Uramaku: Honoo wo Suberu", null, "るろうに剣心・裏幕─炎を統べる─", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/73397/Rurouni_Kenshin_Uramaku__Honoo_wo_Suberu", 1 },
                    { 73631, null, null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/127767.jpg", 3757, 7.4m, new DateTime(2013, 6, 3, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, null, "Haikyuu!! Shousetsu-ban!!", null, "ハイキュー!! ショーセツバン!!", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/73631/Haikyuu_Shousetsu-ban", null },
                    { 73781, "Mahou Shoujo Tart★Magica: The Legend of \"Jeanne d'Arc\" was published in English as Puella Magi Tart Magica: The Legend of Jeanne d'Arc by Yen Press from April 21, 2015, to November 14, 2017.", 21, new DateTime(2017, 2, 8, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/191170.jpg", 2699, 7.53m, new DateTime(2013, 11, 7, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "It is the year 1429—France is embroiled in the arduous Hundred Years' War against England, where the English are steadily driving their opponent toward bitter defeat. However, the tides of the battle unexpectedly turn with the arrival of Jeanne d'Arc: a young maiden who not only wields immense power but also possesses the ability to hear the voice of the angel. Proving her prowess on the battlefield, Jeanne is soon hailed as a miracle, reinvigorating and rallying the French to continue their uphill campaign.\n\nWhile she leads the crusade to liberate France from its English invaders, Jeanne gradually adjusts to her new role as a magical girl with the help of her close confidant, Riz Hawkwood. Their unique abilities enable them to boldly fight a two-front war against \"witches\" and other magical girls with sinister intentions. But as the beacon of light from Jeanne's cause grows ever stronger, so does the darkness that lurks behind the theater of war.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Mahou Shoujo Tart★Magica: The Legend of \"Jeanne d'Arc\"", "Puella Magi Tart★Magica: The Legend of \"Jeanne d'Arc\"", "魔法少女たると★マギカ The Legend of \"Jeanne d'Arc\"", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/73781/Mahou_Shoujo_Tart★Magica__The_Legend_of_Jeanne_dArc", 5 },
                    { 74157, "", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/128659.jpg", 44704, null, new DateTime(2014, 7, 3, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The story of the novel series revolves around female middle school student Chiyoko, who is part of her school's naginata club. In her house sleeps a single revolver. That gun is actually able to transform into human form, and in the past, he was created to be an assassin for the imperial city's information bureau. Chiyoko learns of the revolver, whose name is Zerozero Nanashiki (007-shki), and she teams up with him to defeat the halberd tsukumogami Reishiki (0-shiki), who has been killing people for the past few hundred years.\n\n(Source: ANN)", "Tsukumogami: Teito Jouhoubu Tokken Chohouin 007-shiki", null, "ツクモガミ 帝都情報部特権諜報員零零七式", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/74157/Tsukumogami__Teito_Jouhoubu_Tokken_Chohouin_007-shiki", 1 },
                    { 74339, "Tsubasa: WoRLD CHRoNiCLE - Niraikanai-hen was published in English by Kodansha Comics USA from December 15, 2015 to November 22, 2016.", 19, new DateTime(2016, 3, 18, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/151905.jpg", 1832, 7.68m, new DateTime(2014, 8, 19, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Syaoran and his friends were successful in collecting Sakura's memories and defeating Fei Wang. However, in order to release Fei Wang's last spell, Syaoran had to pay the price of \"continuing his journey.\" He parted with Sakura and once more, accompanied by Kurogane, Fai, and Mokona, travels to a parallel universe! The group has arrived at a seemingly peaceful paradise, but a cloud of darkness approaches...\n\n(Source: Goodreads)", "Tsubasa: WoRLD CHRoNiCLE - Niraikanai-hen", "Tsubasa: WoRLD CHRoNiCLE Niraikanai", "ツバサ WoRLD CHRoNiCLE ニライカナイ編", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/74339/Tsubasa__WoRLD_CHRoNiCLE_-_Niraikanai-hen", 3 },
                    { 74695, "Re:Zero kara Hajimeru Isekai Seikatsu: Dai-1 Shou - Outo no Ichinichi-hen adapts the first volume of the light novel series. The manga was published in English as Re:ZERO -Starting Life in Another World- Chapter 1: A Day in the Capital by Yen Press from July 26, 2016, to October 25, 2016. It was also released in Polish by Waneko from April 24, 2017, to June 23, 2017; and in Russian as Re: Zero. Жизнь с нуля в альтернативном мире. Глава первая by Istari Comics in March 2018.", 11, new DateTime(2015, 2, 26, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/188949.jpg", 1625, 7.72m, new DateTime(2014, 6, 26, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "While returning home from the convenience store, Subaru Natsuki suddenly finds himself standing in an unfamiliar city, surrounded by unfamiliar people speaking unfamiliar words. Subaru quickly connects the dots and realizes that he's been transported to another world. After being chased off by a shop owner for being penniless, Subaru finds himself surrounded by a group of thugs.\n\nJust when Subaru thinks all hope is lost, a mysterious girl named Satella comes to his rescue. She's after a thief who Subaru had previously seen in town. After Satella scares off the thugs, Subaru decides to repay her by helping her look for the thief.\n\nThrough a series of events, the pair finds themselves at a cellar known for housing stolen goods. Shortly after entering the house, Subaru and Satella are ambushed by a dark figure and neither survives the encounter. Subaru opens his eyes to find that he has gone back in time to earlier that day, beginning a confusing series of loops in which he relives past occurrences.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Re:Zero kara Hajimeru Isekai Seikatsu: Dai-1 Shou - Outo no Ichinichi-hen", "Re:ZERO -Starting Life in Another World- Chapter 1: A Day in the Capital", "Re：ゼロから始める異世界生活 第一章 王都の一日編", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/74695/Re_Zero_kara_Hajimeru_Isekai_Seikatsu__Dai-1_Shou_-_Outo_no_Ichinichi-hen", 2 },
                    { 74697, "Re:Zero kara Hajimeru Isekai Seikatsu has been serialized online through the website Shousetsuka ni Narou since April 2012, and was later officially published in book format by Media Factory under the MF Bunko J imprint beginning January 25, 2014. Much of the web content was trimmed and edited for the light novel release. The series ranked second in the 2018 Kono Light Novel ga Sugoi! in the Light Novels category. The series has been published in English as Re:ZERO -Starting Life in Another World- by Yen Press under the Yen On imprint since July 19, 2016. It has also been released in Polish by Waneko since April 6, 2017; in Brazilian Portuguese by NewPOP Editora since October 20, 2017; and in Russian by Istari Comics since March 2018.", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/129447.jpg", 42, 8.79m, new DateTime(2014, 1, 22, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "Exiting the convenience store, Subaru Natsuki emerges to a busy town inhabited by humans and demi-humans. Using dragons and carriages as transportation, the town is clearly not the modern-day Japan that he is familiar with. However, as someone who spends his days engrossed in comics and games, Subaru assumes that he is a protagonist in this new fantasy world, harnessing supreme magical powers.\n\nMuch to his dismay, that is not the case and things quickly go awry as he bumps into a group of thugs. Fortunately, a silver-haired beauty named Satella comes to his rescue, while looking for her stolen insignia. In return for her kindness, Subaru offers to help with the search, which eventually leads them to a loot shop. Assuming that the insignia was traded for money, Subaru enters the shop hoping to negotiate with the owner regarding the stolen item. However, much to his surprise, what awaits them is not the insignia but a brutal assassin that leads the two to their demise.\n\nBut instead of waking up in the afterlife, Subaru is shocked to find himself standing alone in the midst of daytime, as if he never left the town in the first place. Thus, his life in another world mysteriously begins a second time.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Re:Zero kara Hajimeru Isekai Seikatsu", "Re:ZERO -Starting Life in Another World-", "Re：ゼロから始める異世界生活", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/74697/Re_Zero_kara_Hajimeru_Isekai_Seikatsu", null },
                    { 74847, "Tokyo Ghoul was published in English by VIZ Media from October 18, 2016 to April 18, 2017. The series was also published in German by Kazé from 2014 to 2016.", 17, new DateTime(2014, 12, 18, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/194456.jpg", 728, 8.01m, new DateTime(2013, 7, 18, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Explore the world of Tokyo Ghoul with these pros\n\nGhouls live among us, the same as normal people in every way—except their craving for human flesh.\n\nKen Kaneki is an ordinary college student until a violent encounter turns him into the first half-human half-ghoul hybrid. Trapped between two worlds, he must survive Ghoul turf wars, learn more about Ghoul society and master his new powers.\n\nMany conflicts and incidents arise involving the clientele of the café Anteiku, where Ghouls gather. Yoshimura, the café's owner, is harboring suspicions about a certain someone. What sort of darkness will that person bring between those who hunt and those who are hunted? This book chronicles six all-new stories from the Tokyo Ghoul universe.\n\n(Source: VIZ Media)", "Tokyo Ghoul", "Tokyo Ghoul", "東京喰種トーキョーグール", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/74847/Tokyo_Ghoul", 3 },
                    { 74859, "Psycho-Pass: Kanshikan Kougami Shinya has been published in English as Psycho-Pass: Inspector Shinya Kogami by Dark Horse Manga since November 29, 2016.", 35, new DateTime(2017, 11, 3, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/140757.jpg", 2700, 7.53m, new DateTime(2014, 6, 29, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "In the distant future, Japan strives to be an ideal society. As a way to maintain peace, the Sibyl System is established: it serves as a method to measure emotion, desire, or a thought that deviates from the norm—also dubbed as one's \"Psycho-Pass.\" However, crime has yet to be eradicated; the Public Safety Bureau's Inspectors utilize Denominators, lethal weapons that evaluate an individual's Psycho-Pass, to catch and deal with the immoral outlaws.\n\nInspector Shinya Kougami, along with his unit, Division 03, has been tasked with finding the criminal behind \"The Branding Case.\" But as the detectives delve deeper into the unusual incident, it soon turns unexpectedly sinister.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Psycho-Pass: Kanshikan Kougami Shinya", "Psycho-Pass: Inspector Shinya Kogami", "PSYCHO-PASS 監視官 狡噛慎也", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/74859/Psycho-Pass__Kanshikan_Kougami_Shinya", 6 },
                    { 75051, "", 28, new DateTime(2014, 8, 3, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/130273.jpg", 44793, null, new DateTime(2011, 12, 2, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A spin-off of Bobobo-bo Bo-Bobo starring Don Patch.", "Fuwari! Don Patch", null, "ふわり!どんぱっち", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/75051/Fuwari_Don_Patch", 3 },
                    { 75053, "", 1, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/5/130719.jpg", 18573, 6.18m, new DateTime(2014, 7, 1, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Special collaboration between Seo Kouji (Fuuka), Hiroyuki (Aho Girl), Yoshikawa Miki (Yamada-kun to 7-nin no Majo) and Katsuki Hikaru (Baby Steps).", "Magazine Heroines on the Beach", null, "マガジンヒロインズオンザビーチ [M.H.B!]", 3, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/75053/Magazine_Heroines_on_the_Beach", null },
                    { 75055, "", 47, new DateTime(2016, 10, 7, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/184553.jpg", 9017, 6.99m, new DateTime(2014, 8, 8, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "This spin-off manga is a comedy which re-imagines the sins from the original manga as high school students.", "Mayoe! Nanatsu no Taizai Gakuen!", null, "迷え！七つの大罪学園！", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/75055/Mayoe_Nanatsu_no_Taizai_Gakuen", 4 },
                    { 75099, "Sword Art Online: Phantom Bullet was published in English by Yen Press from January 26, 2016 to January 17, 2023.", 20, new DateTime(2021, 12, 9, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/137907.jpg", 2792, 7.52m, new DateTime(2014, 4, 9, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "It has been a full year since the end of the Sword Art Online incident and ten months since the end of the ALfheim Online incident. Although things had returned to normal for some time, mysterious incidents occur in another VRMMO game, called Gun Gale Online (GGO), when in two instances, a player in the game is shot by a mysterious person in a mantle who calls himself \"Death Gun\" and the shot player mysteriously disconnects after a few seconds, only for their real body to be found dead days later. After the second such incident, Kirigaya Kazuto is asked by a member of the VR Crimes Division, Kikuoka Seijirou, to investigate the rumours that the incidents in-game are related to the deaths of the players in the real world.\n\nAfter hearing that Death Gun has a requirement for his targets: the people he supposedly kills are all top players, Kazuto agrees to convert his ALfheim Online avatar into Gun Gale Online using The Seed's character conversion feature to enter the most well known tournament in the game, the Bullet of Bullets, to draw the attention of the mysterious Death Gun.\n\n(Source: Sword Art Online Wikia)", "Sword Art Online: Phantom Bullet", "Sword Art Online: Phantom Bullet", "ソードアート・オンライン ファントム・バレット", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/75099/Sword_Art_Online__Phantom_Bullet", 4 },
                    { 75101, "Sword Art Online: Mother's Rosario was published in English by Yen Press from March 22, 2016, to September 19, 2017. It was also released in Brazilian Portuguese by Panini Comics from September 25, 2020, to January 11, 2021.", 14, new DateTime(2016, 4, 8, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/145353.jpg", 1352, 7.79m, new DateTime(2014, 6, 9, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "While Asuna, Leafa, Silica and Lisbeth were doing their homework in Kirito and Asuna's Log House on the 22nd Floor of New Aincrad, Lisbeth informed Asuna of a player known as \"Zekken\" (Absolute Sword) who was challenging players on the 24th Floor, while offering an 11-hit Original Sword Skill as a reward. Asuna was told that the mysterious player had actually converted from a different game and that over thirty players who had attempted to challenge the player, including Leafa and even Kirito, were defeated. Hearing that Kirito had said something to the player before being defeated and not sharing what he had said with the others and thinking that the mysterious player had come for a reason, Asuna decided to challenge the player as well. To her surprise, the player was actually a girl named Yuuki.\n\n(Source: SAO Wikia)", "Sword Art Online: Mother's Rosario", "Sword Art Online: Mother's Rosary", "ソードアート・オンライン マザーズ・ロザリオ", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/75101/Sword_Art_Online__Mothers_Rosario", 3 },
                    { 75103, "Sword Art Online: Calibur was published in English by Yen Press on December 19, 2017. It was also released in Brazilian Portuguese by Panini Comics on July 25, 2020.", 10, new DateTime(2015, 6, 29, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/162192.jpg", 6568, 7.15m, new DateTime(2014, 7, 29, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "On December 28, 2025, Suguha showed Kazuto a news article that the Holy Sword Excalibur in ALfheim Online had been found. Excalibur was the rarest and most powerful sword in ALO, but, although they had found the sword nearly a year ago, they were not able to break through the guardians of the dungeon that the sword was held in, until they ended up temporarily forgetting about the sword due to more important matters. However, Kazuto was then told that the weapon had only been discovered so far, but not yet acquired. Thus Kazuto called Asuna, Lisbeth, Silica, Klein and Sinon to form a full party and attempt to clear the dungeon again. However, after they arrived at Jötunheimr and got on Tonkii's back, they discovered that the other players discovered the location of the item via a quest that required slaughtering the beast-type Evil Gods.\n\n(Source: Sword Art Online Wikia)", "Sword Art Online: Calibur", "Sword Art Online: Calibur", "ソードアート・オンライン キャリバー", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/75103/Sword_Art_Online__Calibur", 1 },
                    { 75493, "Fairy Girls was published in English by Kodansha Comics USA from November 10, 2015 to April 25, 2017.", 21, new DateTime(2016, 8, 19, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/157526.jpg", 16201, 6.49m, new DateTime(2014, 11, 19, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "In the Kingdom of Fiore, wizards are commonplace, but the powerful women of Fairy Tail are each one of a kind! And after fighting their way to the top of the Grand Magic Games, Lucy, Erza, Wendy, and Juvia deserve a vacation. The wizards slip out of the victory celebration to do some sightseeing as a foursome, but where Fairy Tail goes, trouble's never far behind, and soon they find themselves caught up in yet another chaotic bought of spells lining...with the fate of Fiore in the balance!\n\n(Source: Kodansha USA)", "Fairy Girls", "Fairy Girls", "FAIRY GIRLS", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/75493/Fairy_Girls", 4 },
                    { 75495, "Fairy Tail: Blue Mistral was published in English by Kodansha Comics USA from August 25, 2015, to August 7, 2018. It was also released in Brazilian Portuguese by Editora JBC from November 4, 2019, to December 18, 2019.", 17, new DateTime(2015, 11, 30, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/153098.jpg", 13981, 6.66m, new DateTime(2014, 8, 1, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A mysterious request leads Wendy Marvell and her feline companion Charles to Nanalu Village, only to find that the job requester does not actually exist. Instead, Wendy becomes friends with Yoshino: a girl her age and the only mage in the village. Wendy soon learns that the villagers have slowly been disappearing, supposedly because of a dead dragon's curse. With only herself and Charles to take on the task, Wendy is determined to help Yoshino save the village.\n\nFairy Tail: Blue Mistral depicts Wendy and Charles' adventures soon after joining Fairy Tail. Wendy faces the ghost of a dragon, a cursed mansion, and other tough challenges, desperate to prove herself as a Fairy Tail member.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Fairy Tail: Blue Mistral", "Fairy Tail: Blue Mistral", "FAIRY TAIL ブルー・ミストラル", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/75495/Fairy_Tail__Blue_Mistral", 4 },
                    { 75497, "Tale of Fairy Tail: Ice Trail was published in English by Kodansha Comics USA from December 29, 2015, to June 28, 2016. It was also released in Brazilian Portuguese by Editora JBC in April 2019.", 15, new DateTime(2015, 7, 16, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/164272.jpg", 9165, 6.97m, new DateTime(2014, 7, 15, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Following the death of his master, Ul, Gray Fullbuster sets out on his own to see the world and strengthen the skills he learned from her. While trudging through wild weather and heavy snow, he comes across a frightened girl named Nano Leaf fleeing from pursuers. Outnumbered, they are both captured and brought back to the dark guild Chrono Noise. Gray soon learns of the guild's nefarious plan for Nano, and if he is to go out and see the world, he must do everything he can to stop their evil plot and rescue her.\n\nTale of Fairy Tail: Ice Trail tells the story of Gray's adventures before becoming a part of Fairy Tail and the challenges that he overcomes in order to become stronger.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Tale of Fairy Tail: Ice Trail", "Fairy Tail: Ice Trail", "TALE of FAIRY TAIL ICE TRAIL～氷の軌跡～", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/75497/Tale_of_Fairy_Tail__Ice_Trail", 2 },
