                    { 79133, "Junketsu no Maria: Exhibition was published in English as Maria the Virgin Witch: Exhibition by Kodansha Comics USA on August 25, 2015.", 6, new DateTime(2014, 12, 5, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/147849.jpg", 9306, 6.97m, new DateTime(2014, 7, 6, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Maria and her friends are back in a collection of stories that offer a glimpse into their past, present, and future. From Viv's journey to France, to a day in the life of Maria and her owl companions, and even a brief peek at the result of Ezekiel's judgment, Maria the Virgin Witch: Exhibition allows fans of the series to enjoy their favorite characters once more with new and untold stories.\n\n(Source: Kodansha Comics USA)", "Junketsu no Maria: Exhibition", "Maria the Virgin Witch: Exhibition", "純潔のマリア exhibition", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/79133/Junketsu_no_Maria__Exhibition", 1 },
                    { 80163, null, 308, new DateTime(2022, 11, 11, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/151837.jpg", 2705, 7.53m, new DateTime(2014, 9, 21, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, null, "Let's! Haikyuu!?", null, "れっつ! ハイキュー!?", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/80163/Lets_Haikyuu", 11 },
                    { 80223, "", 16, new DateTime(2018, 2, 4, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/272102.jpg", 5168, 7.26m, new DateTime(2013, 4, 19, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "New installment of Versailles no Bara after 40 years since serialization ended, includes new episodes centered around André, Gerodelle, Fersen, Alain and many more. Each episode tells about events that happened afterward the main story and their unknown pasts that weren't disclosed before.", "Versailles no Bara: Episode-hen", null, "ベルサイユのばら エピソード編", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/80223/Versailles_no_Bara__Episode-hen", 4 },
                    { 80385, "Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku wo! has been published in English as KonoSuba: God's Blessing on This Wonderful World! by Yen Press since November 22, 2016. It has also been published in French as Konosuba : Sois Béni Monde Merveilleux! by Meian since June 29, 2020.", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/154542.jpg", 738, 8.01m, new DateTime(2014, 9, 8, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "Kazuma Satou is a reserved 16-year-old who loses his life in a tragic yet laughable accident. After his untimely death, Kazuma finds himself standing before Aqua—the self-proclaimed water goddess who presents him two with choices: to ascend to heaven or reincarnate in a real fantasy world. Picking the latter, Kazuma gets tasked with defeating the Demon King, an occurring threat in his new world. However, Aqua's provocative attitude strikes a nerve, and in the heat of the moment, Kazuma takes her along.\n\nKazuma and Aqua, now stuck together in another world, embark on a journey. They soon acquire two more companions: Megumin, an archwizard wielding devastating explosion magic; and Lalatina \"Darkness\" Dustiness Ford, a crusader with a worrisome case of masochism. The four of them form an odd party, each member contributing their unique share of power and a peculiar personality. Unfortunately, their adventure soon proves to be challenging and costly, Kazuma's new life may be nothing but a headache.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku wo!", "KonoSuba: God's Blessing on This Wonderful World!", "この素晴らしい世界に祝福を！", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/80385/Kono_Subarashii_Sekai_ni_Shukufuku_wo", null },
                    { 80435, null, null, new DateTime(2007, 12, 13, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/139119.jpg", 5072, 7.27m, new DateTime(2006, 4, 12, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, null, "School Rumble", null, "スクールランブル", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/80435/School_Rumble", 2 },
                    { 80469, "", 18, new DateTime(2017, 2, 2, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/190626.jpg", 1039, 7.88m, new DateTime(2013, 12, 23, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "In the Meiji Era of Japan, legend has it that the \"Orochi\"—an evil giant snake spirit—returns every 300 years to wreak havoc. \"Yamainu,\" an elite fighting force, is assembled to subjugate the Orochi upon its reappearance. Presently, the squad has become involved with a secret government department conducting human experimentation using Orochi cells. This pits Yamainu leader Sousei Abeno against brothers Soramaru and Chuutarou Kumou, who stumble upon several dying escapees of the experiments.\n\nSoramaru encounters Ageha, a criminal doctor allied with Tora, a test subject who massacred cell project researchers using abilities granted by compatible Orochi cells. Despite acknowledging their crimes, Soramaru still decides to side with the two fugitives due to his strong opposition to the exploitation of Orochi cells. With Sousei and Soramaru divided over the ethics of creating novel drugs from the essence of their immortal enemy, the only way to settle this matter may be a fight—however, Soramaru has yet to win once against Yamainu's captain.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Donten ni Warau Gaiden", null, "曇天に笑う 外伝", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/80469/Donten_ni_Warau_Gaiden", 3 },
                    { 80473, "", null, new DateTime(2016, 9, 13, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/142963.jpg", 7413, 7.09m, new DateTime(2013, 12, 3, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Led by Daisuke Aramaki and Motoko Kusanagi, Section 9 deals with such crimes over the entire social spectrum, usually with success. However, when faced with a new A-level hacker nicknamed \"The Laughing Man,\" the team is thrown into a dangerous cat and mouse game, following the hacker's trail as it leaves its mark on Japan.", "Koukaku Kidoutai: Stand Alone Complex - The Laughing Man", null, "攻殻機動隊 STAND ALONE COMPLEX ～The Laughing Man～", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/80473/Koukaku_Kidoutai__Stand_Alone_Complex_-_The_Laughing_Man", 4 },
                    { 80719, "Re:Zero kara Hajimeru Isekai Seikatsu: Dai-2 Shou - Yashiki no Isshuukan-hen adapts the second and third volumes of the light novel series. The manga was published in English as Re:ZERO -Starting Life in Another World-, Chapter 2: A Week at the Mansion by Yen Press from May 23, 2017, to September 18, 2018. It was also released in Polish by Waneko from June 8, 2018, to February 14, 2019.", 31, new DateTime(2017, 10, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/188947.jpg", 736, 8.01m, new DateTime(2014, 10, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The unaware Subaru Natsuki wakes to see two figures standing in a completely unfamiliar room. The two girls, who turn out to be the sisters Rem and Ram, are immediately teased by Subaru for their synchronistic way of speaking. Before he can go too far, he is interrupted by Emilia—the charming girl he saved at the cost of losing his life thrice using \"Return By Death,\" an ability that allows him to return to a certain \"savepoint\" each time he dies.\n\nEmilia informs him that due to the injury he received while protecting her from Elsa Granhiert, she brought him to the mansion she lives in. There, Subaru meets Roswaal L. Mathers, the clownlike count who owns the residence. While everyone is having breakfast, Subaru requests a reward: to let him be hired as a butler alongside Rem and Ram, which Roswaal quickly grants.\n\nEverything seems to be going well for Subaru. However, after a few days inside the mansion, he mysteriously wakes up at the beginning again, reminding him an awful lot of his ability. Can Subaru unravel the mystery behind his death, or will his spirit break first?\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Re:Zero kara Hajimeru Isekai Seikatsu: Dai-2 Shou - Yashiki no Isshuukan-hen", "Re:ZERO -Starting Life in Another World-, Chapter 2: A Week at the Mansion", "Re：ゼロから始める異世界生活 第二章 屋敷の一週間編", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/80719/Re_Zero_kara_Hajimeru_Isekai_Seikatsu__Dai-2_Shou_-_Yashiki_no_Isshuukan-hen", 5 },
                    { 80843, "Gundam: G no Reconguista is based on original TV anime series of the same title.", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/148969.jpg", 45486, null, new DateTime(2014, 8, 25, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "The Universal Century, with its history of colonization and wars, passes into posterity, and time flows on.\n\nMankind enters a new age of seemingly endless peace and prosperity called the \"Regild Century.\"\n\nThe year is R.C. 1014. The Capital Tower, an orbital elevator, connects earth and space. Due to its role in supplying Earth's power by transferring Photon Batteries from space, it is worshiped with a religious fervor. Bellri Zenam, a cadet in the Capital Guard formed to protect Capital Tower, is participating in his first non-simulated exercise when he is attacked by the powerful but unaffiliated \"G-Self\" mobile suit. He manages to capture the G-Self while piloting a \"Recten\" maintenance mobile suit. However, seeing the G-Self's pilot, a young space pirate named Aida Rayhunton, stirs something within him, as does the G-Self which he was sure he'd never seen before. Why does the G-Self accept Bellri as a pilot?\n\nAida's mission to attack Capital Tower. Bellri's destiny as a chosen pilot of the G-Self. The truth which will shake the Regild Century.\n\nIt was all the beginning of the Reconguista.\n\n(Source: Gundam.info)", "Gundam: G no Reconguista", "Gundam: Reconguista in G", "ガンダム Gのレコンギスタ", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/80843/Gundam__G_no_Reconguista", null },
                    { 80909, "Tokyo Ghoul won the Excellence Award in the 113th Manga Grand Prix.", 1, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/140109.jpg", 9022, 6.99m, new DateTime(2011, 3, 14, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The prototype of the series prior to its serialization.", "Tokyo Ghoul", null, "東京喰種－トーキョーグール－", 3, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/80909/Tokyo_Ghoul", null },
                    { 81117, "Tokyo Ghoul:re was the 10th best-selling manga series in Japan in 2015 with an estimated sales of 3,758,541 copies sold. The series was published in English by VIZ Media from October 17, 2017 to April 21, 2020. It is also published in Spanish by Norma Editorial since June 23, 2016; in German by Kazé since September 1, 2016; in Polish by Waneko since August 14, 2017; and in Portuguese by Panini Editorial since December 15, 2017.", 181, new DateTime(2018, 7, 4, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/145997.jpg", 318, 8.29m, new DateTime(2014, 10, 15, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Two years have passed since the CCG's raid on Anteiku. Although the atmosphere in Tokyo has changed drastically due to the increased influence of the CCG, ghouls continue to pose a problem as they have begun taking caution, especially the terrorist organization Aogiri Tree, who acknowledge the CCG's growing threat to their existence.\n\nThe creation of a special team, known as the Quinx Squad, may provide the CCG with the push they need to exterminate Tokyo's unwanted residents. As humans who have undergone surgery in order to make use of the special abilities of ghouls, they participate in operations to eradicate the dangerous creatures. The leader of this group, Haise Sasaki, is a half-ghoul, half-human who has been trained by famed special class investigator, Kishou Arima. However, there's more to this young man than meets the eye, as unknown memories claw at his mind, slowly reminding him of the person he used to be.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Tokyo Ghoul:re", "Tokyo Ghoul:re", "東京喰種-トーキョーグール-:re", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/81117/Tokyo_Ghoul_re", 16 },
                    { 81151, "Psycho-Pass 2 was published in French by Kana and in Italian by Planet Manga.", 27, new DateTime(2017, 2, 2, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/190624.jpg", 4069, 7.37m, new DateTime(2014, 11, 4, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "With the conclusion of the Makishima case, Shinya Kougami is a wanted fugitive, Nobuchika Ginoza has become a potential criminal, and two Enforcers are gone. The Ministry of Welfare's Public Safety Bureau is desperately in need of new personnel, leading the organization to bring in 17-year-old novice Inspector Mika Shimotsuki to join Inspector Akane Tsunemori's Division 01.\n\nWhile Tsunemori now questions and even challenges the Sibyl System, Shimotsuki unconditionally believes in its judgment. However, her first case urges her to see the opposite: a new criminal emerges, an individual who has the power to lower one's Psycho-Pass enough for the System to overlook them as convicts and even humans.\n\nWhen a felon with hard evidence against him walks free with a clear Psycho-Pass, immediate action becomes imperative. Now Inspectors and Enforcers must work together to decipher an unsettling message left behind and trace the guilty criminal who, in the eyes of the System, does not exist.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Psycho-Pass 2", null, "PSYCHO-PASS 2", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/81151/Psycho-Pass_2", 5 },
                    { 81153, "", 23, new DateTime(2017, 2, 19, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/155882.jpg", 8268, 7.03m, new DateTime(2014, 10, 5, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "In the prestigious Psycho-Pass Academy, one club enforces justice across the school's premises: Public Safety Bureau (PSB). The club operates in the name of the Sibyl System—the teachers' watchful eyes—to keep the school safe from vandalism. To this end, they utilize guns called Denominators that measure one's Delinquency Coefficient, the likelihood to turn delinquent.\n\nAkane Tsunemori is a freshman who finds her way into PSB. There, she meets two upperclassmen: Nobuchika Ginoza, who takes his job seriously; and Shinya Kougami, Nobuchika's \"dog\" and a potential delinquent eradicating wrongdoers. Allying herself with this unconventional Disciplinary Committee, Tsunemori begins her ridiculous high school days as she investigates anything that could disrupt the precious peace.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Gakuen Psycho-Pass", null, "学園さいこぱす", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/81153/Gakuen_Psycho-Pass", 3 },
                    { 81157, "", 6, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/140943.jpg", 45542, null, new DateTime(2014, 8, 28, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Novel that focuses on Kagari Shuusei.", "Psycho-Pass Legend: Tsuisekisha Kagari Shuusei", null, "PSYCHO-PASS LEGEND 追跡者 縢秀星", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/81157/Psycho-Pass_Legend__Tsuisekisha_Kagari_Shuusei", 1 },
                    { 81485, "", 29, new DateTime(2015, 12, 25, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/140991.jpg", 6271, 7.17m, new DateTime(2013, 7, 26, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The miniature yet equally troublesome versions of Ikebukuro's residents run amok. However, instead of engaging in deadly schemes, everyone is gathering to organize a laid-back summer festival! Ikebukuro's strongest man is running a chocolate banana stand, the feared Black Rider dresses in a cute yukata, and even the infamous information broker is unknowingly helping everything go smoothly. It seems that as they shrank, so did their problems, and the busy world of gangs and the supernatural finally gets a well-deserved break.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Minidura", null, "みにでゅら", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/81485/Minidura", 4 },
                    { 81551, "Durarara!! Relay is an adaptation of Kadokawa Games' PlayStation Vita game, released on January 29, 2015.", 12, new DateTime(2015, 11, 20, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/160115.jpg", 6114, 7.19m, new DateTime(2014, 10, 21, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "It has been almost a year since Mikado Ryuugamine moved to Ikebukuro, and the city seems stagnant. He recalls Izaya Orihara's words: even the most eventful city like Tokyo will eventually feel monotonous. However, when Mikado's old friend Miyoshi Yoshimune returns to Raira Academy, life picks up its restless pace once more.\n\nMeanwhile, during the calm, Shizuo Heiwajima wishes more control over his anger outbursts. His boss, Tom Tanaka, suggests they go see the new popular movie starring Shizuo's brother Kasuka, the film which has brought overwhelming popularity to the attaché cases everyone now seems to be carrying. But despite the apparent peace, Ikebukuro's anonymous online chat—now joined by Yoshimune—talks about an unsettling development: attaché case thefts are on the rise and odd tornadoes are hitting Ikebukuro—yet no one can understand why.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Durarara!! Relay", null, "デュラララ!! Relay", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/81551/Durarara_Relay", 2 },
                    { 81575, "", 8, new DateTime(2014, 6, 22, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/141177.jpg", 7224, 7.11m, new DateTime(2004, 3, 3, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "1. Nanatsu no Taizai (The Seven Deadly Sins)\n2-3. Mayoe Kohitsuji-tachi!\n4. Cowgirl Tai Sora Tobu Enban\n5. Blizzard Axel\n6-7. Memory of Moon\n8. Mujihi na Country Girl", "Nanatsu no Tanpen", "The Seven Stories", "七つの短編 鈴木央短編集", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/81575/Nanatsu_no_Tanpen", 1 },
                    { 81611, "", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/141221.jpg", 45582, null, new DateTime(2014, 10, 10, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "An anthology of Aldnoah.Zero by various mangaka.", "Aldnoah.Zero Anthology Comic", null, "ALDNOAH.ZERO アンソロジーコミック", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/81611/AldnoahZero_Anthology_Comic", null },
                    { 81667, "Overlord was published in English by Yen Press from June 28, 2016, to October 15, 2024. The series has also been released in Italian by J-POP since May 18, 2016; and in Spanish by ECC Ediciones since October 31, 2017.", null, new DateTime(2023, 5, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/161407.jpg", 817, 7.97m, new DateTime(2014, 11, 25, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Momonga is an average salaryman who spends his free time playing Yggdrasil, a DMMO-RPG (Dive Massively Multiplayer Online Role-Playing Game) well-known across Japan for its immense world and limitless customization. Unfortunately, all good things come to an end, and Yggdrasil's servers shut down in the year 2138. Wanting to witness the game’s final hours, Momonga, the leader of the guild Ainz Ooal Gown, logs in for the last time and heads toward the guild’s headquarters.\n\nAfter reminiscing about his comrades and adventures, Momonga prepares for the server to automatically log him out as the clock strikes midnight. However, he is not forcefully booted out of the game. Instead, he finds himself in a new world—now trapped in the body of his avatar and where non-player characters are aware of their feelings.\n\nLeft with no other options, Momonga takes on the name of his guild in hopes that other players would recognize Ainz Ooal Gown. Determined to make sense of the bizarre situation, Momonga embarks on a journey to unravel the mysteries hidden in this uncharted world.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Overlord", "Overlord", "オーバーロード", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/81667/Overlord", 19 },
                    { 81669, "Overlord has been published in English by Yen Press under the Yen On imprint in hardcover format since May 24, 2016. It has also been released in Polish by Kotori since October 17, 2016; in French by Ofelbe since May 11, 2017; in Spanish by Panini Comics since December 2018; and in Brazilian Portuguese by JBC since June 10, 2022.", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/160558.jpg", 85, 8.62m, new DateTime(2012, 7, 29, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "Yggdrasil is a virtual reality game renowned for the freedom it offers its players. After a simple tutorial, players are left to explore the world and can customize anything and everything, from their classes to their weapons. However, in the year 2138, the game sees its final hours as its servers shut down at midnight.\n\nMomonga, a devoted player of Yggdrasil, decides to spend the game's last hours inside his guild, Ainz Ooal Gown. Strangely, at the stroke of midnight, the game does not log him out. Instead, Momonga finds himself transported to another world, one that is seemingly identical to that of Yggdrasil. Facing an already abnormal situation, he discovers that the NPCs have gained sentience.\n\nTrapped in his avatar's skeletal body and desperate to uncover the cause of his predicament and find other players like him, Momonga sets out to take control of the new world with the help of his loyal subjects.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Overlord", "Overlord", "オーバーロード", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/81669/Overlord", null },
                    { 82283, "", 7, new DateTime(2012, 3, 31, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/142469.jpg", 45674, null, new DateTime(2011, 8, 31, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A cyber battle sci-fi. In 2022, the technology of quantum computing has greatly advanced and many people have transfered their mind into the cyber space.\n\nRemu's sister, Shiki, skipped grades and entered a high school in the academic city \"Okinotori-island Mega Float City (OMFC)\" when she was 14. One day, Shiki confessed to her brother via Skype that she was talking to him directly from the cyber space and her real body had been kept in a water tank filled with a culture medium. It's called \"Body pool\" and Shiki connected to the network by nanomachines implanted in her brain.\n\nRemu was surprised but he accepted her decision until an accident called \"Early Rupture\" happened. The network server got overloaded and users' minds were lost in cyber space leaving soulless living bodies in the Body Pools. In order to bring Shiki's mind back, Remu visits her apartment in OMFC and there meets Shiki escaped from the hospital. But the girl tells him that she is not Shiki and she happens to haven taken over Shiki's body.\n\nWhen Remu tries to figure out the situation, a violent attack strikes the apartment.", "Arve Rezzle: Kikaijikake no Yousei-tachi", null, "アルヴ・レズル ―機械仕掛けの妖精たち―", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/82283/Arve_Rezzle__Kikaijikake_no_Yousei-tachi", 1 },
                    { 82285, "", 8, new DateTime(2013, 2, 28, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/142465.jpg", 45677, null, new DateTime(2012, 12, 25, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "A cyber battle sci-fi. In 2022, the technology of quantum computing has greatly advanced and many people have transfered their mind into the cyber space.\n\nRemu's sister, Shiki, skipped grades and entered a high school in the academic city \"Okinotori-island Mega Float City (OMFC)\" when she was 14. One day, Shiki confessed to her brother via Skype that she was talking to him directly from the cyber space and her real body had been kept in a water tank filled with a culture medium. It's called \"Body pool\" and Shiki connected to the network by nanomachines implanted in her brain.\n\nRemu was surprised but he accepted her decision until an accident called \"Early Rupture\" happened. The network server got overloaded and users' minds were lost in cyber space leaving soulless living bodies in the Body Pools. In order to bring Shiki's mind back, Remu visits her apartment in OMFC and there meets Shiki escaped from the hospital. But the girl tells him that she is not Shiki and she happens to haven taken over Shiki's body.\n\nWhen Remu tries to figure out the situation, a violent attack strikes the apartment.", "Arve Rezzle: Kikaijikake no Yousei-tachi", null, "アルヴ・レズル ―機械仕掛けの妖精たち―", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/82285/Arve_Rezzle__Kikaijikake_no_Yousei-tachi", 1 },
                    { 82289, null, 13, new DateTime(2013, 2, 28, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/142467.jpg", 45679, null, new DateTime(2012, 9, 30, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, null, "Unknown Arve: Kindan no Yousei-tachi", null, "アンノウン・アルヴ ―禁断の妖精たち―", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/82289/Unknown_Arve__Kindan_no_Yousei-tachi", 1 },
                    { 82795, "Sword Art Online Alternative: Gun Gale Online has been published in English by Yen Press under the Yen On imprint since June 26, 2018.", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/180432.jpg", 2247, 7.6m, new DateTime(2014, 12, 9, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "A brand-new battlefield awaits!\n\nKaren Kohiruimaki is a college student who stands at an imposing six feet. While her complex about her height makes it hard for her to make friends in the real world, the VRMMO Gun Gale Online changes everything. Now equipped with her ideal \"mini\" avatar and clad in a pink battle suit, Karen is ready to shoot up the world of GGO as Llenn! Before long, she meets the beautiful Pitohui, and the two rare female players become fast friends. Little does Llenn know that this friendship is the key to her entry in the first-ever Squad Jam, a team-based battle royale that echoes the famous Bullet of Bullets tournament...\n\n(Source: Yen Press)", "Sword Art Online Alternative: Gun Gale Online", "Sword Art Online Alternative: Gun Gale Online", "ソードアート・オンライン オルタナティブ ガンゲイル・オンライン", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/82795/Sword_Art_Online_Alternative__Gun_Gale_Online", null },
                    { 82801, "Tony Takezaki no Evangelion was published in English as Tony Takezaki's Neon Genesis Evangelion by Dark Horse on June 9, 2015.", 36, new DateTime(2011, 9, 2, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/143805.jpg", 8228, 7.04m, new DateTime(2010, 10, 3, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Neon Genesis Evangelion's official parody manga.", "Tony Takezaki no Evangelion", "Tony Takezaki's Neon Genesis Evangelion", "トニーたけざきのエヴァンゲリオン", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/82801/Tony_Takezaki_no_Evangelion", 1 },
                    { 83187, "Magical Pâtissière Kosaki-chan!! has been published in Spanish by Ivrea beginning since December 2015.", 43, new DateTime(2016, 9, 21, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/157716.jpg", 11957, 6.8m, new DateTime(2014, 11, 30, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Kosaki, Chitoge and Marika are bestowed upon powers of a magical girl who shall preserve peace in the world with Kosaki serving as their leader.\n\n(Source: Nisekoi WIkia)", "Magical Pâtissière Kosaki-chan!!", null, "マジカルパティシエ小咲ちゃん!!", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/83187/Magical_Pâtissière_Kosaki-chan", 4 },
                    { 83257, "The Last: Naruto the Movie was published in Spanish by Planeta Cómic on July 2, 2019.", 5, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/144797.jpg", 1067, 7.87m, new DateTime(2014, 12, 7, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The moon is beginning to fall, and at the rate it's going, it is doomed to fall on the Earth. The countdown for the survival of the planet begins. Among the havoc, Hinata's younger sister Hanabi is captured by the mysterious enemy, Toneri Ootsutsuki. Naruto must overcome great danger on a mission to save Hanabi and the world along with Hinata, Sai, Shikamaru, and Sakura in their final story.\n\n(Source: ANN)", "The Last: Naruto the Movie", null, "THE LAST -NARUTO THE MOVIE-", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/83257/The_Last__Naruto_the_Movie", 1 },
                    { 83411, "Atom: The Beginning has been published in English by Titan Comics under the Titan Manga imprint since October 11, 2022. The series has been published in Spanish by Milky Way Ediciones since April 27, 2017.", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/157917.jpg", 3046, 7.48m, new DateTime(2014, 11, 30, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "The prequel to one of the most influential mangas of all time: Astro Boy by Osamu Tezuka!\n\nA sci-fi manga about the turbulent lives of two robotics engineering students and their latest revolutionary project: the unassuming yet insanely strong A106, or \"Six.\"\n\nAtom: The Beginning blazes its own trail, as well as speaking to fans of the iconic Astro Boy and Osamu Tezuka. It's story full of hear and humor for fans of action-packed science fiction, robots, and manga.\n\n(Source: Titan Comics)", "Atom: The Beginning", "Atom: The Beginning", "アトム ザ・ビギニング", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/83411/Atom__The_Beginning", null },
                    { 83729, "", 14, new DateTime(2015, 12, 11, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/145365.jpg", 45863, null, new DateTime(2014, 12, 11, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Around the same time Slaine and Trillram went down to New Awara where Inaho and the others were, up at Sapporo, Hokkaido, twin Martian Knights sisters who pilot a Kataphrakt unit from the Vers Empire were landing in the town where the twin siblings Mizuki and Haruya Mikage live...", "Aldnoah.Zero Gaiden: Twin Gemini", null, "ALDNOAH.ZERO外伝 TWIN GEMINI", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/83729/AldnoahZero_Gaiden__Twin_Gemini", 4 },
                    { 83807, "", 10, new DateTime(2016, 3, 2, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/163711.jpg", 1123, 7.85m, new DateTime(2014, 12, 26, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The college basketball team Strky, comprised of familiar faces from past Interhigh tournaments, is ready to face off against the Jabberwock, a popular American street basketball team that has just arrived in Japan. But what they believe will be a friendly match against a foreign team turns into a devastating loss, and afterwards, the Jabberwock's captain Nash Gold Jr. comments that the people of Japan are equivalent to monkeys and should stop pretending to play basketball.\n\nAngered by this insult, Kagetora Aida proposes a rematch with a different Japanese team, to which Nash accepts, believing the outcome will be the exact same. For the revenge match, Kagetora assembles the Vorpal Swords, consisting of the Generation of Miracles alongside Tetsuya Kuroko and Taiga Kagami—the only team that stands a chance in teaching the Jabberwock a lesson.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Kuroko no Basket: Extra Game", null, "黒子のバスケ EXTRA GAME", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/83807/Kuroko_no_Basket__Extra_Game", 2 },
                    { 84427, null, null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/146237.jpg", 8162, 7.04m, new DateTime(2014, 12, 16, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, null, "Nanatsu no Taizai Gaiden", null, "小説 七つの大罪 ―外伝―", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/84427/Nanatsu_no_Taizai_Gaiden", null },
                    { 85033, "", 33, new DateTime(2003, 8, 31, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/147401.jpg", 46011, null, new DateTime(2003, 3, 19, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "An anthology of Kidou Senshi Gundam by various mangaka.", "Kidou Senshi Gundam: The Anthology", null, "機動戦士ガンダム THE ANTHOLOGY", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/85033/Kidou_Senshi_Gundam__The_Anthology", 2 },
                    { 85391, "", null, new DateTime(1986, 2, 18, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/148097.jpg", 46048, null, new DateTime(1985, 2, 18, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The year is Universal Century 0087. Seven years have passed since the end of the One Year War. In its zeal to stamp out any remaining opposition, the Earth Federation has organized the Titans, an elite fighting force. However, the Titans soon get out of hand, committing atrocities on par with the worst the Principality of Zeon had to offer during the war. In response, dissatisfied citizens, former Zeon soldiers, and even members of the Earth Federal Forces form a resistance group known as the Anti-Earth Union Group, or AEUG. As the next war is brewing, a small AEUG group arrives at Side 7 to investigate the new Gundam Mk. II...\n\n(Source: ANN)", "Kidou Senshi Zeta Gundam", null, "機動戦士Ｚ〈ゼータ〉ガンダム", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/85391/Kidou_Senshi_Zeta_Gundam", 5 },
                    { 85393, "", null, new DateTime(1986, 12, 25, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/148101.jpg", 46049, null, new DateTime(1986, 6, 30, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "As the continuation of Zeta Gundam, this series once again follows the story of the Anti Earth Union Group (AEUG) battleship Argama after Zeta's final episode. To fight off the Axis Zeon, now called the Neo Zeon, Captain Bright Noa recruits a group of teenage junk collectors led by the loudmouthed but powerful Newtype Judau Ashta to pilot the Argama's mobile suits. Now sporting a line up of the behemoth MSZ-010 Double Zeta Gundam and the returning MSZ-006 Zeta Gundam, RX-178 Gundam Mk-II and Gundam-like MSN-00100 Hyaku Shiki, the group is nicknamed the Gundam Team. As such, this became the first of a number of Gundam series where a team of Gundam mobile suits fight alongside each other regularly. The climax takes place at Side 3 in the Battle of Axis.\n\n(Source: Gundam Wikia)", "Kidou Senshi Gundam ZZ", "Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ", "機動戦士ガンダムZZ", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/85393/Kidou_Senshi_Gundam_ZZ", 2 },
                    { 85707, "Durarara!! RE;Dollars-hen has been published in English as Durarara!! Re;Dollars Arc by Yen Press since June 5, 2018.", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/160114.jpg", 3200, 7.46m, new DateTime(2014, 11, 17, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "Known for his short temper, Shizuo Heiwajima sends a whole biker gang from Saitama to the hospital. Their leader, the strong and handsome womanizer Chikage Rokujou, comes to Ikebukuro to settle the score. However, Shizuo is not his only target; he and his gang intend to also take revenge on the Dollars, who have apparently been wreaking havoc in Saitama.\n\nWhile Masaomi Kida is gone, Mikado Ryuugamine runs into an unusual problem. His new junior, Aoba Kuronuma, effortlessly finds out about the Dollars' leader and insists on befriending Mikado. Although Mikado tries to distance himself from the Dollars following the advice of an anonymous user—who he assumes is Kida—their online chat's newest member shares unsettling stories of the gang being violent, which makes it difficult to ignore.\n\nMeanwhile, Celty Sturluson goes on a job for yakuza member Haruya Shiki. In her absence, Shizuo is attacked by a young girl who refuses to explain the reason behind it. As Shinra Kishitani tries to help, a mysterious Russian pair shows up with but one goal: to kidnap the strange girl.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Durarara!! RE;Dollars-hen", "Durarara!! Re;Dollars Arc", "デュラララ!! RE；ダラーズ編", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/85707/Durarara_RE_Dollars-hen", null },
                    { 85781, "Dungeon Meshi ranked first and sixth in the 2016 and 2017 Kono Manga ga Sugoi! for the Male Readers division, respectively. The manga was also nominated for the Manga Taisho Award for four consecutive years from 2016 to 2019. The series was published in English as Delicious in Dungeon by Yen Press from May 23, 2017, to July 23, 2024. It was also released in Italian by J-POP from February 1, 2017, to April 24, 2024; in Spanish by Milky Way Ediciones since February 27, 2017; and in French by Casterman since May 17, 2017.", 102, new DateTime(2023, 9, 14, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/148949.jpg", 51, 8.74m, new DateTime(2014, 2, 14, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "After the Golden Kingdom is sunk underground by an insane magician, its king emerges, promising all of his treasure to any who defeat the magician, before crumbling to dust. Guilds are spurred on by this promise, traversing the labyrinthine dungeon in search of the magician. Laios Touden, the leader of one such guild, encounters a dragon that wipes out his party and devours his sister, Falin. Despite having lost the entirety of their supplies and belongings, Laios along with Marcille Donato, an elven healer, and Chilchuck Tims, a halfling thief, immediately reenter the dungeon, determined to save Falin.\n\nTime being of the essence, Laios suggests the taboo of eating the monsters of the dungeon as a means of gathering supplies. Upon the preparation of their first meal in the dungeon, they are stopped by an on-looking dwarf named Senshi. An enthusiast of monster cooking, he helps them prepare their monster ingredients for safe consumption. After learning of Laios' circumstances, Senshi expresses his desire to cook a dragon and joins their guild, thus beginning their food-filled foray into the dungeon together.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Dungeon Meshi", "Delicious in Dungeon", "ダンジョン飯", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/85781/Dungeon_Meshi", 14 },
                    { 85884, "Mahou Shoujo Madoka★Magica: Homura Revenge! was published in English as Puella Magi Madoka Magica: Homura's Revenge! by Yen Press from July 21, 2015, to October 27, 2015. It was also released in Brazilian Portuguese by NewPOP Editora from June 10, 2022, to July 31, 2022.", 9, new DateTime(2013, 10, 9, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/149731.jpg", 4445, 7.33m, new DateTime(2012, 6, 7, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Failing to prevail in the destined battle against Walpurgis Night, Homura Akemi uses her power to go back to a time before Madoka Kaname becomes a magical girl. Despite being prepared to endure the events once more, Homura is met with a surprising development: Madoka can remember everything from the previous timeline!\n\nKnowing what to expect in the coming weeks, Madoka and Homura resolve to save their friends and change their unfortunate fate. However, the two are not the only ones armed with new tactics—the apathetic Kyuubey reveals that it too has retained its memories. To stay on track with their plans, the girls must thwart the Incubator's schemes or risk losing their only chance at a promising future.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Mahou Shoujo Madoka★Magica: Homura Revenge!", "Puella Magi Madoka★Magica: Homura's Revenge", "魔法少女まどか★マギカ ほむらリベンジ!", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/85884/Mahou_Shoujo_Madoka★Magica__Homura_Revenge", 2 },
                    { 85900, "Kuroko no Basuke: Replace Plus was published in Italian by Edizioni Star Comics.", 66, new DateTime(2018, 4, 23, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/157861.jpg", 2249, 7.6m, new DateTime(2015, 1, 26, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The \"Generation of Miracles\" is a name given to a team of five middle school basketball prodigies who led Teikou Middle School to win three consecutive championship titles. Underneath all of the prestige, they are middle school students with middle school problems at the end of the day. From managing their crushes to planning the perfect summer vacation, these prodigies find themselves in typical age-appropriate situations in the company of amusing friends and teammates.\n\nAdapted from the light novels of the same series, Kuroko no Basuke: Replace Plus follows the antics of Tetsuya Kuroko and the Generation of Miracles before they went their separate ways. Intermixed with the hilarity are anecdotes from their high school teammates, who also end up in strangely hilarious situations outside the court.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Kuroko no Basket: Replace Plus", null, "黒子のバスケ Replace PLUS", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/85900/Kuroko_no_Basket__Replace_Plus", 10 },
                    { 85924, "", null, new DateTime(2020, 3, 9, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/159421.jpg", 14744, 6.6m, new DateTime(2014, 12, 24, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Set in 2025, a roboticist named Fudou Yuuki joins a project involving a large mural depicting humanity's true past as well as the ancient but advanced technology found in Antarctica.\n\n(Source: Devilman Wikia)", "Devilman Saga", null, "デビルマンサーガ", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/85924/Devilman_Saga", 13 },
