                    { 152709, "Saijaku Tamer wa Gomi Hiroi no Tabi wo Hajimemashita. began as a web novel on Shousetsuka ni Narou on August 9, 2018. The first official volume was published on November 9, 2019 by TO Books under the TO Books Ranobe label. The series has been published in English as The Weakest Tamer Began a Journey to Pick Up Trash by Seven Seas Entertainment under the Airship imprint since October 25, 2022.", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/270429.jpg", 2770, 7.52m, new DateTime(2019, 11, 8, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "In Ivy's world, stars are everything. She's a Tamer, born to subdue monsters and animals, but she was also born starless! With her life in danger, Ivy flees into the forest where she befriends a weak little slime named Sora—the one creature she can tame. Together, the unlikely pair set off on a journey, salvaging rubbish to survive. Along the way they'll win hearts, evade danger, and discover there's more to starless Ivy than meets the eye!\n\n(Source: Seven Seas Entertainment)", "Saijaku Tamer wa Gomi Hiroi no Tabi wo Hajimemashita.", "The Weakest Tamer Began a Journey to Pick Up Trash", "最弱テイマーはゴミ拾いの旅を始めました。", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/152709/Saijaku_Tamer_wa_Gomi_Hiroi_no_Tabi_wo_Hajimemashita", null },
                    { 152986, "", 5, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/270953.jpg", 36584, null, new DateTime(2022, 3, 18, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Norainu Iggy takes place before Stardust Crusaders set in 1980's Downtown New York City and features the battle between Iggy and Muhammad Avdol.\n\n(Source: JoJo Wiki, edited)", "Norainu Iggy", "Iggy the Stray Dog", "野良犬イギー", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/152986/Norainu_Iggy", 1 },
                    { 153000, "Naruto: Konoha Shinden - Yukemuri Ninpouchou was released to celebrate the 20th anniversary of the Naruto anime. It is set approximately between the end of the Naruto parent series and the beginning of the Boruto: Naruto Next Generations sequel. The series was published digitally as an English simulpub as Naruto: Konoha's Story - The Steam Ninja Scrolls: The Manga through MANGA Plus. The volumes were published by VIZ Media under the Shonen Jump imprint from July 9, 2024, to October 8, 2024. It has also been published in German by Carlsen since July 2, 2024.", 15, new DateTime(2023, 5, 26, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/282751.jpg", 14247, 6.64m, new DateTime(2022, 10, 28, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Lively teenager Mirai Sarutobi is determined to become a respected ninja, aspiring to match the legacies of her late father, Asuma, and grandfather, Third Hokage Hiruzen. As a regular bodyguard for Seventh Hokage Naruto Uzumaki, the active village leader, she feels she is steadily progressing toward her goal. When entrusted with escorting Sixth Hokage Kakashi Hatake during a border inspection, an eager Mirai senses a chance to establish her reputation by defending Kakashi against countless enemies. But what she anticipates to be a perilous, career-defining two-day mission turns out to be a leisurely 20-day vacation.\n\nReeling from her disappointment, Mirai struggles to enjoy touring hot springs alongside the absent-minded Kakashi and his overzealous friend Guy Might. As Mirai finally relaxes, however, she is suddenly offered a tantalizing opportunity—one that may just be too good to be true.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Naruto: Konoha Shinden - Yukemuri Ninpouchou", "Naruto: Konoha's Story - The Steam Ninja Scrolls: The Manga", "NARUTO-ナルト- 木ノ葉新伝 湯煙忍法帖", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/153000/Naruto__Konoha_Shinden_-_Yukemuri_Ninpouchou", 2 },
                    { 153037, "", 7, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/285439.jpg", 3925, 7.38m, new DateTime(2020, 10, 15, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Tanjirou, along with Zenitsu, Inosuke, Nezuko, arrives at their next mission's destination, the Mugen Train, where over 40 individuals have vanished within a brief span of time. Teaming up with Kyoujurou, the Flame Hashira, Tanjirou confronts the hidden demon lurking within the train. However, what awaits them is an endless dream...!?\n\n(Source: Shueisha, translated)", "Gekijouban Kimetsu no Yaiba: Mugen Ressha-hen Novelize", null, "劇場版 鬼滅の刃 無限列車編 ノベライズ", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/153037/Gekijouban_Kimetsu_no_Yaiba__Mugen_Ressha-hen_Novelize", 1 },
                    { 153082, null, null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/273361.jpg", 36608, null, new DateTime(2022, 10, 16, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, null, "Shousetsu Blue Lock: Tatakai no Mae, Bokura wa.", null, "小説 ブルーロック 戦いの前、僕らは。", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/153082/Shousetsu_Blue_Lock__Tatakai_no_Mae_Bokura_wa", null },
                    { 153208, "Koutetsu Jeeg was published in Italian by Dynamic Italia in 2002, by d/visual in 2008, and by Edizioni BD under the J-POP imprint on November 8, 2013.", 10, new DateTime(1976, 4, 30, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/271341.jpg", 30395, null, new DateTime(1975, 6, 30, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "The story tells about Hiroshi Shiba, a car racer who is mortally wounded on a laboratory accident, but restored to life by his father, Professor Shiba, a talented scientist/archeologist, who is incidentally investigating the relics of the ancient Yamatai Kingdom. The professor discovers a tiny bronze bell with sorcerous powers, and shortly afterwards he is murdered by the henchmen of Queen Himika, the ruler of the Yamatai (sometimes translated as Jamatai) Kingdom, who wants to seize the ancient bell and its power.\n\n(Source: MU)", "Koutetsu Jeeg", null, "鋼鉄ジーグ", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/153208/Koutetsu_Jeeg", 2 },
                    { 153266, "", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/282713.jpg", 33361, null, new DateTime(2022, 11, 25, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "A.S. (Ad Stella) 122―An era when a multitude of corporations have entered space and built a huge economic system. A lone girl from the remote planet Mercury transfers to the Asticassia School of Technology, run by the Beneritt Group which dominates the mobile suit industry. Her name is Suletta Mercury. With a scarlet light burning in her pure heart, this girl walks step by step through a new world.\n\n(Source: Crunchyroll)", "Shousetsu Kidou Senshi Gundam: Suisei no Majo", "Mobile Suit Gundam: The Witch from Mercury", "小説 機動戦士ガンダム 水星の魔女", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/153266/Shousetsu_Kidou_Senshi_Gundam__Suisei_no_Majo", null },
                    { 153622, "Ore wa Subete wo \"Parry\" Suru: Gyaku Kanchigai no Sekai Saikyou wa Boukensha ni Naritai began as a web novel on Shousetsuka ni Narou on October 17, 2019. The first official volume was published on September 15, 2020 by Earth Star Entertainment under the Earth Star Novel label. The series has been published digitally in English as I Parry Everything: What Do You Mean I'm the Strongest? I'm Not Even an Adventurer Yet! by J-Novel Club since February 28, 2023.", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/273087.jpg", 33411, null, new DateTime(2020, 9, 14, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "The Kingdom of Clays faces a dire crisis: an assassination attempt has just been made on its own Princess Lynneburg, and its neighboring countries eye the aftermath like starving vultures, plotting the Kingdom's downfall. The ensuing conflict will shape the face of the continent for centuries to come...but Noor doesn't have a clue about any of that! Having freshly arrived at the royal capital after over a decade of rigorous, isolated training at his mountain home, he's dead set on achieving his childhood dream of becoming an adventurer, even if the only skills he possesses are useless ones. Sure, he can \"Parry\" thousands of swords in the span of a single breath, but everybody knows you need more than that if you want to be an adventurer! Our hero's road to making his dream come true will be long(?) and arduous(?)—but if there's one thing Noor's not afraid of, it's some good ol' fashioned hard work!\n\n(Source: J-Novel Club)", "Ore wa Subete wo \"Parry\" suru: Gyaku Kanchigai no Sekai Saikyou wa Boukensha ni Naritai", "I Parry Everything: What Do You Mean I'm the Strongest? I'm Not Even an Adventurer Yet!", "俺は全てを【パリイ】する ～逆勘違いの世界最強は冒険者になりたい～", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/153622/Ore_wa_Subete_wo_Parry_suru__Gyaku_Kanchigai_no_Sekai_Saikyou_wa_Boukensha_ni_Naritai", null },
                    { 154021, "", 6, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/1/273077.jpg", 36771, null, new DateTime(2022, 11, 3, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "Extra! Extra! Read all about the Third Division! After all, who wouldn't want to memorize every little tidbit about the talented folks saving Japan from the threat of monstrous kaiju? In this exposé, you'll get an exclusive sneak peek into the lives of the heroes, including new recruits Kafka and Reno and their brutal training, star soldier Kikoru Shinomiya and the story behind her weapon, and Vice-Captain Hoshina and his secret worries! Want to know more about the Third Division? Read on!\n\n(Source: VIZ Media)", "Kaijuu 8-gou: Micchaku! Dai-3 Butai", "Kaiju No. 8: Exclusive on the Third Division", "怪獣8号 密着！第3部隊", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/154021/Kaijuu_8-gou__Micchaku_Dai-3_Butai", 1 },
                    { 154487, "", null, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/3/287234.jpg", 38782, null, new DateTime(2022, 11, 16, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "After a disastrous defeat at the 2018 World Cup, Japan's team struggles to regroup. But what's missing? An absolute Ace Striker, who can guide them to the win. The Japan Football Union is hell-bent on creating a striker who hungers for goals and thirsts for victory, and who can be the decisive instrument in turning around a losing match...and to do so, they've gathered 300 of Japan's best and brightest youth players. Who will emerge to lead the team...and will they be able to out-muscle and out-ego everyone who stands in their way?\n\n(Source: Kodansha USA)", "Shousetsu Blue Lock", null, "小説 ブルーロック", 5, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/154487/Shousetsu_Blue_Lock", null },
                    { 154545, "Youkoso Jitsuryoku Shijou Shugi no Kyoushitsu e 0 was included with volume 1 of the limited-edition Blu-Ray/DVD of Youkoso Jitsuryoku Shijou Shugi no Kyoushitsu e 2nd Season.", 8, null, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/manga/2/295562.jpg", 263, 8.34m, new DateTime(2022, 12, 22, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "This may be a story of the past that had been concealed, and mustn't be seen.\n\nAbout 20 years before Kiyotaka Ayanokouji enrolled at Advanced Nurturing High School. There was a man. Atsuomi Ayanokouji, aged 31. A politician. Atsuomi was born as a \"have-not\" in Japan's society of disparity, but there was one thing he possessed more than anybody else: his uncontrollable, ever-expanding \"ambition.\"\n\nAtsuomi had been doing dirty work for Jinnosuke Naoe, the head of the Naoe faction that he was a part of. As a chance to reward all the hard work that he had done, Naoe offers him a top-secret project: the founding of an institution for a \"Talented Persons Nurturing Program,\" which is under the direct control of the government. Atsuomi, who is busy pursuing his ambitions, brings them to fruition and names the institution he establishes the White Room. He had also started on another project: to get his own biological child to join him in the White Room.\n\nThis is the beginning of everything. A story about the \"dissection\" of Kiyotaka Ayanokouji. Within a cold white room, what does the future look like in the eyes of a young child?\n\n(Source: Kadokawa, translated)", "Youkoso Jitsuryoku Shijou Shugi no Kyoushitsu e 0", null, "ようこそ実力至上主義の教室へ0", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/manga/154545/Youkoso_Jitsuryoku_Shijou_Shugi_no_Kyoushitsu_e_0", 1 },
